directions:
1. For the meatloaf, finely dice the chorizo, dice the onion, whisk the egg, mince or finely dice the garlic, chop the fresh parsley and cut each bacon slice into 2 pieces. For the slaw, thinly slice the cabbage and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease a 9-inch by 5-inch (23 cm by 13 cm) loaf pan and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, chorizo, onion, egg, coconut milk, almond flour, garlic, and fresh parsley. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. If needed, add additional coconut milk if the mixture is too dry.
  4. Place the mixture in the greased loaf pan and cover the top completely with the bacon.
  5. Place the loaf pan in the oven and bake for 60 minutes. Check with a meat thermometer that the internal temperature reaches 160°F (71°C). 
  6. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, toss to combine the cabbage with the olive oil, lemon juice, fennel seeds, and fresh parsley. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. 
  7. Slice the meatloaf and serve with the slaw.

name: Keto One-Pan Huevos Rancheros
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 slices of bacon (56 g), diced
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), diced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 1 chili pepper (14 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, bell pepper, tomato and onion. Finely dice the chili pepper, seeds removed. Mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. Add the olive oil to a large frying pan or skillet over medium-high heat. 
  3. Add the bacon, bell pepper, tomato, onion, optional chili pepper, and garlic to the pan. Saute until the vegetables are tender, about 8 to 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Make 4 indentations in the vegetable mixture and break an egg into each indentation.
  5. Cover the pan and cook for 3 to 5 minutes until the egg whites are solid and the yolks are slightly runny.
  6. Sprinkle with the fresh cilantro and serve immediately.

name: Keto Coconut Chicken Curry
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 2 cups of chicken broth (480 ml)
  • 1 carrot (50 g), diced
  • 0.25 cup of coconut cream (60 ml) (from the top of 1 refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 1 Tablespoon of curry powder (7 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast, onion and carrot. Mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a large saucepan, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and onion to the saucepan and saute until the chicken is browned, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken broth and carrot to the saucepan. Reduce the heat and let simmer for 30 minutes until the chicken is tender and cooked through.
  4. Add the coconut cream, curry powder and garlic to the saucepan. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide between 2 plates and garnish with fresh cilantro.

name: Keto Hot and Sour Soup
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 3 cups of chicken broth (720 ml)
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 2 chili peppers (28 g), diced (or to taste) (optional)
  • 1 Tablespoon of vinegar (15 ml) (or more, to taste)
  • 1 Tablespoon of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (15 ml) (or more, to taste)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of fish sauce (5 ml)
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), spiralized or grated
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • 2 green onions (10 g), finely chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast, tomato and chili peppers. Mince or finely dice the fresh ginger, spiralize or grate the zucchini, chop the fresh cilantro and finely chop the green onions.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the chicken breast to the saucepan and saute until cooked through, about 7 to 10 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken broth, tomato, optional chili peppers, vinegar, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, fresh ginger and fish sauce to the saucepan and cook for 5 minutes.
  4. Remove from the heat and add the zucchini and fresh cilantro to the saucepan. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and garnish with green onions.

name: Keto Chili Crusted Pork Tenderloin
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of onion powder (7 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of chili powder (4 g), (or to taste)
  • 2 teaspoons of paprika (4 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of cumin powder (2 g)
  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). 
  2. In a small bowl, combine the garlic powder, onion powder, chili powder, paprika and cumin powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Rub the mixture into the tenderloin, covering completely.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over high heat. Add the tenderloin to the skillet and sear on all sides, about 2 minutes per side, using tongs to turn over the tenderloin. Place the tenderloin and the skillet drippings on a rimmed baking sheet.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes until the center of the pork is slightly pink with an internal temperature of 145 F (63 C). Let the tenderloin rest for 5 minutes before slicing and serving.

name: Keto Large Salad with Creamy Lemon Aioli
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), sliced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced

For the creamy lemon aioli -

  • 4 Tablespoons of mayo (60 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of lemon zest (2 g)
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the romaine lettuce. Slice the cucumber, avocado and tomato, and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a bowl, whisk to combine the lemon aioli ingredients.
  3. Toss the aioli with the romaine lettuce leaves, cucumber, avocado, tomato, and onion.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Cod Kedgeree
ingredients:
• 2 medium eggs (96 g)
  • 3 Tablespoons of ghee (45 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 2 filets of cod, fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of curry powder (7 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of garlic powder (5 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of cumin powder (2 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Defrost the cod filets if frozen. Process the cauliflower into rice-like pieces and dice the onion. Minced or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger. Chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove from heat and put the lid on the pot. Let sit for 12 minutes and then drain the eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel the eggs and slice each one in half.
  3. Meanwhile, in a large pan, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of ghee over medium heat. Add the cod and cook for 4 minutes. Carefully turn over and cook for an additional 4 to 5 minutes or until cooked through. Remove from the pan and flake. Set aside.
  4. In the same pan, melt the remaining 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of ghee over medium-high heat. Add the cauliflower, onion, curry powder, garlic cloves, fresh ginger, garlic powder and cumin powder to the pan. Saute for 10 minutes until the vegetables are soft. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Return the cod to the skillet and add the lime juice. Season with additional salt and pepper, to taste, if desired.
  6. Divide the cod kedgeree between 2 plates and garnish with the fresh cilantro. Serve with the sliced eggs.

name: Keto Garlic Beef Eggplant Saute
ingredients:
• 2 beef steaks (400 g), sliced into strips
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 medium eggplant (500 g), diced
  • 2 green onions (10 g), chopped
  • 1 teaspoon of vinegar (5 ml) (of choice)
  • 1 Tablespoon of cumin powder (6 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the beef steaks into strips. Mince or finely dice the garlic, dice the eggplant and chop the green onions.
  2. Season the beef with salt, to taste.
  3. In a large skillet, heat 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil over medium-high heat. Add the garlic and saute until fragrant, about 30 seconds.
  4. Add the beef to the skillet and cook to desired doneness, about 2 to 3 minutes for medium-rare. Remove from the skillet and set aside.
  5. In the same skillet, add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil. Add the eggplant and green onions to the skillet. Saute until the eggplant starts to brown, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  6. Cover the skillet and continue to cook for an additional 5 minutes or until the eggplant is soft.
  7. Return the beef to the skillet and add the vinegar and cumin. Stir well to combine. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  8. Divide the beef and eggplant between 2 plates and enjoy.

name: Keto Mustard-Ghee Chicken
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 0.25 cup of chicken broth (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large pan, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the pan and saute until browned, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken broth and mustard to the pan. Cook for 10 minutes until the liquid is reduced.
  4. Add the spinach to the pan and cook until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  5. Add the garlic to the pan and season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Chicken Adobo with Cauli-Rice
ingredients:
For the chicken adobo -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook chicken with
  • 4 chicken breasts (800 g), chopped
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), chopped
  • 8 cloves of garlic (24 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 cup of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (120 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) + 2 teaspoons of vinegar (10 ml) (of choice)
  • 1 green onion (5 g), finely chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the cauli-“rice” -

  • 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), food processed into rice-like pieces
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), to cook cauli-”rice” with
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the chicken adobo, chop the chicken breasts and onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and finely chop the green onion. For the “rice”, process the cauliflower into rice-like pieces.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the chicken, onion and garlic to the pan and saute until the chicken is cooked through, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  3. Reduce the heat to a simmer and add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos and vinegar to the pan. Cover and cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Meanwhile, to make the cauliflower “rice,” saute the cauliflower pieces in the coconut oil on high heat for 5 minutes until softened.
  5. Serve the chicken adobo over the cauli-“rice” and garnish with green onion.

name: Keto Zucchini Noodles with Shrimp and Pesto
ingredients:
For the pesto -

  • 0.5 cup of fresh basil leaves (16 g), roughly torn
  • 2 Tablespoons of pine nuts (16 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g)
  • 0.25 cup of olive oil (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the shrimp and zucchini “noodles” -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 lb of shrimp (225 g), fresh or defrosted, peeled and deveined
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), peeled
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the pesto, roughly tear the fresh basil leaves. For the “noodles”, defrost the shrimp if frozen then peel and devein and peel the zucchini.
  2. In a food processor or high-speed blender, pulse to combine the basil, pine nuts, and garlic. Slowly add the olive oil and continue to blend until smooth. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Set aside.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the shrimp and lemon juice to the skillet. Saute for 2 to 4 minutes until the shrimp are opaque and fully cooked.
  4. Remove the skillet from the heat and add the pesto to the skillet, stirring well to combine. Season with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
  5. Make the zucchini “noodles” by using the shredding attachment of a food processor, a spiralizer, or a potato peeler to create pasta-like strands or shreds.
  6. Divide the zucchini “noodles” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the pesto shrimp.

name: Keto Creamy Tuna and Avocado Salad
ingredients:
• 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of mustard (5 ml)
  • 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), diced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the romaine lettuce, drain and flake the tuna and dice the cucumber and avocado.
  2. In a large bowl, toss the romaine lettuce leaves with the mayo and mustard. Add the tuna, cucumber, and avocado to the bowl. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Pork Tenderloin with Braised Cabbage
ingredients:
For the pork tenderloin -

  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • Salt, to taste

For the braised cabbage -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook the cabbage with
  • 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 0.25 cup of chicken broth (60 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of vinegar (5 ml) (of choice)
  • 1 teaspoon of fennel seeds (2 g) (optional)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the braised cabbage, chop the cabbage and dice the onion.
  2. Cut the pork tenderloin in half to form 2 shorter pieces. Pat dry the tenderloin and generously season each half with salt.
  3. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over high heat. Add the tenderloin to the skillet and brown on all sides, about 2 to 3 minutes per side, using tongs to turn over the tenderloin.
  4. Reduce the heat to medium and continue to cook until the internal temperature reaches 145 F (63 C) for medium-rare. Remove the tenderloin from the skillet and let rest for 5 minutes.
  5. Meanwhile, in a separate skillet, melt an additional 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the cabbage and onions to the skillet and saute until slightly browned, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  6. Reduce the heat and add the chicken broth, vinegar, and optional fennel seeds to the skillet. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
  7. Remove the cover and continue to cook until the liquid has evaporated, stirring constantly. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  8. Serve the pork tenderloin with the braised cabbage.

name: Keto Thai Green Chicken Curry
ingredients:
• 1 cup of coconut milk (240 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of fresh cilantro (4 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • 1 chili pepper (14 g), seeds removed (optional)
  • 1 Tablespoon of curry powder (7 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of ginger powder (4 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Remove the seeds of the chili pepper and dice the chicken breast, bell pepper and onion.
  2. To make the curry sauce, blend the coconut milk, fresh cilantro, lime juice, optional chili pepper, curry powder, garlic, and ginger powder until smooth. Set aside.
  3. In a large skillet or pan, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken, bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until the chicken is browned, about 5 minutes.
  4. Reduce the heat to low and add the curry sauce to the skillet. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the curry between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Zucchini Spaghetti and Meatballs
ingredients:
For the meatballs - 

  • 1 medium egg
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (4 g), finely chopped
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the “spaghetti” and sauce -

  • 1 zucchini (120 g), peeled
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (4 g), finely chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the meatballs, finely chop the fresh basil leaves and mince or finely dice the garlic. For the “spaghetti” and sauce, peel the zucchini, dice the tomato, mince or finely dice the garlic and finely chop the fresh basil leaves.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. In a large bowl, combine all of the meatball ingredients. Form the mixture into golf ball-size meatballs and place on a rimmed baking sheet.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 18 to 22 minutes or until cooked through with an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C).
  5. Meanwhile, make the zucchini “noodles” by using the shredding attachment of a food processor, a spiralizer, or a potato peeler to create pasta-like strands or shreds.
  6. Add the olive oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the zucchini “noodles”, tomato and garlic to the skillet and saute for 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Divide the “spaghetti” and sauce between 2 plates. Top with the meatballs and garnish with fresh basil.

name: Keto Spinach and Onion Egg Muffins
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with (plus additional to grease the muffin pan)
  • 0.5 lb of ground beef (225 g)
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g), chopped
  • 8 medium eggs, whisked
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of 1 refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the spinach, whisk the eggs and finely dice the onion.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease an 8-cup muffin pan and set aside.
  3. In a skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef to the skillet and saute until browned, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove the skillet from the heat and let cool.
  5. In a bowl, combine the whisked eggs, coconut cream, onion, and beef mixture. Season with additional salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the mixture into the greased muffin pan, filling each muffin cup about 2/3 full.
  6. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until the eggs are set.

name: Keto Baked Salmon with Roasted Cabbage Wedges
ingredients:
For the baked salmon -

  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the roasted cabbage -

  • 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), cut into 1-inch (2.5 cm) wedges
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml) (plus additional for coating the baking sheet)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the baked salmon, defrost the salmon filets if frozen. For the roasted cabbage, cut the cabbage into 1-inch (2.5 cm) wedges.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. Lightly coat the baking sheet with avocado oil and place the cabbage wedges on the baking sheet in a single layer. Brush each cabbage wedge with avocado oil. Season with salt, to taste.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until the cabbage is tender and edges are light brown.
  5. Meanwhile, lightly season the salmon with salt and pepper, to taste. Place each salmon filet on a piece of aluminum foil with 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil. Fold the aluminum foil to form packets and place on a baking sheet.
  6. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily.
  7. Serve the salmon with the roasted cabbage wedges.

name: Keto Beef Goulash
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), sliced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 lb of beef stew meat (450 g), cut into 1-inch (2.5 cm) cubes
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 5 white button mushrooms (50 g), quartered
  • 0.5 cup of beef broth (120 ml)
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of paprika (6 g)
  • 1 bay leaf (0.2 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the onion and bell pepper, mince or finely dice the garlic, cut the beef stew meat into 1-inch (2.5 cm) cubes, cut the white button mushrooms into quarters, dice the tomato and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large pot over high heat. Add the onion and garlic to the pot and saute until the onion is translucent, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the stew meat to the pot and saute until partially browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the bell pepper and mushrooms to the pot and saute for 5 minutes.
  5. Reduce the heat to very low and add the beef broth, tomato, paprika and bay leaf to the pot.
  6. Partially cover the pot with the lid and simmer for 60 minutes until the beef is fork-tender, stirring occasionally. Add additional water, 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) at a time, to prevent the mixture from sticking to the bottom of the pot, as needed.
  7. If the sauce is too thin, remove the lid and increase the heat slightly. Cook, stirring often, until the sauce is thick to your liking. Remove and discard the bay leaf. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  8. Divide among 4 bowls and garnish with fresh parsley.

name: Keto Bacon Asparagus Quiche
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 6 slices of bacon (168 g), diced
  • 4 spears of asparagus (64 g), chopped
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g), chopped
  • 10 medium eggs, whisked
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of 1 refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, onion and tomato. Chop the asparagus and spinach and whisk the eggs.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C).
  3. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 3 to 4 minutes. Remove the bacon with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  4. In the same skillet, add the asparagus and onion to the reserved bacon fat and saute for about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Remove the skillet from the heat and let cool.
  6. In a medium bowl, combine the eggs, coconut cream, bacon, tomato, and the cooled asparagus mixture. Season with additional salt and pepper, if desired. Pour the egg mixture into a greased 9-inch (23 cm) square baking dish.
  7. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 20 to 30 minutes until the eggs are set.

name: Keto Garlic Chicken Nuggets
ingredients:
• 0.5 cup of coconut flour (56 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of garlic powder (20 g)
  • 1 medium egg
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), for frying (plus additional, if needed)
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), cut into approx. 1.5-inch (4 cm) pieces
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. Cut the chicken breasts into approximately 1.5-inch (4 cm) pieces.
  2. In a bowl, combine the coconut flour and garlic powder. Taste the mixture and season with salt, as needed.
  3. In a separate bowl, whisk the egg to create an egg wash.
  4. In a large saucepan, melt the ghee over medium heat. (Alternatively, use a deep fryer to cook the nuggets.)
  5. Place each chicken piece into the egg wash and then cover completely with the coconut flour mixture.
  6. In batches, carefully place the “breaded” chicken pieces in a single layer in the hot ghee and fry until golden brown and the chicken is cooked through, about 10 minutes. Turn the chicken several times while frying to ensure even cooking on both sides of the nuggets.
  7. Remove the cooked nuggets from the pan and place on a paper towel-lined plate. Continue until all of the nuggets are cooked, adding more ghee to the pan in between batches, as needed.
  8. Enjoy the nuggets with a side dish, of choice.

name: Keto Turkey and Vegetable Skillet
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1.5 lbs of turkey breasts (675 g), diced
  • 8 slices of bacon (224 g), diced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), diced
  • 6 spears of asparagus (96 g), chopped
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g), chopped
  • 4 teaspoons of fresh thyme (4 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the turkey breasts, bacon and onion. Chop the asparagus, spinach and fresh thyme.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the turkey and bacon to the skillet and saute until slightly browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Add the onion, asparagus, spinach and fresh thyme to the skillet. Saute for an additional 10 minutes until the turkey and bacon are cooked through and the vegetables are soft. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Coconut Dijon Chicken Tossed with Avocado
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh thyme (3 g), chopped
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breasts and avocado. Chop the fresh thyme.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  3. Add the mustard and fresh thyme to the skillet. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Remove the skillet from the heat and toss the chicken with the avocado.
  5. Divide between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Rosemary Baked Salmon
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh rosemary (3 g), chopped
  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the fresh rosemary. Defrost the salmon filets if frozen.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C).
  3. In a bowl, mix to combine the olive oil, fresh rosemary and salt, to taste. Rub the olive oil mixture into the salmon filets.
  4. Wrap each salmon filet with any remaining olive oil in aluminum foil or parchment paper to form a packet. Place each packet on a baking sheet.
  5. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily.
  6. Serve the salmon with a side dish, of choice.

name: Keto Lemon Shrimp and Avocado Salad
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 lb of shrimp (450 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), diced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Peel and devein the shrimp, defrosted if frozen. Dice the avocado and tomato and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the shrimp to the hot skillet and saute until cooked through, about 4 to 5 minutes. Add the lemon juice to the skillet when there is about 1 minute left of cooking time.
  3. Remove the skillet from the heat and toss the shrimp with the avocado, tomato and fresh parsley. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the shrimp salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Ginger Shaking Beef
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1.5 lbs of ground beef (675 g)
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 0.5 cup of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (60 ml)
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh ginger (10 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the onion. Mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef to the skillet and saute until slightly browned, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the onion, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, garlic and fresh ginger to the skillet. Saute, stirring frequently, for an additional 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Dijon Pork Chops with Pan-Roasted Cauliflower
ingredients:
• 2 pork chops (320 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the cauliflower into small florets and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. Generously season the pork chops with salt and pepper.
  3. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over high heat.
  4. Place the pork chops into the skillet and cook on one side for 2 to 3 minutes. Cover one side of each pork chop with equal amounts of mustard. Using tongs, turn over the pork chops and cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes (or until done to your liking) with an internal temperature of 145 F (63 C) for medium. Set aside to rest for 5 minutes.
  5. Meanwhile, in a pot of salted water, parboil the cauliflower florets for 5 minutes.
  6. In a separate large skillet, add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil over high heat. Add the cauliflower and saute until golden brown and tender to your liking, about 4 to 6 minutes.
  7. Remove the skillet from the heat and toss the cauliflower with the fresh parsley. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  8. Serve the pork chops with the cauliflower.

name: Keto One-Pan Fried Sausages and Veg
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 lb of sausages of your choice (225 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), diced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of hot sauce (5 ml) (optional)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the sausages, zucchini, tomato and onion. Break the cauliflower into small florets and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. In a large pan, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the sausage, cauliflower, zucchini, tomato and onion to the skillet. Saute until the sausage is cooked through and the vegetables are slightly brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
  3. Add the mustard and optional hot sauce to the pan. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide between 2 plates and garnish with fresh parsley.

name: Keto Pan-Grilled Chicken and Guac
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), sliced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g)
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), diced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the chicken breasts, dice the tomato, dice or finely chop the garlic and chop the cilantro.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 8 to 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Meanwhile, in a bowl, mash the avocado and combine with the tomato, lime juice, garlic and fresh cilantro. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Serve the chicken with the guac.

name: Keto Deli Meat Avocado Wrap
ingredients:
• 8 slices of ham (224 g)
  • 4 Tablespoons of mayo (60 ml), divided
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium bell pepper (60 g), sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
directions:
1. Slice the avocado and bell pepper and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. Spread each ham slice with 0.5 Tablespoon (7.5 ml) of mayo. Place equal amounts of avocado, bell pepper and fresh parsley on the ham slices.
  3. Wrap the ham slices and enjoy.

name: Keto Salmon Tacos with Lime Radish Salsa
ingredients:
• 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped small
  • 1 stalk of celery (20 g), chopped small
  • 4 radishes (8 g), chopped small
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), finely chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of lime juice (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 2 cans of salmon (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), separated into individual leaves
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the tomato, celery stalks and radishes into small pieces. Finely chop the fresh cilantro, drain and flake the salmon, mince or finely dice the garlic and separate the romaine lettuce into individual leaves.
  2. To make the salsa, combine the tomato, celery, radishes and fresh cilantro with the lime juice. Set aside.
  3. Meanwhile, in a nonstick skillet, melt the coconut oil over high heat. Add the salmon and garlic to the skillet and saute until the salmon is heated through, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. To serve, fill the lettuce leaves with the salmon and top with the salsa.

name: Keto Mustard Chicken with Celery Avocado Slaw
ingredients:
For the mustard chicken -

  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), sliced into cutlets
  • 3 Tablespoons of mustard (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • Salt and pepper

For the celery avocado slaw -

  • 1 large avocado (200 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 stalks of celery (40 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of mayo (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of macadamia nuts (32 g), crushed
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the mustard chicken, slice the chicken breasts into cutlets. For the slaw, thinly slice the avocado and celery stalks and crush the macadamia nuts.
  2. If needed, pound the chicken cutlets to ensure they are equal in thickness.
  3. Completely cover the chicken cutlets with the mustard. Season with salt and pepper.
  4. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over high heat. In batches, add the chicken cutlets and cook until golden brown with an internal temperature of 165°F (75°C), about 3 minutes per side. 
  5. Meanwhile, toss the avocado and celery with the mayo and lime juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste, and top with the macadamia nuts.
  6. Serve the chicken cutlets with the slaw.

name: Keto Bacon and Broccoli Soup
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), chopped
  • 2 stalks of celery (40 g), chopped
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), broken into small florets
  • 1 cup of chicken broth (240 ml)
  • 1 cup of coconut milk (240 ml)
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the onion and celery stalks. Mince or finely dice the garlic, break the broccoli into small florets and dice the bacon.
  2. In a saucepan, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the onion, celery and garlic to the saucepan and saute for 5 minutes.
  3. Add the broccoli, chicken broth and coconut milk to the saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes until the broccoli is tender.
  4. Use an immersion blender to puree the soup until smooth. (Alternatively, let the soup cool slightly and puree using a food processor or high-speed blender.) Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Meanwhile, in a nonstick skillet, cook the bacon until crispy, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  6. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and top with the bacon.

name: Keto Zucchini Squash Vegetable Chili
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), chopped
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium bell pepper (60 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 4 radishes (8 g), diced
  • 1 cup of chicken broth (240 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, tomatoes, bell pepper, onion and radishes. Chop the zucchinis.
  2. Toss the zucchinis with the olive oil. Season with salt, to taste, and set aside.
  3. Add the avocado oil to a saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the bacon to the saucepan and cook until crispy, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the zucchinis, tomatoes, bell pepper, onion and radishes to the saucepan and saute for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
  5. Lower the temperature and add the chicken broth to the saucepan. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes until the vegetables are soft to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Spicy Avocado Salad
ingredients:
• 2 large avocados (400 g), diced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium bell pepper (60 g)
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g)
  • 1 chili pepper (14 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • 0.25 cup of olive oil (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the avocados and tomato. Finely dice the chili pepper, seeds removed. Chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a bowl, toss the avocados, tomato, bell pepper, onion, optional chili pepper, and cilantro with the olive oil and lime juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the avocado salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Beef and Broccoli
ingredients:
• 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), broken into small florets
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 beef steaks (400 g), sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of sesame oil (5 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the broccoli into small florets, slice the beef steaks and mince or finely chop the garlic.
  2. In a pot of salted water, boil the broccoli until tender, about 2 to 3 minutes. Remove the broccoli from the pot with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the sliced steak and cook to desired doneness, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the broccoli, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, garlic and sesame oil to the skillet and continue to saute until the beef is cooked to your liking and the broccoli is heated through. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the beef and broccoli between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Quick Spaghetti Bolognese
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 lb of ground beef (225 g)
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium bell pepper (60 g), diced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely chopped
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), spiralized or shredded
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the onion, tomatoes and bell pepper. Mince or finely chop the garlic and spiralize or shred the zucchini.
  2. In a large skillet or pan, melt the coconut oil over high heat. Add the ground beef and onion to the skillet and saute until the ground beef is browned, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Reduce the heat to low and add the tomatoes and bell pepper to the skillet. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
  4. Add the garlic to the skillet. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the zucchini “spaghetti” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of bolognese sauce.

name: Keto Savory Zucchini Bread
ingredients:
• 1 zucchini (120 g), shredded or grated, excess moisture removed
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g), whisked
  • 0.5 cup of coconut oil (120 ml) (plus additional to grease the loaf pan)
  • 0.5 cup of almond flour (60 g), sifted
  • 0.25 cup of coconut flour (28 g), sifted
  • 1 teaspoon of baking powder (2 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract (5 ml)
  • Dash of salt
directions:
1. Shred or grate the zucchini, excess moisture removed. Whisk the eggs and sift the almond flour and coconut flour.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease a 9-inch by 5-inch (23 cm by 13 cm) loaf pan and set aside.
  3. Using a clean paper towel, squeeze any excess moisture from the shredded zucchini.
  4. In a large bowl, combine the zucchini, eggs, coconut oil, almond flour, coconut flour, baking powder, vanilla extract and a dash of salt. Pour the mixture into the prepared loaf pan.
  5. Place the loaf pan in the oven and bake for 50 minutes until a toothpick inserted into the middle of the zucchini bread comes out clean.
  6. Remove from the oven and let cool before slicing.

name: Keto Braised Bacon and Cabbage
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml)
  • 6 slices of bacon (168 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of napa/Chinese cabbage (400 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 1 cup of chicken broth (240 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon and tomato. Thinly slice the cabbage and onion and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a large pan, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bacon to the pan and saute until the bacon is crispy, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  3. Add the cabbage and onion to the pan and saute until the cabbage is slightly softened and the onion is translucent, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the tomato and chicken broth to the pan. Cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes until the cabbage is soft to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the braised cabbage between 2 plates and garnish with the fresh cilantro.

name: Keto Slow Cooker Pot Roast with Mashed Cauliflower
ingredients:
For the pot roast -

  • 2 lbs of beef roast (900 g), cut into 6 large pieces
  • 4 cups of beef broth (960 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the mashed cauliflower -

  • 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), broken into florets
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), melted
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the pot roast, cut the beef roast into 6 large pieces. For the mashed cauliflower, break the cauliflower into florets and melt the ghee.
  2. Add the beef roast, beef broth and tamari sauce or coconut aminos to the slow cooker and cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours until the roast shreds easily. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Meanwhile, make the cauliflower mash by steaming or boiling the cauliflower florets until tender and then blending it with the ghee and salt, to taste.
  4. Slice or shred the roast and serve with the cauliflower mash.

name: Keto Chicken Noodle Salad
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), grated or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 carrot (50 g), grated
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the dressing -

  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of sesame seeds (14 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of sesame oil (5 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of hot sauce (5 ml) (optional)
  • 1 teaspoon of vinegar (5 ml) (of choice)
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast. Grate the cucumber or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands. Thinly slice the onion, grate the carrot and chop the fresh cilantro. 
  2. In a skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until the chicken is cooked through with an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C), about 6 to 8 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Set aside.
  3. In a bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the cucumber, onion, carrot and chicken.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and garnish with fresh cilantro.

name: Keto Vegetable Saute with Fried Eggs
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), sliced
  • 0.5 head of napa/Chinese cabbage (400 g), sliced
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), sliced
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the onion, cabbage and zucchini. Chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a large pan, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the pan and saute until translucent, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  3. Add the cabbage to the pan and saute until soft to your liking, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  4. Add the zucchini to the pan and saute until soft. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Meanwhile, in a separate skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil. Add the eggs to the skillet and cook to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the saute between 2 plates and top with the fried eggs. Garnish each plate with fresh cilantro and serve.

name: Keto Tamari-Baked Salmon with Roasted Asparagus
ingredients:
For the tamari-baked salmon -

  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of garlic powder (20 g)
  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the roasted asparagus -

  • 10 spears of asparagus (160 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Defrost the salmon if frozen.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C).
  3. In a bowl, whisk to combine the avocado oil, tamari sauce or coconut aminos and garlic powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Dip each salmon filet in the marinade and place on a piece of parchment paper or aluminum foil. (For a more flavorful result, marinate in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.) Pour an equal amount of the marinade over each filet. Tightly wrap the parchment paper or aluminum foil to make parcels ensuring the marinade does not leak during cooking. Place the parcels on a rimmed baking tray.
  5. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily.
  6. Meanwhile, toss the asparagus with the olive oil. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Place the asparagus on a rimmed baking tray and bake with the salmon for 20 minutes or until tender to your liking.
  7. Serve the salmon with the roasted asparagus.

name: Keto One-Pot Cabbage Rolls
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), finely diced
  • 2 lbs of ground beef (900 g)
  • 1 carrot (50 g), finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of cumin powder (12 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of paprika (6 g)
  • 0.5 head of napa/Chinese cabbage (400 g), leaves separated
  • 2 Tablespoons of mustard (30 ml), for serving (optional)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Finely dice the onion and carrot and separate the leaves of the cabbage.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until translucent, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef to the skillet and saute until browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  4. Add the carrot to the skillet and saute until the ground beef is cooked to your liking.
  5. Add the cumin powder, garlic powder, and paprika to the skillet. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Meanwhile, bring a pot of salted water to a boil. Add the cabbage to the pot and boil for 2 to 4 minutes until the cabbage leaves are soft. Drain the cabbage leaves and pat dry with a paper towel.
  7. Place the desired amount of beef mixture in each cabbage leaf. Roll each cabbage leaf, folding in the sides to keep the beef mixture from spilling. Secure each cabbage roll with a toothpick.
  8. Serve the cabbage rolls with mustard, if desired.

name: Keto Garlic Butter Shrimp
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), to cook with
  • 1 lb of shrimp (450 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Peel and devein the shrimp, defrosted if frozen. Mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium heat. Add the shrimp and saute for 1 minute.
  3. Add the garlic to the skillet and saute until the shrimp are opaque and cooked through, about 2 to 4 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Slow Cooker Chicken & Bacon with Cucumber Salad
ingredients:
For the chicken and bacon -

  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g)
  • 8 slices of bacon (224 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • Salt, to taste

For the cucumber salad -

  • 1 cucumber (220 g), diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of vinegar (10 ml) (of choice)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon and cucumber.
  2. Add the chicken breasts, bacon and 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of olive to the slow cooker and cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours until the chicken shreds easily. Season with salt, to taste.
  3. Meanwhile, toss the cucumber with 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of olive oil and vinegar. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Serve the chicken and bacon with the cucumber salad.

name: Keto Apple Dijon Pork Chops
ingredients:
• 2 pork chops (320 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), to cook with
  • 2 Tablespoons of applesauce (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of mustard (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Generously season the pork chops with salt and pepper.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over high heat. Using tongs, place the pork chops on their sides with the fat in direct contact with the skillet. Render until the fat is brown and crispy.
  3. Reduce the heat to medium-high and place the pork chops flat in the skillet. Cook the pork chops for 3 minutes. Turn over and cook for an additional 3 to 5 minutes with an internal temperature of 145 F (63 C) for medium-rare. Remove the pork chops from the skillet and let rest for 3 minutes.
  4. Meanwhile, add the applesauce and mustard to the same skillet and cook for about 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, if desired.

name: Keto Lemon Salmon with Garlicky Green Beans
ingredients:
For the salmon -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the green beans -

  • 6 oz of green beans (168 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the salmon, defrost the filets if frozen. For the green beans, mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Season the salmon filets with salt and pepper.
  3. Add the avocado oil to a nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add the salmon, skin side down, to the skillet and cook for 5 minutes. Carefully turn over the salmon and cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Drizzle the lemon juice over the salmon. Remove from the heat and let rest for 1 to 2 minutes before serving.
  4. Meanwhile, if desired, for more tender green beans, parboil in a pot of salted water for 2 minutes. Remove the green beans from the water and drain.
  5. In a separate skillet, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the green beans to the skillet and saute until slightly brown, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  6. Add the garlic to the skillet. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Serve the salmon with the green beans.

name: Keto Tuna Linguine with Spicy Olive Sauce
ingredients:
• 4 Tablespoons of olive oil (60 ml)
  • 12 olives (36 g), pitted
  • 1 chili pepper (14 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh parsley (1 g), chopped
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), spiralized or use a peeler to make into long strands
  • 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Pit the olives. Finely dice the chili pepper, seeds are removed. Chop the fresh parsley and spiralize the zucchini or use a peeler to make into long strands. Drain and flake the tuna.
  2. To make the olive sauce, combine the olive oil, olives, optional chili pepper, and fresh parsley in a blender or food processor. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. In a bowl, toss the zucchini “noodles” and tuna with the olive sauce.
  4. Divide between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Pan-Fried Chicken Drumsticks with Bacon and Kale
ingredients:
• 4 chicken drumsticks (with skin on) (500 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 6 oz of kale (168 g), stems removed and chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon and chop the kale, stems are removed.
  2. Generously season the drumsticks with salt and set aside.
  3. Add the avocado oil to a large nonstick pan or cast iron skillet over medium-high heat. Add the bacon to the skillet and saute until crispy, about 2 to 4 minutes. Remove the bacon with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  4. Lower the heat to medium and place the drumsticks in the same skillet with the bacon fat. Cook on one side for 15 minutes. Using tongs, turn over each drumstick and cook for an additional 10 to 15 minutes until the internal temperature reaches 165 F (75 C). Remove from the skillet and set aside.
  5. In the same skillet, add the kale and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Return the bacon to the skillet. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Serve the drumsticks with the bacon and kale.

name: Keto Easy Beef Stroganoff over Cauliflower Rice
ingredients:
For the beef stroganoff -

  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml)
  • 0.75 lb of beef stew chunks (338 g)
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 5 white button mushrooms (50 g), sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of paprika (6 g)
  • 1 cup of beef broth (240 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of coconut cream (60 ml) (from the top of 1 refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the cauliflower “rice” -

  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the beef stroganoff, thinly slice the onion and garlic and slice the white button mushrooms. For the “rice”, process the cauliflower into rice-like pieces.
  2. In a large pot, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the beef to the pot and brown on all sides, about 3 to 4 minutes. Remove the beef from the pot and set aside.
  3. Add the onion and garlic to the pot and saute until the onion is soft, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the mushrooms, mustard, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, and paprika to the pot. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
  5. Reduce the heat to low. Return the browned beef to the pot and add the beef broth. Cover and cook for 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
  6. Add the coconut cream and cook, uncovered, for an additional 10 minutes until the beef is fork-tender. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Meanwhile, to make the cauliflower “rice”, saute the cauliflower pieces in the coconut oil on high heat for 5 to 10 minutes until softened. Season with salt, to taste.
  8. Divide the cauliflower “rice” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of beef stroganoff.

name: Keto Pork Loins with Mushroom Sauce and Kale Salad
ingredients:
For the pork loins and mushroom sauce -

  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), chopped
  • 0.25 cup of coconut cream (60 ml) (from the top of 1 refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 0.75 lb of pork loin (338 g) (or pork tenderloin), sliced into 1/2-inch (1.25 cm) thick slices
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 teaspoons of vinegar (10 ml) (of choice)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the salad -

  • 6 oz of kale (168 g), stems removed and chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 6 olives (18 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the pork loins and mushroom sauce, chop the mushrooms and cut the pork loin into 1/2-inch (1.25 cm) thick slices. For the salad, chop the olives, fresh parsley and kale, stems are removed.
  2. To make the mushroom sauce, combine the mushrooms and coconut cream in a blender or food processor. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Set aside.
  3. Generously season the sliced pork loin with salt.
  4. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the sliced pork loin to the skillet and cook for 2 to 3 minutes. Using tongs, turn over the pork loin and cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes or until cooked to your liking. Remove the pork loin from the skillet and set aside.
  5. Add the mushroom sauce to the same skillet. Reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Add the vinegar and season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Meanwhile, in a bowl, toss the kale with the olive oil, olives, and fresh parsley. If desired, season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Return the pork loin to the skillet with the mushroom sauce and heat for about 1 minute. Season with additional salt and pepper, to taste.
  8. Divide the pork loin with the mushroom sauce between 2 plates and serve with the kale salad.

name: Keto Lemon Garlic Baked Chicken
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), melted
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml) (or more, to taste)
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), chopped
  • 4 white button mushrooms (40 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Melt the ghee, mince or finely dice the garlic, dice the chicken breasts, slice the bell pepper and mushrooms and chop the zucchini.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. In a large bowl, combine the melted ghee, lemon juice, and garlic. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Add the chicken, bell pepper, zucchini, and mushrooms to the bowl. Stir to combine to ensure the chicken and vegetables are completely covered with the ghee mixture.
  5. Pour the chicken mixture onto a large rimmed baking sheet with space between the chicken and vegetables.
  6. Place in the oven and bake for 10 minutes. Stir the mixture and continue to bake for an additional 5 minutes until the chicken is fully cooked and the vegetables are soft. Check with a meat thermometer that the internal temperature of the chicken is 165 F (75 C).
  7. Season the vegetables and chicken with additional salt and pepper, to taste. If desired, add additional lemon juice, to taste.
  8. Divide the chicken and vegetables between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Egg and Mushroom Scramble with Chimichurri Sauce
ingredients:
For the egg and mushroom scramble -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), finely diced
  • 6 white button mushrooms (60 g), sliced
  • 6 medium eggs (294 g), whisked
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the chimichurri sauce -

  • 4 Tablespoons of olive oil (60 ml)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of lemon juice (8 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (4 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the egg and mushroom scramble, finely dice the onion, slice the mushrooms and whisk the eggs. For the chimichurri sauce, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the fresh cilantro and fresh parsley.
  2. Combine the chimichurri sauce ingredients in a blender or food processor and set aside until ready to use.
  3. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until the onion is translucent, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the mushrooms to the skillet and saute until softened, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  5. Add the whisked eggs to the skillet and scramble until cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the scramble between 2 plates and drizzle with the chimichurri sauce.

name: Keto Broiled Sesame Salmon with Zucchini Salsa
ingredients:
For the broiled salmon -

  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of garlic powder (20 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of ginger powder (4 g)
  • 4 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (680 g), defrosted if frozen
  • 1 Tablespoon of sesame seeds (14 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the zucchini salsa -

  • 1 zucchini (120 g), diced
  • 6 cherry tomatoes (102 g), quartered
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Defrost the salmon filets if frozen. For the salsa, dice the zucchini and cut the cherry tomatoes into quarters.
  2. Preheat the broiler and place the rack about 6-inches (15 cm) under the broiler.
  3. In a bowl, whisk to combine the avocado oil, lemon juice, garlic powder, and ginger powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Place the salmon filets on a rimmed baking tray and cover with half of the avocado oil mixture. Place in the oven and broil for 3 to 5 minutes until browned. Carefully turn over the salmon filets and cover with the remaining avocado oil mixture. Continue to broil for an additional 3 to 5 minutes until the salmon is cooked through.
  5. Meanwhile, in a bowl, toss to combine the zucchini salsa ingredients.
  6. Place each salmon filet on a plate and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Serve the salmon with the zucchini salsa.

name: Keto Zucchini Pasta with Creamy Bacon Mushroom Sauce
ingredients:
• 8 slices of bacon (224 g), diced
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), diced
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of 1 refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 0.25 cup of chicken broth (60 ml)
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), spiralized or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon and mushrooms. Spiralize the zucchinis or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands.
  2. In a nonstick skillet or pan, saute the bacon until crispy, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Add the mushrooms to the skillet and saute until softened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Reduce the heat to a simmer and add the coconut cream and chicken broth to the skillet. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes until the sauce reduces, stirring frequently. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the zucchini “pasta” between 2 plates and top with the bacon mushroom sauce.

name: Keto Scrambled Eggs with Smoked Salmon
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 6 medium eggs, whisked
  • 4 oz of smoked salmon (112 g), diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Whisk the eggs and dice the salmon.
  2. In a skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium heat. Add the whisked eggs to the skillet and scramble.
  3. While the eggs are slightly wet, add the smoked salmon to the skillet and continue to scramble until the eggs are cooked to your liking and the smoked salmon is heated through, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Arugula Avocado Walnut Salad
ingredients:
• 1 large bag of arugula leaves (125 g)
  • 0.25 cup of walnuts (29 g), chopped
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the walnuts and slice the avocado.
  2. In a large bowl, toss the arugula leaves and walnuts with the olive oil and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of avocado slices.

name: Keto Jalapeno Chicken Casserole
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 chicken breasts (800 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 medium bell peppers (240 g), chopped
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), chopped
  • 2 jalapeno peppers (28 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 2 cups of coconut milk (480 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of hot sauce (15 ml) (or to taste) (optional)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.25 cup of fresh parsley (8 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breasts, break the broccoli into small florets and chop the bell peppers, onion and fresh parsley. Mince or finely dice the garlic and finely dice the jalapeno peppers, seeds are removed.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).
  3. In a large pan, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken, broccoli, bell peppers, onion, and optional jalapeno peppers to the pan. Saute until the chicken is cooked through and the vegetables are soft, about 10 to 12 minutes.
  4. Remove the pan from the heat and add the coconut milk, optional hot sauce, garlic, and fresh parsley. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Carefully pour the mixture into a baking dish.
  5. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 20 minutes.
  6. Divide the casserole among 4 plates and serve.

name: Keto Sri Lankan Prawn Curry
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), chopped
  • 1 chili pepper (14 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of curry powder (7 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of ginger powder (2 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of cumin powder (2 g)
  • 1 cup of coconut milk (240 ml)
  • 0.5 lb of shrimp (225 g), peeled and deveined, defrosted if frozen
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh cilantro (1 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the onion and fresh cilantro. Finely dice the chili pepper, seeds are removed. Mince or finely dice the garlic and peel and devein the shrimp, defrosted if frozen.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion, optional chili pepper, and garlic to the skillet and saute until the onion is translucent, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the curry powder, ginger powder, and cumin powder to the skillet and saute for about 30 seconds.
  4. Add the coconut milk to the skillet and reduce the heat to a simmer.
  5. Add the shrimp to the skillet and continue to simmer until the shrimp are cooked through, about 3 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the shrimp curry between 2 plates and garnish with fresh cilantro.

name: Keto Bacon and Egg Pesto Spaghetti
ingredients:
For the “spaghetti” -

  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 2 medium eggs
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), spiralized or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the pesto -

  • 0.75 cup of fresh basil leaves (24 g), torn
  • 2 Tablespoons of pine nuts (16 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g)
  • 4 Tablespoons of olive oil (60 ml)
directions:
1. For the “spaghetti”, dice the bacon and spiralize the zucchinis or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands. For the pesto, tear the fresh basil leaves.
  2. To make the pesto, combine the fresh basil, pine nuts, lemon juice, and garlic in a blender or food processor. While the blender or food processor is running, slowly add the olive oil and continue to blend until the desired consistency is achieved. Set aside.
  3. In a skillet over medium-high heat, saute the bacon until crispy, about 3 to 4 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  4. In the same skillet, fry the eggs in the bacon fat until cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Set aside.
  5. In a large bowl, toss with zucchini “spaghetti” and bacon with the pesto.
  6. Divide the “spaghetti” between 2 plates and top each plate with a fried egg.

name: Keto Lemon Tuna Salad with Avocado
ingredients:
• 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of lemon juice (10 ml) (plus 1 teaspoon [5 ml] of lemon zest)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna, chop the fresh parsley and romaine lettuce and slice the avocado.
  2. In a bowl, combine the tuna, mayo, lemon juice, lemon zest and fresh parsley. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the romaine lettuce between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of tuna salad and avocado slices.

name: Keto Simple Beef Meatballs
ingredients:
• 1.5 lbs of ground beef (675 g)
  • 2 medium eggs, whisked
  • 2 Tablespoons of garlic powder (20 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of onion powder (14 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Whisk the eggs.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. In a bowl, combine all of the ingredients until incorporated. Form the beef mixture into golf ball-size meatballs and place on a rimmed baking tray.
  4. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 20 minutes until an instant-read thermometer reaches 170 F (75 C).

name: Keto Ginger Cabbage and Beef Saute
ingredients:
• 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh ginger (10 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 green onions (10 g), chopped
  • 1 beef steak (200 g), sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the cabbage, mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger, chop the green onions and slice the beef steak.
  2. In a large pot of salted water, boil the cabbage until tender, about 5 minutes. Drain well and set aside.
  3. Meanwhile, add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the garlic, fresh ginger, and green onions to the skillet and saute until fragrant, about 1 minute.
  4. Add the beef steak to the skillet and saute until cooked to your liking, about 2 to 4 minutes for medium-rare.
  5. Add the cabbage and tamari sauce or coconut aminos to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the saute between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Beef Teriyaki with Sesame and Kale
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of applesauce (15 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (4 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 beef steaks (400 g), sliced (pick a well marbled steak)
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml)
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 2 oz of curly kale (56 g), stems removed and chopped
  • 1 teaspoon of sesame oil (5 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger, slice the beef steaks and mushrooms and chop the kale, stems are removed.
  2. In a bowl, whisk to combine the tamari sauce or coconut aminos, applesauce, garlic, and fresh ginger. Place the sliced beef steaks in the marinade and set aside.
  3. Add the avocado oil to a large frying pan or wok over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms to the pan and stir-fry until golden brown, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the beef steaks and the marinade to the pan and stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
  5. Add the kale to the pan and continue to stir-fry until the beef steaks are cooked to your liking and the kale is wilted.
  6. Add the sesame oil to the pan and stir well to combine. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Tuna Patties with Creamy Dill Sauce
ingredients:
For the tuna patties -

  • 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 2 medium eggs
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut flour (14 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of shredded coconut (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh dill (3 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the dill sauce -

  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut milk (30 ml)
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh dill (1 g), finely chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the tuna patties, drain and flake the canned tuna and chop the fresh dill. For the dill sauce, mince or finely dice the garlic and finely chop the fresh dill.
  2. In a small bowl, whisk to combine the dill sauce ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.
  3. In a large bowl, combine the tuna, eggs, coconut flour, shredded coconut and 1 Tablespoon (3 g) of fresh dill. Season with salt and pepper. Shape the mixture into 4 patties.
  4. In a large nonstick skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium heat. Place the patties in the skillet and cook until golden brown, about 3 to 4 minutes per side.
  5. Serve the tuna patties with the dill sauce.

name: Keto French Hamburgers
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 1.5 lbs of ground beef (675 g)
  • 1 medium egg, whisked
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh thyme (3 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the onion, whisk the eggs and chop the fresh thyme.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml) over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until translucent, about 4 to 5 minutes. Set aside to cool.
  3. In a medium bowl, combine the ground beef, egg, fresh thyme, and cooled onion with the pan drippings. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Form the meat mixture into 8 hamburger patties.
  4. In the same skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat.
  5. In batches, add the hamburgers to the skillet. Sear the burgers for 3 to 4 minutes on one side. Using a spatula, flip the burgers and sear for an additional 3 to 5 minutes or to desired doneness. Check with a meat thermometer that the internal temperature reaches 160 F (71 C) for medium.
  6. Serve the hamburgers with a side dish of choice.

name: Keto Viet Beef Pho with Zucchini Noodles and Poached Eggs
ingredients:
• 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • 3 cups of chicken broth (720 ml)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of cinnamon powder (2 g)
  • 0.75 lb of beef roast (338 g), sliced very thin
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), spiralized or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands
  • 10 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (20 g), chopped
  • 1 lemon (58 g), cut into 4 wedges (for serving)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Mince or finely dice the fresh ginger, thinly slice the beef roast and chop the fresh basil leaves. Spiralize or use a peeler to make the zucchinis into long noodle-like strands.
  2. Bring a saucepan of water to a boil and lower to a simmer. One at a time, add each egg to the simmering water. Swirl a spoon to push the egg whites closer to the yolks. Turn off the heat and cover the pan for 4 minutes. After 4 minutes, use a slotted spoon to remove the poached eggs from the pot and set aside.
  3. In a large pot over high heat, add the chicken broth and bring to a boil.
  4. Add the fresh ginger and cinnamon powder to the pot and continue to boil for about 1 minute.
  5. Slowly add the sliced beef to the pot and continue to boil for about 1 minute, stirring constantly to keep the beef slices separated. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the pho between 2 large bowls. Add the zucchini “noodles” and basil leaves into each bowl. Top each bowl with 2 poached eggs and serve with the lemon wedges.

name: Keto Italian Chicken Mini Meatloaves
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with (plus additional for greasing muffin pan)
  • 1 lb of ground chicken (450 g)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g), chopped
  • 8 medium eggs, whisked
  • 4 teaspoons of Italian seasoning (4 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of salt (15 g) (or to taste)
  • 1 teaspoon of pepper (1 g) (or to taste)
  • 0.5 cup of coconut milk (120 ml)
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic, chop the spinach and whisk the eggs.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Grease a 12-cup muffin pan and set aside.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the ground chicken, onion and garlic to the skillet and saute until the chicken is cooked through, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the spinach leaves and continue to saute until completely wilted, about 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool slightly.
  5. In a bowl, combine the chicken mixture, whisked eggs, Italian seasoning, coconut milk, salt and pepper. Place equal amounts of the mixture into the greased muffin pan.
  6. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 10 minutes until the eggs are cooked through and the meatloaves are firm.

name: Keto Ginger Asparagus Mash
ingredients:
• 10 spears of asparagus (160 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), melted
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (4 g), finely chopped
  • 1 teaspoon of lemon juice (5 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the asparagus, thinly slice the onion and melt the ghee. Mince or finely dice the fresh ginger and finely chop the fresh parsley.
  2. In a pot of boiling salted water, blanch the asparagus for 2 minutes. Immediately drain and set aside to cool slightly.
  3. In a medium skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until translucent, about 2 minutes.
