  4. In a food processor or blender, combine the blanched asparagus, sauteed onion, ghee, fresh ginger, fresh parsley, and lemon juice until smooth. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Shrimp Lettuce Tacos with Easy Guacamole
ingredients:
For the shrimp tacos -

  • 1 lb of shrimp (450 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined 
  • 2 Tablespoons of lime juice (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 1 head of iceberg lettuce (450 g), leaves separated
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the guacamole -

  • 1 large avocado (200 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), finely chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the shrimp tacos, peel and devein the shrimp, defrost if frozen and separate the leaves of the iceberg lettuce. For the guacamole, chop the avocado and fresh cilantro. Finely chop the onion.
  2. In a large bowl, combine the shrimp, lime juice and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Marinate for at least 30 minutes in the refrigerator prior to cooking.
  3. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine the guacamole ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.
  4. When ready to cook, add the shrimp and marinade to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook, turning the shrimp frequently, until the shrimp are firm and opaque, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  5. Serve the shrimp and guacamole in the lettuce leaves.

name: Keto Avocado Baked Eggs
ingredients:
• 2 large avocados (400 g)
  • 4 medium eggs (176 g)
  • 1.5 Tablespoons of olive oil (23 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  2. Cut each avocado in half and remove each pit.
  3. Crack each egg into a bowl. Carefully scoop each egg yolk and place in the center of each avocado half.
  4. Pour about 1 teaspoon (5 ml) of olive oil over each yolk.
  5. Place the avocado halves in a baking sheet. Bake in the oven for 12 minutes.
  6. Season each avocado half with salt and pepper, to taste. Season with any additional herb or spice, if desired.
  7. Place 2 avocado halves on each plate and serve.

name: Keto Stir-Fried Lemon Garlic Ground Chicken with Veg
ingredients:
For the stir-fried chicken -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (8 ml)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of hot sauce (3 ml) (optional)
  • 1 lb of ground chicken (450 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the veg -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), sliced
  • 1 carrot (50 g), sliced
  • 3 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (3 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the stir-fried chicken, mince or finely dice the garlic. For the veg, Mince or finely dice the garlic, slice the onion and carrot, and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a small bowl, combine 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil, lemon juice, garlic, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, optional hot sauce, salt and pepper. Place the ground chicken and marinade in a sealed container or storage bag and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours. (For more flavorful results, marinate in the refrigerator overnight.)
  3. When ready to cook, add the ground chicken and the marinade to a nonstick pan over medium-high heat. Saute until the chicken is fully cooked, about 7 to 8 minutes. Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.
  4. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil and garlic to the same pan over medium-high heat. Stir-fry until the garlic becomes fragrant, about 30 seconds.
  5. Add the onion and carrot to the pan and stir-fry until the vegetables are browned and soft, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  6. Add the fresh cilantro, lemon juice and tamari sauce or coconut aminos and stir-fry until the liquids begin to evaporate and the vegetables are cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Avocado Salad with Tomato and Basil
ingredients:
• 2 large avocados (400 g), sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (4 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the avocados and tomato. Chop the fresh basil leaves.
  2. Place an equal amount of sliced avocado and sliced tomato on 2 plates. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Top with an equal amount of fresh basil and drizzle with olive oil.

name: Keto Bacon-Wrapped Asparagus
ingredients:
• 8 slices of bacon (224 g), sliced in half lengthwise
  • 16 spears of asparagus (256 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bacon in half lengthwise.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).
  3. Wrap each halved slice of bacon tightly around each asparagus spear. Place the asparagus on a rimmed baking tray. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Place the tray in the oven and bake for 15 minutes. Using tongs, turn over each asparagus and continue to bake for an additional 10 to 15 minutes until the bacon starts to become crisp.
  5. If desired, place the asparagus under the broiler for 2 to 3 minutes until the bacon is crisp to your liking.

name: Keto Fall-Off-The Bone Baked Ribs with Apple Ginger Tamari Glaze
ingredients:
• 1 lb of baby back ribs (15.5 oz / 440 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of applesauce (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Mince or finely dice the fresh ginger and garlic.
  2. Preheat the oven to 275°F (135°C). If your oven doesn't go down this low, then turn it to the lowest temperature setting.
  3. Generously season the ribs with salt and pepper and wrap tightly with aluminum foil. Place the package on a rimmed baking tray. Place in the oven and bake at low temperature for 3 hours.
  4. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, whisk to combine the applesauce, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, olive oil, garlic, and fresh ginger to make a marinade.
  5. After 3 hours, remove the ribs from the oven and increase the heat to 450°F (230°C) or to the highest temperature setting.
  6. Carefully open up the foil so that the ribs are sitting on top of the foil. Using a pastry brush, cover the ribs with the marinade. Return the ribs to the oven and bake for an additional 5 to 10 minutes until the ribs become sticky with the marinade.

name: Keto Crunchy Chia and Apple Avocados
ingredients:
• 1 small green apple (150 g), diced
  • 2 stalks of celery (40 g), diced
  • 3 Tablespoons of mayo (45 ml)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), cut in half and pit removed
  • 1 Tablespoon of chia seeds (12 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the apple and celery stalks. Pit the avocado and cut it in half.
  2. In a small bowl, combine the apple and celery with the mayo. If desired, season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Place each avocado half on a plate and fill with equal amounts of the apple mixture. Sprinkle each avocado with equal amounts of chia seeds and serve.

name: Keto Broccoli Bacon Chicken Casserole
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), for greasing pan
  • 10 slices of bacon (280 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook chicken in
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 2 heads of broccoli (900 g), broken into small florets
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 2 cups of coconut milk (480 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, chicken breasts, mushrooms and onion. Break the broccoli into small florets.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease a large baking dish with the ghee and set aside. 
  3. In a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 5 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  4. In the same skillet, melt the coconut oil with the bacon grease over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 10 minutes. Season with salt, to taste. Remove from the heat and let cool slightly. 
  5. In a large bowl, combine the bacon, chicken with the cooking oil, broccoli, mushrooms, onion and coconut milk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the chicken mixture into the greased baking dish.
  6. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 1 hour until bubbly and the broccoli is tender.
  7. Let cool slightly before serving.

name: Keto Hamburger Steak with Broccoli Mash
ingredients:
For the hamburger steak -

  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 0.5 medium egg (22 g), whisked
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of onion powder (4 g)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of garlic powder (5 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook burgers with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the broccoli mash -

  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), broken into small florets
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the hamburger steak, whisk the egg and dice the onion. For the mash, break the broccoli into small florets and mince the garlic.
  2. In a bowl, combine the ground beef, whisked egg, garlic powder and onion powder. Season with salt and pepper. Form the mixture into 6 thin patties.
  3. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of ghee over medium-high heat. In batches, add the patties to the skillet and cook until desired doneness, about 2 to 3 minutes per side for medium.
  4. In the same skillet, add the onion and saute until golden brown, about 3 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Meanwhile, boil the broccoli in a pot of salted water until tender, about 2 to 3 minutes. Remove the broccoli from the pot with a slotted spoon and drain.
  6. Place the broccoli, 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of ghee and garlic cloves in a food processor or high-speed blender and blend to desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Serve the burgers topped with the sauteed onions and the broccoli mash.

name: Keto Shrimp Caesar Salad
ingredients:
For the shrimp -

  • 1 lb of shrimp (450 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the Caesar dressing -

  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of mustard (5 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the salad -

  • 2 heads of romaine lettuce (400 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), chopped
directions:
1. Peel and devein the shrimp, defrost if frozen. Chop the romaine lettuce and cucumber.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. Toss the shrimp with the olive oil and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Place the shrimp on a rimmed baking tray.
  4. Place the baking tray in the oven and roast for 10 minutes until the shrimp are cooked through and opaque. Remove from the oven and let cool slightly.
  5. Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine the dressing. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves, cucumber and roasted shrimp.
  6. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Cauliflower Fried "Rice" with Bacon
ingredients:
• 3 Tablespoons of coconut oil (45 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • 6 green onions (30 g), finely chopped
  • 8 slices of bacon (224 g), chopped
  • 4 medium eggs, whisked
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of fresh cilantro (4 g), finely chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Process the cauliflower into rice-like pieces, finely chop the green onions and fresh cilantro, chop the bacon and whisk the eggs.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of coconut oil over medium heat. Add the cauliflower and green onion to the skillet and saute until the cauliflower starts to soften, about 10 to 12 minutes.
  3. Meanwhile, in a separate skillet over medium-high heat, add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet and discard the excess bacon fat. Set aside the bacon. 
  4. In the same skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium heat. Add the whisked eggs to the skillet and let sit for about 1 minute. Gently stir the eggs until fully cooked, careful not to let them clump together. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Add the reserved bacon and cooked eggs to the cauliflower “rice” and continue to saute for about 5 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
  6. Add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos and fresh cilantro to the skillet and continue to saute for about 2 additional minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Vegetable Saute topped with Fried Egg
ingredients:
• 3 Tablespoons of coconut oil (45 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), sliced
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), chopped into small pieces
  • 1 carrot (50 g), grated
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), grated
  • 3 stalks of celery (60 g), chopped
  • 4 medium eggs
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the onion, chop the cauliflower into small pieces, grate the carrot and cucumber and chop the celery stalks and fresh cilantro.
  2. In a large pan, melt 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the pan and saute until translucent, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  3. Add the cauliflower and carrot to the pan and saute until soft to your liking, about 5 to 7 minutes. (Place a lid on the pan while cooking for softer vegetables.)
  4. Add the cucumber and celery to the skillet and continue to saute until the celery is soft to your liking, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Add additional seasonings of choice, if desired.
  5. Meanwhile, in a separate skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the eggs to the skillet and cook to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the saute between 2 plates and top with the fried eggs. Garnish each plate with fresh cilantro and serve.

name: Keto Steak with Mushroom Sauce
ingredients:
For the mushroom sauce -

  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced small
  • 3 white button mushrooms (30 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of mustard (5 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of garlic powder (3 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of salt (2 g) (or to taste)

For the steak -

  • 2 beef steaks (400 g)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of salt (8 g) (or to taste)
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
directions:
1. For the mushroom sauce, dice the onion into small pieces.
  2. Season the steaks with salt and set aside.
  3. To make the mushroom sauce, use a blender or food processor to blend the onion, mushrooms, olive oil, mustard, garlic powder and salt until smooth. 
  4. In a small pan over medium heat, add the mushroom sauce and cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
  5. Meanwhile, add the avocado oil to a large skillet over high heat. Add the steaks to the skillet and sear for 3 minutes. Using tongs, turn over the steaks and sear for an additional 3 to 4 minutes for medium-rare with an internal temperature of 140 F (60 C). Set aside the steaks to rest for 5 minutes.
  6. Serve the steaks with the mushroom sauce.

name: Keto Bacon Spinach Quiche
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 6 slices of bacon (168 g), diced
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 10 medium eggs, whisked
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, onion and tomato, chop the bell pepper and spinach and whisk the eggs.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C).
  3. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 3 to 4 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  4. In the same skillet, add the bell pepper and onion to the reserved bacon fat and saute for about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Remove the skillet from the heat and let it cool.
  6. In a medium bowl, combine the eggs, coconut cream, tomato and the cooled spinach mixture. Pour the egg mixture into a greased 9-inch (23 cm) square baking dish.
  7. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 20 to 30 minutes until the eggs are set.

name: Keto Easy Chicken Curry
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), diced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), diced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of curry powder (7 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of cumin powder (2 g)
  • 0.25 cup of fresh cilantro (4 g), chopped
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breasts, bell pepper and onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until browned, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the bell pepper, onion and garlic to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the curry powder, cumin powder and fresh cilantro to the skillet and saute until the chicken is cooked through. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Canned Tuna Salad Nicoise
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 2 medium eggs (98 g)
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 1 can of tuna (170 g), drained and flaked
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), sliced
  • 8 olives (24 g), chopped
  • 4 radishes (8 g), thinly sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the dressing -

  • 0.25 cup of olive oil (60 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna, thinly slice the cucumber and radishes, slice the tomato and chop the olives.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove from heat and put the lid on the pot. Let sit for 12 minutes and then drain the eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and slice the eggs in half.
  3. Meanwhile, in a bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the spinach leaves.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with the tuna, cucumber, tomato, olives, hard-boiled eggs and radishes.

name: Keto Lemon Blueberry Chicken Salad
ingredients:
For the salad - 

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 10 blueberries (5 g) (or other berry, of choice)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast, chop the romaine lettuce and thinly slice the cucumber and onion.
  2. In a nonstick skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 7 to 8 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. In a bowl, whisk to combine the olive oil and lemon juice. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves. 
  4. Add the cooked chicken, cucumber, onion and blueberries to the bowl.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Steak and Peppers
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 beef steaks (400 g), sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of cumin powder (6 g)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of garlic powder (5 g)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of onion powder (4 g)
  • 0.25 teaspoon of chili powder (1 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh cilantro (1 g), finely chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell pepper and beef steaks, thinly slice the onion and finely chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until golden brown, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  3. Add the steak to the skillet and saute until slightly browned, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  4. Add the cumin powder, garlic powder, onion powder and chili powder to the skillet and continue to saute until the steak is done to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Garnish the steak and peppers with fresh cilantro and serve.

name: Keto Smoked Salmon and Cucumber on Toast
ingredients:
• 1/3 cup of almond flour (40 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of baking powder (1 g)
  • Dash of salt 
  • 1 medium egg (49g), whisked
  • 2.5 Tablespoons of ghee (38 ml), melted (plus additional for the mug)
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 oz of smoked salmon (112 g)
directions:
1. Whisk the egg, melt the ghee and thinly slice the cucumber.
  2. In a small bowl, whisk to combine the almond flour, baking powder, egg, ghee and salt until completely combined. Pour the mixture into a greased microwave-safe mug. 
  3. Place the mug in a microwave and cook for 90 seconds on high. Remove from the microwave and let cool slightly.
  4. Once the mug is cool enough to touch, gently remove the bread and slice into 4 pieces. Toast the bread using a toaster, toaster oven or under a broiler. 
  5. Place two slices of “toast” on each plate. Top with an equal amount of cucumber and salmon before serving.

name: Keto Turkey Bacon Stew
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 lbs of turkey breasts (900 g), diced
  • 8 slices of bacon (224 g), diced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced
  • 4 cups of chicken broth (960 ml)
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), chopped
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the turkey breasts and bacon, slice the onion and chop the zucchinis.
  2. In a pot or large saucepan, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the turkey, bacon and onion to the pot and saute until the turkey is cooked through, about 10 to 12 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken broth to the pot and bring to a boil.
  4. Reduce the heat to a simmer and add the zucchini. Continue to simmer until the zucchini is soft, about 5 minutes.
  5. Add the spinach to the pot and simmer for about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Chicken and Pepper Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 medium bell peppers (240 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 lb of ground chicken (450 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell peppers, thinly slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bell peppers and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are golden brown, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  3. Add the ground chicken and garlic to the skillet and saute until the chicken is cooked through, about 5 to 8 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the saute between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Asian Meatballs with Dipping Sauce and Sauteed Spinach
ingredients:
For the meatballs -

  • 1 lb of ground beef (450 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (15 ml)
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 green onion (5 g), finely chopped
  • 1 teaspoon of sesame oil (5 ml)

For the dipping sauce -

  • 3 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (45 ml)
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 green onion (5 g), finely chopped
  • 1 teaspoon of vinegar (5 ml) (of choice)
  • 1 teaspoon of sesame oil (5 ml)

For the sauteed spinach -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (4 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the meatballs, mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger and finely chop the green onion. For the dipping sauce, mince or finely dice the garlic and finely chop the green onion. For the sauteed spinach, mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger and chop the fresh basil leaves.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).
  3. In a mixing bowl, combine the ground beef, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, garlic, fresh ginger, green onion, and sesame oil. Form the mixture into 10 to 12 meatballs and place on a rimmed baking sheet.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 18 to 22 minutes until cooked through with an internal temperature of 165°F (75°C). Let rest for 5 minutes before serving.
  5. Meanwhile, to make the dipping sauce, whisk to combine the tamari sauce or coconut aminos, garlic, green onion, vinegar, and sesame oil in a small bowl. Set aside until ready to serve.
  6. To make the sauteed spinach, add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the spinach and saute for about 1 minute. Add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos, garlic, fresh ginger, and fresh basil leaves to the skillet and saute until the spinach is completely wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Serve the meatballs with the dipping sauce and sauteed spinach.

name: Keto Bacon Egg Muffins
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to grease muffin pan
  • 8 slices of bacon (224 g), diced
  • 6 medium eggs (294 g), whisked
  • 1 cup of spinach (30 g), chopped
  • 2 green onions (10 g), finely chopped
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a can of coconut milk) 
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, whisk the eggs, chop the spinach and finely chop the green onions.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease an 8-cup muffin pan with coconut oil and set aside.
  3. In a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 5 to 6 minutes. Remove the bacon with a slotted spoon and set aside to cool slightly.
  4. In a large bowl, combine the eggs, spinach, green onions, coconut cream and cooked bacon. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Divide the egg mixture between the 8 muffin cups. Be sure to fill each cup 2/3 full as the muffins will rise when baking.
  5. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until the eggs are cooked through.

name: Keto Pork and Cashew Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 2 medium eggs (98 g), whisked
  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium bell pepper (60 g), sliced
  • 2 green onions (10 g), finely chopped
  • 1.5 oz of cashew (42 g) (or nut of choice)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Whisk the eggs, thinly slice the pork tenderloin, chop the zucchini, slice the bell pepper, finely chop the green onions and mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the eggs and scramble until fully cooked, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove from the skillet and set aside.
  3. In the same skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil. Add the pork and saute until browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the zucchini, bell pepper, green onion and cashews to the skillet. Continue to saute until the vegetables start to soften, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  5. Return the scrambled eggs to the skillet and add the fresh ginger, garlic and tamari sauce or coconut aminos. Continue to saute until the pork is cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. 
  6. Divide the stir-fry between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Creamy Basil and Tomato Chicken Pasta
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (4 g), chopped
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.25 cup of coconut cream (60 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), spiralized or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until fully cooked, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  2. Add the tomatoes to the skillet and saute until soft, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the fresh basil, garlic and coconut cream to the skillet and cook until the sauce starts to thicken, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the zucchini “noodles” between 2 plates. Top with the creamy basil chicken and serve.

name: Keto Bacon Egg and Avocado Salad
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 2 medium eggs (98 g)
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), diced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of balsamic vinegar (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, avocado and tomato and chop the romaine lettuce.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove from the heat and put a lid on the pot. Let sit for 12 minutes and then drain the eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and chop the eggs. Set aside.
  3. In a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 3 to 4 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside to cool slightly.
  4. In a bowl, whisk to combine the olive oil and balsamic vinegar. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves. Add the chopped eggs, cooked bacon, avocado and tomato to the bowl.
  6. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Zucchini Sliders with Tomato Salad
ingredients:
For the sliders -

  • 0.5 Tablespoon of avocado oil (8 ml), for greasing a baking tray
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), sliced into 1/2-inch (1 cm) thick slices (around 14-16 slices)
  • 0.5 lb of ground beef (225 g)
  • 0.5 large avocado (100 g), sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml), for serving (optional)
  • 2 teaspoons of mustard (10 ml), for serving (optional)
  • Salt, to taste

For the tomato salad -

  • 1 cucumber (220 g), sliced
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of vinegar (10 ml) (of choice)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the sliders, slice the zucchini [into 1/2-inch (1 cm) thick slices (around 14-16 slices)] and avocado. For the tomato salad, slice the cucumber, chop the tomatoes and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a bowl, combine the cucumber, tomatoes and onion with the olive oil and vinegar. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
  3. Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 400F (200C). Grease a rimmed baking tray with avocado oil and sprinkle with salt.
  4. Place the zucchini slices on the baking tray. Form the ground beef into 7 or 8 small patties and place on the baking tray.
  5. Place the baking tray into the oven and bake for 15 minutes or until the slider patties are done to your liking. Let cool slightly.
  6. Assemble the sliders by using the zucchini as “buns” and placing a slice of avocado on each slider and topping each with mayo and mustard, if desired. Serve the sliders with the tomato salad.

name: Keto Canned Tuna and Spinach Casserole
ingredients:
• 4 cans of tuna (680 g), drained and flaked
  • 1 cup of coconut cream (240 ml) (from the top of 2 refrigerated cans of coconut milk)
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), diced
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml)
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna, dice the bell pepper, chop the spinach and fresh parsley, thinly slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Combine all of the ingredients in a large bowl. Pour the tuna mixture into a greased 8-inch (20 cm) square baking dish.
  3. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 35 minutes until cooked through and bubbly.
  4. Remove the casserole from the oven and let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

name: Keto Italian Sausage Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), chopped
  • 0.5 lb of sausages of your choice (225 g), sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 10 olives (30 g), chopped
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of Italian seasoning (3 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the onion, tomato and olives, slice the sausages (of your choice) and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Add the olive oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until translucent, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the sausages and saute until cooked through, about 5 to 8 minutes. (If using precooked sausages, saute until heated through, about 2 to 3 minutes.)
  4. Add the tomato, olives, and garlic to the skillet and saute until the tomato is soft, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  5. Add the Italian seasoning to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Baked Chicken Thigh Casserole
ingredients:
• 3 Tablespoons of avocado oil (45 ml), divided, to cook with (plus additional to grease a baking dish or rimmed baking tray)
  • 8 chicken thighs (with skin on) (1200 g)
  • 1 head of broccoli (450 g), broken into small florets
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 30 white button mushrooms (300 g), halved
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh rosemary (6 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the broccoli into small florets, thinly slice the onion, cut the mushrooms in halves, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the fresh rosemary.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Lightly grease a large baking dish or a rimmed baking tray with avocado oil and set aside.
  3. Generously season the chicken thighs with salt and pepper.
  4. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet, skin side down, and cook until the skin is golden and crispy, about 7 to 8 minutes. Using tongs, turn over the chicken and continue to cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes.
  5. Place the chicken thighs (skin side up), broccoli, onion, mushrooms, garlic and fresh rosemary in the baking dish. Drizzle the remaining 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of avocado oil over the chicken and vegetables.
  6. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until the chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C). (For softer vegetables, remove the chicken from the baking dish and decrease the oven temperature to 350 F [175 C]. Continue to bake the vegetables for an additional 10 to 15 minutes until soft to your liking.) Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Serve the chicken thighs with the vegetables.

name: Keto 10-Minute Chicken Noodle Soup
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook in
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 carrot (50 g), grated
  • 4 cups of chicken broth (960 ml)
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), grated or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast, thinly slice the onion, grate the carrot, grate the cucumber or use a peeler to make it into long noodle-like strands and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a saucepan, melt the coconut oil over high heat. Add the chicken to the saucepan and saute until browned, about 4 to 6 minutes.
  3. Add the onion and carrot to the saucepan and saute until the vegetables are soft and slightly browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the chicken broth to the saucepan and bring to a boil. Add the cucumber “noodles” to the saucepan and continue to boil for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Remove the saucepan from the heat and season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and garnish with fresh cilantro.

name: Keto Easy Steak Fajitas
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 2 beef steaks (400 g)
  • 2 medium bell peppers (240 g), sliced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of cumin powder (2 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell peppers and onion.
  2. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over high heat. Add the steaks and sear for 3 minutes. Using tongs, turn over the steaks and sear for an additional 3 to 4 minutes for medium-rare with an internal temperature of 140 F (60 C). Set aside the steaks to rest for 5 minutes before slicing.
  3. In a separate skillet over high heat, add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil. Add the bell peppers, onion, garlic powder, and cumin powder to the skillet and saute until soft and just browned, about 6 to 8 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the peppers and onion between 2 plates and top with the sliced steak.

name: Keto Colorful Steak and Pepper Salad
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 beef steak (200 g)
  • 2 medium bell peppers (240 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 carrot (50 g), grated or thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of vinegar (5 ml) (of choice)
directions:
1. Slice the bell peppers, thinly slice the onion and grate or thinly slice the carrot.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over high heat. Add the steak to the skillet and sear for 3 minutes. Using tongs, turn over the steak and sear for an additional 3 to 4 minutes for medium-rare with an internal temperature of 140 F (60 C). Set aside the steak to rest for 5 minutes before slicing.
  3. In a large bowl, toss the sliced steak, bell peppers, onion and carrot with the olive oil and vinegar.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Chicken Lettuce Cups
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), ground or finely chopped
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), separated into individual leaves
  • 1 Tablespoon of almond butter (15 ml), slightly warmed (for drizzling)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the onion, grind or finely chop the chicken breast, mince or finely chop the garlic, separate the romaine lettuce into individual leaves and slightly warm the almond butter (for drizzling).
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until transparent, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  4. Add the garlic to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes.
  5. Add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos to the skillet. Season with salt, to taste.
  6. Spoon the desired amount of chicken into the lettuce leaves. Drizzle the lettuce cups with the almond butter and serve.

name: Keto Baked Egg Cups
ingredients:
• 8 slices of bacon (224 g)
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  2. In a large skillet over high heat, add the bacon and cook until the fat is rendered but not crispy, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  3. Line a greased 4-cup muffin pan with 2 slices of bacon in each cup. Crack 1 egg into each muffin cup. Lightly season each cup with salt and pepper.
  4. Place the muffin pan into the oven and bake for 20 minutes or until the eggs are cooked to your liking. Remove the eggs from the oven and let cool slightly.

name: Keto Ginger-Baked Salmon with Braised Cabbage
ingredients:
For the ginger-baked salmon -

  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the braised cabbage -

  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), to cook cabbage with
  • 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), chopped
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cup of chicken broth (120 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the ginger-baked salmon, defrost the salmon filets (if frozen) and mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger. For the braised cabbage, chop the cabbage and tomato.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Place each salmon filet on a piece of parchment paper or aluminum foil to create a packet.
  3. In a small bowl, whisk to combine the avocado oil, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, garlic, and fresh ginger. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Cover the salmon filets with equal amounts of the ginger mixture. Fold the sides and top of the parchment paper or aluminum foil to ensure the liquid remains inside each packet. Place the packets on a rimmed baking sheet.
  5. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the salmon flakes easily. Let rest for 2 to 3 minutes before serving.
  6. Meanwhile, melt the coconut oil in a large pan over high heat. Add the cabbage to the pan and saute until slightly browned, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  7. Add the tomato to the pan and saute until softened, about 1 minute.
  8. Add the chicken broth to the pan and lower the heat to a simmer. Continue to simmer until the cabbage is soft and most of the liquid has evaporated, about 20 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  9. Serve the salmon with the braised cabbage.

name: Keto Easy Sausage and Peppers
ingredients:
• 0.75 lb of sausages of your choice (338 g), sliced
  • 2 medium bell peppers (240 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), sliced
  • 1 carrot (50 g), grated or thinly sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the sausages (of your choice), bell peppers and onion and grate or thinly slice the carrot.
  2. Add the sausages to a large nonstick skillet over medium heat and saute until browned, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  3. Add the bell peppers, onion and carrot to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are slightly brown and the sausages are cooked through, about 6 to 8 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Shrimp and Cucumber Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.75 lb of shrimp (338 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), diced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Peel and devein the shrimp, defrosted if frozen. Dice the cucumber and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the shrimp, cucumber and garlic to the skillet and saute until the shrimp are cooked through, about 3 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the saute between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Egg Fried Rice
ingredients:
• 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into "rice"-like pieces
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g), whisked
  • 1 Tablespoon of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (15 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 green onions (10 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Process the cauliflower into "rice"-like pieces, whisk the eggs, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the green onions and fresh cilantro.
  2. Using clean paper towels, squeeze the excess water from the cauliflower “rice” and set aside.
  3. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a medium skillet over high heat. Add the eggs and scramble until fully cooked, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove the scrambled eggs from the skillet and set aside.
  4. Add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a separate large skillet over medium heat. Add the cauliflower “rice” to the skillet and saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
  5. Return the scrambled eggs to the skillet and add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos and garlic. Continue to saute until the egg is heated through, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the fried “rice” between plates and garnish with green onions and fresh cilantro.

name: Keto Beanless Chili and Cornbread
ingredients:
For the beanless chili -

  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml), to cook chili with
  • 2 lbs of ground beef (900 g)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), diced
  • 3 medium bell peppers (360 g), diced
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), chopped
  • 3 chili peppers (42 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 1 can of diced tomatoes (400 g)
  • 1 can of tomato paste (170 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of Italian seasoning (6 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of chili powder (2 g) (or to taste)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the “corn”bread -

  • 0.75 cup of almond flour (90 g)
  • 0.25 cup of coconut flour (28 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of baking powder (4 g)
  • 3 medium eggs, whisked
  • 0.75 cup of coconut milk (180 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), melted and cooled
  • 3 chili peppers (42 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
directions:
1. For the beanless chili, dice the onion and bell peppers, chop the mushrooms and fresh cilantro, finely dice the optional chili peppers (seeds are removed) and mince or finely dice the garlic. For the “corn”bread, whisk the eggs, melt and cool the ghee and finely dice the optional chili peppers (seeds are removed).
  2. Add the olive oil to a large pot over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef and onion and saute until browned, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  3. Add the bell peppers, mushrooms and optional chili peppers to the pot and saute for about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Add the diced tomatoes, tomato paste, Italian seasoning, and chili powder to the pot. Cover and cook for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
  5. Remove the lid and add the garlic and fresh cilantro to the pot. Continue to cook, uncovered, for about 10 minutes. Season with additional salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease or line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners and set aside.
  7. In a large bowl, combine the almond flour, coconut flour, and baking powder with the whisked eggs, coconut milk, ghee, and optional chili peppers. Mix well and pour equal amounts of the batter into the prepared muffin pan.
  8. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 20 minutes. Remove the “corn”bread from the oven and let cool.
  9. Serve the chili with the “corn”bread muffins.

name: Keto Salmon Tacos
ingredients:
• 1 can of salmon (170 g), drained and flaked
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), diced
  • 2 green onions (10 g), chopped
  • 2 teaspoons of paprika (4 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of cumin powder (4 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), broken into individual leaves
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the salmon, dice the avocado, chop the green onions and fresh cilantro and break/separate the romaine lettuce into individual leaves.
  2. In a bowl, mix to combine the salmon and mayo with the avocado, green onions, paprika, cumin powder, and fresh cilantro. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Spoon the desired amount of the salmon mixture into the lettuce leaves and serve.

name: Keto Chicken Bulgogi and Easy Kimchi
ingredients:
For the bulgogi -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 chicken breasts (800 g), ground or diced small
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), diced
  • 0.25 cup of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of sesame oil (15 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of sesame seeds (14 g) (for garnish)
  • 2 green onions (10 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt, to taste

For the kimchi -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 head of napa/Chinese cabbage (800 g), chopped or sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of hot sauce (15 ml) (or to taste) (optional)
  • 2 green onions (10 g), chopped
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the bulgogi, grind or finely dice the chicken breasts, dice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the green onions. For the kimchi, chop or slice the cabbage and chop the green onions.
  2. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and onion to the skillet and saute until the chicken is cooked through, about 10 to 12 minutes.
  3. Add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos, sesame oil, and garlic to the skillet and saute for about 1 minute. Season with salt, to taste.
  4. Meanwhile, add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a separate skillet over high heat. Add the cabbage to the skillet and saute until slightly softened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  5. Remove the skillet from the heat and toss the cabbage with the optional hot sauce and green onions. Season with salt, to taste.
  6. Divide the bulgogi among 4 plates and garnish with the sesame seeds and green onions. Serve the bulgogi with the kimchi.

name: Keto Spicy Chicken "Couscous"
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into “rice”-like pieces
  • 1 Tablespoon of tahini sauce (15 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of hot sauce (10 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast and process the cauliflower into “rice”-like pieces.
  2. In a skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and saute until cooked through, about 5 to 7 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. In a bowl, toss the cauliflower with the tahini sauce and hot sauce. Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
  4. Divide the cauliflower “couscous” between 2 plates and top with the cooked chicken.

name: Keto "Corn"bread Muffins
ingredients:
• 0.75 cup of almond flour (90 g)
  • 0.25 cup of coconut flour (28 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of baking powder (4 g)
  • 3 medium eggs (147 g), whisked
  • 0.75 cup of coconut milk (180 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), melted and cooled
  • 3 chili peppers (42 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
directions:
1. Whisk the eggs, melt and cool the ghee and finely dice the optional chili peppers (seeds are removed).
  2. Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease or line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, combine the almond flour, coconut flour, and baking powder with the whisked eggs, coconut milk, ghee and optional chili peppers. Mix well and pour equal amounts of the batter into the prepared muffin pan.
  4. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 20 minutes. Remove the “corn”bread from the oven and let cool completely before serving.

name: Keto Bean-Less Chili
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml), to cook chili with
  • 2 lbs of ground beef (900 g)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), diced
  • 3 medium bell peppers (360 g), diced
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), chopped
  • 3 chili peppers (42 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 1 can of diced tomatoes (400 g)
  • 1 can of tomato paste (170 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of Italian seasoning (6 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of chili powder (2 g) (or to taste)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the onion and bell peppers, chop the mushrooms and fresh cilantro, finely dice the optional chili peppers (seeds are removed) and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Add the olive oil to a large pot over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef and onion and saute until browned, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  3. Add the bell peppers, mushrooms and optional chili peppers to the pot and saute for about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Add the diced tomatoes, tomato paste, Italian seasoning, and chili powder to the pot. Cover and cook for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
  5. Remove the lid and add the garlic and fresh cilantro to the pot. Continue to cook, uncovered, for about 10 minutes. Season with additional salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Non-traditional Shepherd's Pie
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml)
  • 1.5 lbs of ground beef (675 g)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cups of beef broth (480 ml)
  • 2 carrots (100 g), grated
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh rosemary (6 g), finely chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh thyme (3 g), finely chopped
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 3 Tablespoons of ghee (45 ml), melted
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, grate the carrots, mince or finely dice the garlic, finely chop the fresh rosemary and fresh thyme, break the cauliflower into small florets and melt the ghee.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large saucepan or pot over high heat. Add the ground beef and onion to the pan and saute until browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Reduce the heat to low and add the beef broth, carrots, garlic, fresh rosemary and fresh thyme to the pan. Simmer, uncovered, for 25 minutes until the vegetables are soft, stirring frequently. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Meanwhile, boil the cauliflower florets in a pot of salted water until soft, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove the cauliflower from the water and drain well. Blend the cauliflower with the melted ghee using a food processor or blender. Season with salt, to taste.
  5. Add the mustard to the beef mixture and stir well to combine. Pour the beef mixture into a large square or rectangular casserole dish. Press down on the mixture with the back of a spoon to compress.
  6. Place the mashed cauliflower on top of the beef mixture.
  7. Divide the shepherd’s pie between 4 plates and serve.

name: Keto Creamy Cucumber and Avocado Salad
ingredients:
• 1 cucumber (220 g), diced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), diced
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of Italian seasoning (1 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the cucumber and avocado.
  2. In a bowl, combine the cucumber and avocado with the mayo and Italian seasoning. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto 5-Spice Pan-Fried Tilapia with Cauliflower Mash
ingredients:
• 2 filets of white fish, fresh or frozen (340 g) (tilapia or another white fish), defrost if frozen
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 Tablespoons of Chinese five-spice seasoning (12 g)
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), melted
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Defrost the white fish filets, if frozen. Break the cauliflower into small florets and melt the ghee.
  2. Season the fish filets with salt and pepper.
  3. Melt the coconut oil in a nonstick skillet over high heat. Add the fish filets to the skillet and cook for 5 minutes. Carefully turn over each filet and cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes until the fish filets are cooked through and flake easily. Sprinkle each filet with equal amounts of Chinese five-spice seasoning and additional salt and pepper, if desired.
  4. Meanwhile, boil the cauliflower florets in a pot of salted water until soft, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove the cauliflower from the water and drain well. Blend the cauliflower with the melted ghee using a food processor or blender. Season with salt, to taste.
  5. Serve with fish filets with the cauliflower mash.

name: Keto Lemon Broccoli and Tuna Bowl
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), chopped
  • 1 can of tuna (170 g), drained and flaked
  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the broccoli. Drain and flake the tuna.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the broccoli to the skillet and saute until soft, about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Meanwhile, mix the tuna with the mayo.
  4. Divide the broccoli between 2 bowls and top each bowl with equal amounts of tuna salad and lemon juice.

name: Keto Spanish Frittata
ingredients:
• 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml), to cook with (plus additional to grease the baking dish)
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), diced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), chopped
  • 6 medium eggs (294 g), whisked
  • 0.25 cup of coconut cream (60 ml) (from the top of 1 refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 0.25 cup of fresh parsley (4 g), chopped
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh thyme (1 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bell pepper and onion, chop the cauliflower, fresh parsley and fresh thyme and whisk the eggs.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Lightly grease a 9-inch (23 cm) square baking dish with olive oil and set aside.
  3. Add the olive oil to a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute for 5 minutes. Remove the vegetables from the skillet and set aside to cool.
  4. In the same skillet, add the cauliflower and saute for 10 minutes until slightly soft. (If needed, add several Tablespoons of water to the skillet to help cook the cauliflower.) Remove the cauliflower from the skillet and set aside to cool.
  5. In a large bowl, combine the whisked eggs, coconut cream, fresh parsley, and fresh thyme with the cooled vegetables. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the egg mixture into the prepared baking dish.
  6. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 20 minutes until the eggs are soft but set.
  7. Remove the baking dish from the oven and let the frittata cool slightly before serving.

name: Keto Chicken Shawarma Salad
ingredients:
For the chicken shawarma -

  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of onion powder (7 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of cumin powder (2 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of paprika (2 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of Italian seasoning (1 g)
  • Pinch of cayenne pepper (optional)
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the salad -

  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (4 g), chopped (for garnish)

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the chicken shawarma, dice the chicken breasts. For the salad, chop the romaine lettuce and fresh parsley, slice the cucumber and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a bowl, combine the garlic powder, onion powder, cumin, paprika, Italian seasoning and optional cayenne pepper. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Coat the diced chicken with the spice mixture, covering completely.
  3. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and saute until cooked through, about 8 to 10 minutes. Season with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
  4. Meanwhile, in a bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the salad leaves, cucumber and onion.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates. Top with equal amounts of chicken and garnish with fresh parsley.

name: Keto 3-Ingredient Creamy Salmon "Pasta"
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 8 oz of smoked salmon (224 g), diced
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), spiralized or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
directions:
1. Dice the salmon. Spiralize the zucchinis or use a peeler to make into long noodle-like strands.
  2. In a skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the smoked salmon and saute until slightly browned, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the zucchini “noodles” to the skillet and saute until soft, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  4. Add the mayo to the skillet, stirring well to combine.
  5. Divide the “pasta” between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Seared Duck Breast with Orange Sauce
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml), to cook with (plus additional to grease a roasting tray)
  • 1 small orange (100 g), zest (peeled into long strips, if possible)
  • 3 star anise (6 g)
  • 2 duck breasts (770 g), with the skin
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), sliced
  • 0.5 small orange (50 g), juiced
  • Pinch of erythritol, to taste (optional)
  • 1 teaspoon of arrowroot flour (2 g), for thickening sauce
  • 0.5 cup of chicken broth (120 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (4 g), finely chopped (for garnish)
  • Additional grated orange zest (for garnish) (optional)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Zest a small orange (peeled into long strips, if possible). Slice the onion, juice a half small orange, finely chop the fresh parsley and grate an orange zest (optional, for garnish).
  2. Preheat the oven to 300°F (150°C). Lightly grease a roasting tray with olive oil and set aside.
  3. Place the orange zest strips and star anise in a muslin and tie the top of it with butcher's string to create a parcel. Set aside.
  4. Using a very sharp knife, carefully score each of the duck breast skin at a 45-degree angle. Rub salt and pepper all over the duck breasts, including into the scored skin.
  5. Heat a large nonstick skillet over high heat until hot. Carefully place the duck breasts in the hot skillet, skin side down, and sear the duck breasts until the skin has caramelized and crisped, about 5 minutes.
  6. Using tongs, turn the breasts over and cook the meat side until browned, about 2 to 3 minutes. Remove the duck breasts from the skillet and place, skin side up, on the greased roasting tray.
  7. Place the roasting tray in the oven and bake for 10 to 15 minutes until the duck is cooked to your liking. Let rest for 2 to 3 minutes before serving.
  8. Meanwhile, in the same skillet with the rendered duck fat, add the olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until golden brown, about 4 to 6 minutes.
  9. Add the orange juice and the muslin parcel (with the orange zest and star anise) to the skillet and saute for 1 to 2 minutes, using a wooden spoon to scrape any brown bits from the bottom of the skillet.
  10. Strain the sauce using a fine mesh sieve and discard the onions (but not the muslin parcel).
  11. Return the strained sauce to the skillet. Untie the muslin parcel and add the orange zest and star anise to the sauce. Discard the muslin and butcher's string. If desired, add the optional stevia, to taste, to the sauce.
  12. In a small bowl, whisk to combine the arrowroot powder with the chicken broth until smooth. Pour the arrowroot mixture into the skillet and continue to cook over high heat until the sauce is the desired thickness, about an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  13. Place each duck breast on a plate and serve with the desired amount of sauce. Garnish each duck breast with fresh parsley, and additional orange zest, if desired.

name: Keto Green Beans and Bacon Saute
ingredients:
• 8 slices of bacon (224 g), diced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), diced
  • 8 oz of green beans (224 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon and onion.
  2. In a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 5 to 6 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. Add the onion to the same skillet and saute in the bacon fat until the onion is translucent, about 2 to 3 minutes. (Add avocado or coconut oil to the skillet, if needed.)
  4. Add the green beans to the skillet and saute until soft to your liking, about 5 to 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the green beans between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the crispy bacon.

name: Keto Crispy Garlic Drumsticks with Creamy Cauliflower Mash
ingredients:
For the drumsticks -

  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml) (plus additional to grease a baking tray)
  • 0.25 cup of garlic powder (40 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of salt (15 g)
  • 12 chicken drumsticks (with skin on) (1500 g)

For the cauliflower mash -

  • 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), broken into florets
  • 0.25 cup of ghee (60 ml), melted
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the mash, break the cauliflower into florets and melt the ghee.
  2. Preheat the oven to 450 F (230 C). Lightly grease a rimmed baking sheet with olive oil and set aside.
  3. In a bowl, combine the garlic powder with the salt. Dip each drumstick in the garlic salt, covering completely, and place on the greased baking sheet. Drizzle the olive oil evenly over the drumsticks.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 40 minutes until the internal temperature reaches 165 F (75 C).
  5. Meanwhile, boil or steam the cauliflower until soft, about 5 to 7 minutes. Drain well, if needed.
  6. Using a food processor or blender, combine the cauliflower with the ghee until creamy. Season with salt, to taste.
  7. Serve the drumsticks with the cauliflower mash.

name: Keto Lemon Ghee Poached Salmon with Garlic Spinach
ingredients:
For the poached salmon -

  • 2 cups of water (480 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml) (plus additional for serving)
  • 1 Tablespoon of salt (15 g)
  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh parsley (1 g), chopped

For the garlic spinach -

  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the poached salmon, defrost the salmon filets (if frozen) and chop the fresh parsley. For the garlic spinach, mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Add the water, lemon juice and salt to a saucepan over high heat and bring to a boil.
  3. Reduce the heat to a simmer and carefully add the salmon to the saucepan. Continue to simmer until the salmon is fully cooked, about 10 to 15 minutes. Remove the salmon from the water and drain well.
  4. Meanwhile, add the olive oil to a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  5. Add the garlic to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Place each salmon filet on a plate and top with the ghee, fresh parsley, and additional lemon juice, if desired. Serve the salmon with the garlic spinach.

name: Keto Roast Beef with Carrots and Onions
ingredients:
• 2 carrots (100 g), roughly chopped
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), roughly chopped
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g) lightly crushed
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml), divided
  • 4 teaspoons of fresh rosemary (4 g), divided, chopped
  • 1.75 lbs of beef round (788 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Roughly chop the carrots and onion, lightly crush the garlic and chop the fresh rosemary.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. In a bowl, toss the carrots, onion, and garlic with 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of olive oil and 2 teaspoons (2 g) of fresh rosemary. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Place the vegetables in the bottom of a roasting tray.
  4. Cover the beef round with the remaining 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of olive oil and the remaining 2 teaspoons (2 g) of fresh rosemary. Place the beef round on top of the vegetables in the roasting tray.
  5. Place the roasting tray in the oven and bake for 60 minutes or until the beef is cooked to your liking.
  6. Slice the beef and serve with the vegetables.

name: Keto Crunchy Green Salad with Soft Poached Eggs
ingredients:
• 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • 4 oz of green beans (112 g)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), diced
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 8 olives (24 g), chopped
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the avocado and chop the olives.
  2. Crack each egg in an individual cup or ramekin.
  3. Bring a pot of water to a boil and then reduce the heat to a simmer.
  4. Gently add each egg to the water and poach to your liking, gently spooning the simmering water over the eggs. Cook for 3 minutes for runny poached eggs and up to 5 minutes for soft but not runny poached eggs. Carefully remove the poached eggs from the water with a slotted spoon and place on a clean paper towel to drain.
  5. While poaching the eggs, bring a separate pot of water to a boil and add the green beans to the pot. Parboil the green beans for 1 to 2 minutes and then remove from the water. Rinse the green beans with cold water to stop the cooking process and drain well.
  6. In a large bowl, toss the parboiled green beans, avocado, spinach and olives with the olive oil and lemon juice.
  7. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top each salad with 2 poached eggs. Sprinkle the eggs with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Tuna Avocado Boats
ingredients:
• 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • 1 teaspoon of mustard (5 ml)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), pit removed and halved
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna, chop the fresh parsley and cut the avocado in half (pit removed).
  2. In a bowl, combine the tuna, mayo, fresh parsley, and mustard. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Place each avocado half on a plate and top with equal amounts of tuna.

name: Keto Grilled Chicken Skewers with Lebanese Salad
ingredients:
For the chicken skewers -

  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), cubed
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)

For the Lebanese salad -

  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 4 olives (12 g), diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh mint (2 g), diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the chicken skewers, cube the chicken breasts and chop the bell pepper and onion. For the Lebanese salad, dice the tomato, cucumber, onion, olives and fresh mint.
  2. Preheat the oven to 450 F (230 C) or preheat the grill to medium. If using wood skewers, soak in warm water for about 15 minutes.
  3. In a bowl, toss the chicken, bell pepper and onion with the olive oil. Thread the chicken and vegetables alternately on the skewers with space on both ends to allow for handling.
  4. Place the skewers on a rimmed baking sheet with the ends of the skewers resting on the rim of the baking sheet. Place in the oven and bake for 10 minutes before turning over the skewers and baking for an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until the internal temperature of the chicken reaches 165 F (75 C).
  5. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, toss the tomato, cucumber, onion, olives, and fresh mint with the olive oil and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Serve the chicken skewers with the salad.

name: Keto Steamed Veggie Bowl with Creamy Dijon Dressing
ingredients:
• 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 oz of green beans (56 g)
  • 1 carrot (50 g), sliced
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of Dijon mustard (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the cauliflower into small florets and slice the carrot.
  2. Add the cauliflower, green beans, and carrot to a steamer and steam for 5 to 10 minutes or until the vegetables are soft to your liking. (Alternatively, bring to a boil about a 1/2-inch (1.25 cm) of water in a saucepan. Add the vegetables to the saucepan, cover, and steam for 5 to 10 minutes or until soft to your liking.)
  3. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix to combine the mayo and mustard.
  4. Divide the steamed vegetables between 2 plates. Drizzle the dressing over the vegetables, and season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Bacon-Wrapped Shrimp with Spinach Salad
ingredients:
• 8 slices of bacon (224 g), cut in half (use thin bacon slices)
  • 0.5 lb of shrimp (225 g) (approx. 16 large shrimp), peeled and deveined, defrosted if frozen

For the spinach salad -

  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 4 olives (12 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Cut the bacon slices in half (use thin bacon slices). Peel and devein the shrimp (defrosted if frozen). For the salad, dice the tomato and onion and chop the olives.
  2. Preheat the oven to 450 F (230 C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper.
  3. Place the bacon slices on the parchment-lined baking sheet. Place the baking sheet on the lowest rack in the oven and bake for 5 to 7 minutes until the bacon slices are cooked but not crispy.
  4. Remove the baking sheet from the oven. Wrap each shrimp in a slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick or cocktail stick. Place each bacon-wrapped shrimp on the parchment-lined baking sheet.
  5. Return the baking sheet to the lowest rack in the oven and continue to bake for 10 to 15 minutes until the shrimp is cooked through and the bacon is slightly crispy. Remove and discard the toothpicks or cocktail sticks.
  6. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, toss the spinach leaves, tomato, onion, and olives with the olive oil and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top each salad with an equal number of the bacon-wrapped shrimp.

name: Keto Grilled Chicken Lettuce Tacos
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml)
  • 4 chicken breasts (800 g), sliced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of cumin powder (2 g)
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), separated into individual leaves
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the chicken breasts, thinly slice the onion and separate the romaine lettuce into individual leaves.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and onion to the skillet and saute until the chicken is cooked through and the onion is golden brown, about 12 to 15 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. In a bowl, combine the cooked chicken and onion with the mayo and cumin powder. Season with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
  4. Place the desired amount of the chicken mixture in the lettuce leaves and serve.

name: Keto Shrimp and Leek Pasta
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 leek (90 g), sliced
  • 0.5 lb of shrimp, fresh or frozen (225 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), grated or spiralized
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the leek. Peel and devein the shrimp (defrosted if frozen). Chop the fresh parsley and grate or spiralize the zucchini.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the leek to the skillet and saute until slightly softened, about 5 minutes.
  3. Add the shrimp to the skillet and saute until cooked through and opaque, about 3 to 5 minutes. Add the fresh parsley to the skillet and season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove from the heat and set aside.
  4. In a bowl, toss the zucchini “noodles” with the olive oil. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the zucchini “noodles” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the shrimp and leek saute.

name: Keto Onion Cauliflower Mash
ingredients:
• 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), broken into small florets
  • 3 Tablespoons of ghee (45 ml), melted
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (4 g), finely chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the cauliflower into small florets, melt the ghee, thinly slice the onion and finely chop the fresh parsley.
  2. Place the cauliflower in a steamer and steam until fork-tender, about 5 to 8 minutes. (If you do not have a steamer, bring to a boil about 1/4-inch [6.35 mm] of water in a large skillet. Place the cauliflower in the skillet and cook, covered, until fork-tender, about 5 to 8 minutes.) Remove the cauliflower from the steamer and drain.
  3. In a medium skillet, add the melted ghee over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until soft and golden brown, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  4. Place the cauliflower and onion with the pan drippings in a food processor or blender and combine until smooth. Stir in the fresh parsley and season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Bunless Burgers with Mustard and Zucchini Fries
ingredients:
For the burgers -

  • 1 lb of ground beef (450 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of onion powder (7 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of mustard (30 ml)

For the zucchini fries -

  • 0.25 cup of almond flour (30 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of Italian seasoning (3 g)
