  • 1 medium egg (49 g), whisked
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), seeds removed and cut into fry-size wedges
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the fries, whisk the egg and cut the zucchinis into fry-size wedges (seeds are removed).
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, garlic powder, and onion powder. With your hands, form the mixture into 4 patties.
  4. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. In batches, add the burgers to the skillet. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes per side for medium and 4 to 5 minutes per side for well done.
  5. Meanwhile, make the zucchini fries by combining the almond flour and Italian seasoning in a small bowl. In a separate small bowl, whisk the egg.
  6. Dip each zucchini “fry” into the whisked egg and then into the almond flour mixture. Place the zucchini fries in a single layer on a parchment paper-lined rimmed baking tray.
  7. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 30 minutes, turning once during the cooking time, until crispy and golden on the outside. Season with salt, to taste.
  8. Top the burgers with mayo and mustard and serve with the zucchini “fries.”

name: Keto Coconut Fish Soup
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cups of chicken broth (480 ml)
  • 2 filets of white fish, fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen, chopped
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 1 cup of coconut cream (240 ml) (from the tops of 2 cans of refrigerated coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion and chop the fish filets (defrosted if frozen).
  2. In a saucepan, melt the coconut oil over high heat. Add the onion to the saucepan and saute until golden brown, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken broth to the saucepan and bring to a boil.
  4. Add the fish and spinach to the saucepan and continue to boil until the fish is cooked through and the spinach is wilted, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  5. Reduce the heat to a simmer and add the coconut cream. Continue to simmer, stirring frequently, for about 5 to 6 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and serve.

name: Keto Easy Steak Salad
ingredients:
• 1 beef steak (200 g)
  • 4 Tablespoons of olive oil (60 ml), divided
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 6 olives (18 g), chopped
  • 1 teaspoon of vinegar (5 ml) (or to taste) (of choice)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the romaine lettuce and olives, dice the tomato and thinly slice the onion.
  2. Generously season the steak with salt.
  3. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of olive oil to a large skillet over high heat. Add the steak to the skillet and sear for 3 minutes. Using tongs, turn over the steak and sear for an additional 3 to 4 minutes for medium-rare with an internal temperature of 140 F (60 C). Set aside the steak to rest for 5 minutes and then slice.
  4. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, toss the romaine lettuce leaves, tomato, onion and olives with the remaining 3 Tablespoons (45 ml) of olive oil and vinegar.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with the sliced steak.

name: Keto Baked Chicken Drumsticks with Olives and Tomatoes
ingredients:
• 6 chicken drumsticks (with skin on) (750 g)
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml), divided
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 4 olives (12 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion. Chop the tomato and olives.
  2. Preheat the oven to 450 F (230 C).
  3. Toss the chicken with 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of olive oil. Place the chicken on a parchment paper-lined rimmed baking sheet.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 40 minutes until the chicken is cooked through with an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C). Set aside to rest for 2 to 3 minutes.
  5. Meanwhile, add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of olive oil to a skillet over medium heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until golden brown, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  6. Add the tomato and olives to the skillet and continue to saute until the tomato is soft, about an additional 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Serve the drumsticks with the tomato and olive saute.

name: Keto Easy Ground Beef and Pepper Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), sliced
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell pepper and onion.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until soft and slightly golden brown, about 7 to 8 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef to the skillet and saute until cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Spicy Salmon with Spinach Garlic Saute
ingredients:
• 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 2 teaspoons of hot sauce (10 ml) (or to taste)
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Defrost the salmon filets, if frozen. Thinly slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Lightly season the salmon with salt and pepper.
  3. In a medium skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over high heat. Place the salmon, skin side down, in the hot coconut oil and cook for 5 minutes. Carefully turn over the salmon and continue to cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Add the hot sauce to the skillet. Remove salmon from the skillet and set aside to rest for 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Meanwhile, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil in a separate skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until the onion is translucent, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  5. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  6. Add the garlic to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Serve the salmon with the spinach saute.

name: Keto Smoked Salmon with Poached Eggs
ingredients:
• 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • 10 oz of smoked salmon (280 g), sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • Crushed pink peppercorns, to taste (optional)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the smoked salmon.
  2. Crack each egg in an individual cup or ramekin.
  3. Bring a pot of boiling water to a boil and then reduce the heat to a simmer.
  4. Gently add each egg to the water and poach to your liking, gently spooning the simmering water over the eggs. Cook for 3 minutes for runny poached eggs and up to 5 minutes for soft but not runny poached eggs. Carefully remove the poached eggs from the water with a slotted spoon and place on a clean paper towel to drain.
  5. Place an equal amount of smoked salmon on each plate and top with the poached eggs.
  6. Drizzle the eggs with the olive oil and season with the optional pink peppercorns and salt, to taste.

name: Keto Slow Cooker Pulled Pork with Broccoli Mash
ingredients:
For the pulled pork -

  • 2 lbs of pork shoulder (900 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the broccoli mash -

  • 3 Tablespoons of ghee (45 ml), to cook with (plus additional, if needed)
  • 1 head of broccoli (450 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 small green apple (150 g), grated or thinly sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the mash, break the broccoli into small florets, thinly slice the onion and grate or thinly slice the apple.
  2. Generously season the pork shoulder with salt and pepper.
  3. If needed, cut the pork shoulder into several large pieces and place in the slow cooker. Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or on low for 6 to 8 hours until the pork shreds easily.
  4. Let the pork rest for 30 minutes before removing it from the slow cooker. Place the pork on a carving board and use 2 forks to shred it into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. While the pork rests, melt the ghee in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the broccoli and onion to the pan, cover, and cook until the vegetables are soft, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  6. Place the broccoli, onion, and pan drippings in a blender or food processor and blend until smooth. If needed, add additional ghee to create a smooth mash.
  7. Place the apple in the lemon juice and drain any excess lemon juice. Stir the apple into the broccoli mash. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  8. Serve the pulled pork with the broccoli mash.

name: Keto Chicken and Brussels Sprouts Bake
ingredients:
• 4 chicken breasts (800 g), diced
  • 16 Brussels sprouts (304 g), ends removed and quartered
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 Tablespoons of olive oil (60 ml), divided
  • 2 Tablespoons of balsamic vinegar (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breasts, cut the Brussels sprouts into quarters (ends are removed) and thinly slice the onion.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. In a bowl, toss the chicken, Brussels sprouts, and onion with 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of olive oil. Place the chicken mixture on a rimmed baking tray.
  4. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 20 minutes until the chicken is cooked through with an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C).
  5. In a small bowl, whisk to combine the balsamic vinegar with the remaining 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Drizzle the chicken and vegetables with the balsamic mixture and serve.

name: Keto Creamy Mushroom Soup
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 1 cup of chicken broth (240 ml)
  • 1 cup of coconut cream (240 ml) (from the tops of 2 refrigerated cans of coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the mushrooms and dice the onion.
  2. In a saucepan, melt the coconut oil over medium heat. Add the mushrooms and onion to the saucepan and saute until the vegetables are soft and the liquid evaporates; about 10 minutes.
  3. Reduce the heat to low and add the chicken broth and coconut cream to the saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
  4. Use an immersion blender to blend the soup until creamy. (Alternatively, use a blender or food processor to blend the soup until creamy.) Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and serve.

name: Keto Lemon Pepper Chicken Drumsticks with Cucumber Salad
ingredients:
• 4 chicken drumsticks (with skin on) (500 g)
  • 4 Tablespoons of olive oil (60 ml), divided
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml)
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), diced
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the cucumber and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.
  3. In a bowl, toss the drumsticks with 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of olive oil and lemon juice. Place the drumsticks on the prepared baking sheet. Drizzle the olive oil and lemon juice mixture over the drumsticks and season with pepper.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until the internal temperature of the drumsticks reaches 165 F (75 C).
  5. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, toss the cucumber and garlic with the remaining 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Serve the drumsticks with the cucumber salad.

name: Keto Simple Pan-Fried Salmon
ingredients:
• 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Defrost the salmon filets, if frozen.
  2. Lightly season the salmon with salt and pepper.
  3. In a medium skillet, melt the coconut oil over high heat. Place the salmon, skin side down, in the hot coconut oil and cook for 5 minutes. Carefully turn over the salmon and continue to cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Remove the salmon from the skillet and set aside to rest for 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

name: Keto Easy Salisbury Steak
ingredients:
• 2 lbs of ground beef (900 g)
  • 2 medium eggs (98 g)
  • 0.25 cup of almond flour (30 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of garlic powder (20 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of onion powder (14 g)
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Line a rimmed baking tray with parchment paper and set aside.
  2. In a large bowl, combine the ground beef with the eggs, almond flour, garlic powder, and onion powder. Form the beef mixture into 8 steak patties and place on the prepared baking tray.
  3. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until the steak patties are cooked through with an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C).

name: Keto Simple Asian Cabbage Salad
ingredients:
• 1 head of cabbage (700 g), shredded or thinly sliced
  • 3 Tablespoons of avocado oil (45 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of sesame oil (10 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Shred or thinly slice the cabbage.
  2. In a large bowl, toss the cabbage with the avocado oil, gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos, and sesame oil. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Garlicky Greek Salad
ingredients:
• 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), thinly sliced
  • 10 cherry tomatoes (170 g), halved
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 15 olives (45 g), chopped

For the dressing -

  • 0.25 cup of olive oil (60 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of dried oregano (1 g)
directions:
1. For the salad, chop the romaine lettuce and olives, thinly slice the cucumber and onion and cut the cherry tomatoes in half. For the dressing, mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves, cucumber, cherry tomatoes, onion, and olives.
  3. Divide the salad between 2 plates and enjoy.

name: Keto Lemon Brussels Sprouts
ingredients:
• 16 Brussels sprouts (304 g), ends removed and quartered
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon zest (6 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Cut the Brussels sprouts into quarters (ends are removed). Thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a medium bowl, toss to combine the Brussels sprouts and onion with the lemon juice and lemon zest. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Place the vegetables on a rimmed baking tray.
  3. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until the Brussels sprouts are soft.

name: Keto Cinnamon Chocolate Breakfast Smoothie
ingredients:
• 0.75 cup of coconut milk (180 ml)
  • 0.5 large avocado (100 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of unsweetened cacao powder (4 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of cinnamon powder (2 g)
  • 0.25 teaspoon of vanilla extract (1 ml)
  • Erythritol, to taste
  • 1 teaspoon of coconut oil (5 ml) (optional)
directions:
1. In a blender or food processor, blend all the ingredients until smooth. If the smoothie is too thick to your liking, add additional coconut milk.
  2. Pour the smoothie into a glass and enjoy.

name: Keto Chili-Style Beef and Guac
ingredients:
For the chili-style beef -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 1.75 lbs of ground beef (788 g)
  • 1 can of diced tomatoes (400 g)
  • 1 can of tomato paste (170 g)
  • 10 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (20 g), finely chopped
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the guac -

  • 1 large avocado (200 g), mashed
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), diced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh cilantro (1 g), chopped
directions:
1. For the chili-style beef, dice the onion, finely chop the fresh basil leaves and mince or finely dice the garlic. For the guac, mash the avocado, dice the tomato and onion and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a large pot, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the pot and saute until translucent, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef to the pot and saute until browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  4. Lower the heat to a simmer and add the diced tomatoes and tomato paste. Cover and continue to simmer for 90 minutes, stirring occasionally. (Add a few Tablespoons of water if the chili becomes too dry while cooking.)
  5. Increase the heat to medium-high and add the fresh basil and garlic to the pot. Continue to cook, uncovered, for an additional 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine the guac ingredients and refrigerate until ready to use.
  7. Divide the chili-style beef among 4 bowls and top with the guac.

name: Keto Chicken Zoodle Soup
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 2 cups of chicken broth (480 ml)
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), peeled and made into long noodle-like strips
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh cilantro (1 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast and onion. Peel the zucchinis and make into long noodle-like strips. Chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a saucepan over high heat. Add the chicken and onion to the saucepan and saute until just browned, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken broth to the saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to a simmer and continue to simmer until the chicken is cooked through, about 5 minutes.
  4. Add the zucchini “noodles” and fresh cilantro to the saucepan and continue to simmer for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and serve.

name: Keto Simple Mexican-Style Soup with Avocado and Lime
ingredients:
• 2 cups of chicken broth (480 ml)
  • 1 can of diced tomatoes (400 g)
  • 1 stalk of celery (20 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of cumin powder (2 g)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh cilantro (1 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the celery stalks and fresh cilantro, mince or finely dice the garlic and slice the avocado.
  2. Add the chicken broth to a saucepan over high heat and bring to a boil.
  3. Add the diced tomatoes, celery, lime juice, garlic and cumin powder to the saucepan. Reduce the heat and simmer for about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and top each bowl with the avocado slices and fresh cilantro.

name: Keto Mustard Tuna Boats
ingredients:
• 1 cucumber (220 g)
  • 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 3 stalks of celery (60 g), finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna, finely dice the celery stalks and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. Cut the cucumber in half lengthwise and then cut into 2-inch (5 cm) pieces. Scoop out the cucumber seeds to form small boats.
  3. In a small bowl, combine the tuna, celery, and fresh parsley with the mayo and mustard. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Fill the cucumber boats with equal amounts of the tuna salad and serve.

name: Keto Ham and Avocado Roll Ups
ingredients:
• 10 slices of ham (280 g)
  • 5 Tablespoons of mayo (75 ml)
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
directions:
1. Thinly slice the cucumber. Slice the avocado. 
  2. Place 5 ham slices on each plate. Spread 0.5 Tablespoon (7.5 ml) of mayo on each ham slice. Place an equal amount of cucumber and avocado on each ham slice.
  3. Roll the ham slices and enjoy.

name: Keto Asian Beef and Noodles
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 beef steaks (400 g), sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), grated or spiralized into noodle-like strands
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger. Slice the beef steaks. Grate or spiralize the zucchini into noodle-like strands and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion, garlic, and fresh ginger to the skillet and saute until the onion is soft and golden brown, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the sliced steak and tamari sauce or coconut aminos to the skillet and saute until the steak is cooked to your liking, about 2 to 3 minutes for medium rare. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the zucchini “noodles” between 2 plates and top with the steak saute. Garnish each plate with fresh cilantro and serve.

name: Keto Spinach Bacon and Avocado Salad
ingredients:
• 2 slices of bacon (56 g), diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of vinegar (15 ml) (of choice)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
directions:
1. Dice the bacon slices, thinly slice the cucumber and onion and slice the avocado.
  2. In a medium nonstick pan, cook the bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 3 to 4 minutes. Remove the bacon from the pan with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, toss the spinach, cucumber, and onion with the olive oil and vinegar.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top each salad with the sliced avocado and bacon.

name: Keto Pressure Cooker Garlic Butter Chicken
ingredients:
• 4 chicken breasts (800 g)
  • 0.25 cup of ghee (60 ml)
  • 10 cloves of garlic (30 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of salt (5 g) (plus additional, to taste)
  • 1 teaspoon of turmeric (2 g)
  • 1 cup of chicken broth (240 ml)
  • Pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Place the chicken, ghee, garlic, salt, turmeric, and chicken broth in a pressure cooker.
  3. Bring to pressure and cook on high pressure for 12 to 15 minutes until the chicken shreds easily. (If using an Instant Pot, select the poultry setting.) Quick-release the pressure and carefully remove the lid.
  4. Let the chicken rest for 5 minutes before using 2 forks to shred it in the pressure cooker. Season with additional salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Chicken and Egg Drop Soup
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g), chopped
  • 4 cups of chicken broth (960 ml)
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g), whisked
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast, thinly slice the onion, chop the spinach and whisk the eggs.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and onion to the saucepan and saute until the chicken is cooked through, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  3. Add the spinach to the saucepan and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  4. Increase the heat to high and add the chicken broth to the saucepan.
  5. Slowly add the eggs, stirring constantly, until the egg whites are fully cooked, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and serve.

name: Keto Bunless Burgers with Easy Guacamole
ingredients:
For the burgers -

  • 2 lbs of ground beef (900 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of onion powder (7 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), to cook with

For the guacamole -

  • 2 large avocados (400 g), mashed
  • 2 Tablespoons of garlic powder (20 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of onion powder (7 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • 3 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (3 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the guacamole, mash the avocados and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. Preheat the oven to 450 F (230 C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil and place the baking sheet in the oven.
  3. In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, garlic powder, and onion powder. Form the ground beef mixture into 8 to 10 burger patties.
  4. In a nonstick skillet, melt the coconut oil over high heat. In batches, sear the burger patties for 2 minutes per side and set aside until all of the burger patties are seared.
  5. Carefully remove the rimmed baking sheet from the oven. Place the burger patties on the baking sheet in a single layer.
  6. Return the baking sheet to the oven and bake for 8 to 9 minutes for medium-rare, 10 to 11 minutes for medium, and 13 to 15 minutes for well-done.
  7. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine the guacamole ingredients and refrigerate until ready to use.
  8. Serve the burgers with the guacamole.

name: Keto Ham and Spinach Egg Cups
ingredients:
• 3 medium eggs (147 g), whisked
  • 4 slices of ham (112 g), diced
  • 0.25 cup of coconut milk (60 ml)
  • 1 cup of spinach (30 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), finely diced
  • 0.5 teaspoon of baking powder (1 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease 2 large or 4 small ramekins.
  2. In a bowl, combine the eggs, ham, coconut milk, spinach, onion, and baking powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the mixture into the prepared ramekins or mini quiche pans.
  3. Place the ramekins in the oven and bake for 15 minutes until the eggs are set. Remove from the oven and let cool for 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

name: Keto Steak Bites with Cauliflower Mash
ingredients:
For the steak bites -

  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 beef steaks (800 g), cut into bite-size pieces
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the cauliflower mash -

  • 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), melted
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the steak bites, thinly slice the onion and cut the beef steaks into bite-size pieces. For the mash, break the cauliflower into small florets and melt the ghee.
  2. Boil or steam the cauliflower until soft, about 5 to 7 minutes. Drain well.
  3. Using a food processor or blender, combine the cauliflower with 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of ghee. Season with salt, to taste.
  4. Meanwhile, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of ghee in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until soft and golden brown, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  5. Add the steak to the skillet and sear until cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Serve the steak bites with the cauliflower mash.

name: Keto Mustard Pork Chops with Spinach and Bacon
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 pork chops (320 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 2 slices of bacon (56 g), diced
  • 8 cups of spinach (240 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Generously season the pork chops with salt and pepper.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over high heat. Using tongs, place the pork chops on their sides with the fat in direct contact with the skillet. Render until the fat is brown and crispy.
  4. Reduce the heat to medium-high and place the pork chops flat in the skillet. Cook the pork chops for 3 minutes. Turn over and cook for an additional 3 to 5 minutes with an internal temperature of 145 F (63 C) for medium-rare. Remove the pork chops from the skillet and let rest for 5 minutes.
  5. Add the mustard to the skillet and reduce the heat to low to keep warm until ready to serve. Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
  6. Meanwhile, in a separate nonstick skillet over medium heat, add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  7. Add the spinach and garlic to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  8. Drizzle the pork chops with the mustard sauce and serve with the sauteed spinach.

name: Keto Egg and Avocado Salad with Spinach
ingredients:
• 4 medium eggs
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), diced
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of mustard (5 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the avocado.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove the pot from heat. Place a lid on the pot and let sit for 12 minutes. Drain the eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and chop the eggs.
  3. Meanwhile, in a bowl, toss the spinach with the olive oil. Divide the spinach between 2 plates.
  4. In the same bowl, combine the chopped eggs and avocado with the mayo and mustard. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Place equal amounts of the egg and avocado salad on top of the spinach leaves and serve.

name: Keto Roasted Broccoli and Tuna Bowls
ingredients:
• 1 head of broccoli (450 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml), divided
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of tahini sauce (30 ml)
  • 1.5 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (23 ml)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of sesame oil (3 ml)
  • 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the broccoli into small florets. Drain and flake the tuna.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. In a large bowl, toss the broccoli with 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Place the broccoli in a single layer on a rimmed baking sheet.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 20 minutes until tender and slightly brown.
  5. Remove the broccoli from the oven and place in the same large bowl. Toss the roasted broccoli with the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of olive oil and lemon juice. Season with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
  6. In a small bowl, whisk to combine the tahini sauce, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, and sesame oil. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Divide the broccoli between 2 bowls and top with equal amounts of tuna. Drizzle equal amounts of the tahini mixture over the tuna and serve.

name: Keto Garlic Oregano Olive Tapenade
ingredients:
• 1 cup of pitted olives (140 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh oregano leaves (3 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g) (plus addition, if desired)
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. Place all the ingredients into a high-speed blender or food processor and blend really well. Season with salt, to taste.
  2. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

name: Keto Chicken and Veggie Casserole
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 chicken breasts (800 g), diced
  • 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), broken into small florets
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 3 Tablespoons of fresh thyme (9 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • 1 cup of coconut cream (240 ml) (from the top of 2 refrigerated cans of coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breasts, break the cauliflower into small florets, slice the mushrooms, thinly slice the onion and chop the fresh thyme and fresh parsley.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease a large baking dish and set aside.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 10 to 15 minutes. Season with salt, to taste.
  4. In a large bowl, combine the cooked chicken with the remaining ingredients. Pour the mixture into the prepared baking dish.
  5. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 60 minutes until the vegetables are soft to your liking. Remove from the oven and let cool slightly before serving.

name: Keto Simple Smoked Salmon and Avocado Salad
ingredients:
• 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • 4 oz of smoked salmon (112 g)
directions:
1. Chop the romaine lettuce and slice the avocado.
  2. In a large bowl, toss the romaine lettuce leaves with the olive oil and lemon juice.
  3. Divide the lettuce leaves between 2 plates and top with the sliced avocado and smoked salmon.

name: Keto Spaghetti and Ground Chicken Meatballs
ingredients:
For the meatballs -

  • 0.75 lb of ground chicken (338 g)
  • 1 medium egg, whisked
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of salt (9 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of pepper (1 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook meatballs with

For the “spaghetti” and sauce -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook the sauce with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 8 cherry tomatoes (136 g), chopped
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to make into noodle-like strands
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the meatballs, whisk the egg. For the “spaghetti” and sauce, thinly slice the onion, chop the cherry tomatoes and fresh cilantro, mince or finely dice the garlic and spiralize the zucchini or use a vegetable peeler to make it into noodle-like strands.
  2. In a medium bowl, combine the ground chicken, egg, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Form the mixture into 1-inch (2.5 cm) meatballs.
  3. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. In batches, add the meatballs to the skillet and brown on all sides, about 2 to 3 minutes per meatball. Remove the browned meatballs from the skillet and set aside.
  4. In the same skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion and saute until slightly browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  5. Add the tomatoes, garlic, and fresh cilantro to the skillet and saute for about 5 minutes.
  6. Add the coconut cream to the skillet and continue to saute until the sauce starts to bubble. Reduce the heat to a simmer and return the meatballs to the skillet. Cover and continue to simmer for 15 minutes until the meatballs are cooked through with an internal temperature of 165 F (74 C). Season the sauce with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Divide the zucchini “noodles” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of meatballs and sauce.

name: Keto Bacon and Spinach Scramble
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 4 white button mushrooms (40 g), sliced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g), whisked
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, slice the mushrooms and whisk the eggs.
  2. In a nonstick skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium heat. Add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 4 to 5 minutes. Remove the bacon with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. In the same skillet over medium heat, add the mushrooms and saute until softened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the spinach and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Return the bacon to the skillet. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Meanwhile, in a separate skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium heat. Add the eggs and scramble until cooked to your liking, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the scrambled eggs between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the spinach saute.

name: Keto Baked Garlic Chicken Nuggets with Broccoli Mash
ingredients:
For the chicken nuggets -

  • 0.5 cup of coconut flour (56 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 medium egg (49 g)
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), cut into approx. 1.5-inch (4 cm) pieces
  • Salt, to taste

For the broccoli mash -

  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g)
  • 0.25 cup of coconut milk (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Cut the chicken breasts into approximately 1.5-inch (4 cm) pieces.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Line a rimmed baking tray with parchment paper and set aside.
  3. In a bowl, combine the coconut flour, garlic powder, and salt.
  4. In a separate bowl, whisk the egg to create an egg wash.
  5. Dip each chicken piece into the egg wash and then completely cover with the coconut flour mixture. Place the coated chicken in a single layer on the prepared baking tray.
  6. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 20 minutes, turning over the chicken nuggets after 10 minutes of cook time. Remove from the oven and let cool slightly.
  7. Meanwhile, add the broccoli to a steamer and steam for about 5 minutes or until soft to your liking. (Alternatively, bring to a boil about a 1/2-inch (1.25 cm) of water in a saucepan. Add the broccoli to the saucepan, cover, and steam for about 5 minutes or until soft to your liking.)
  8. Add the steamed broccoli and coconut milk to a high-speed blender or food processor and blend until smooth. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  9. Serve the chicken nuggets with the broccoli mash.

name: Keto Beef and Cabbage Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 0.5 lb of ground beef (225 g)
  • 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 green onions (20 g), sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 3 teaspoons of hot sauce (15 ml) (or to taste) (optional)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of ginger powder (1 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the cabbage. Slice the green onions.
  2. In a large nonstick skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef and stir-fry until cooked through, about 3 to 4 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove the ground beef from the skillet and set aside.
  3. In the same skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the cabbage and green onions to the skillet and stir-fry until softened, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  4. Return the ground beef to the skillet and add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos, optional hot sauce, and ginger powder. Stir-fry for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the stir-fry between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Bacon Zoodle Salad
ingredients:
• 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands
  • 6 cherry tomatoes (102 g), halved
  • 0.25 cup of fresh basil leaves (8 g), chopped
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, spiralize the zucchinis or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands, cut the cherry tomatoes into halves, chop the fresh basil leaves and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a nonstick skillet over medium heat, add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 4 to 5 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, toss the zucchini “noodles,” tomatoes, fresh basil, and garlic with the olive oil and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the “noodles” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of bacon.

name: Keto Slow Cooker Beef Stroganoff
ingredients:
• 2 cups of beef broth (480 ml)
  • 2 lbs of beef roast (900 g), sliced into thin strips
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 3 Tablespoons of Dijon mustard (45 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the beef roast into thin strips. Thinly slice the onion, slice the mushrooms and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Place the beef broth, beef roast, onion, mushrooms, and garlic in the bottom of a slow cooker.
  3. Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or on low for 6 to 8 hours until the beef is tender.
  4. Add the coconut cream and mustard to the slow cooker and stir well to combine. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Shrimp Scampi with Sauteed Cabbage
ingredients:
For the shrimp scampi -

  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook the shrimp with
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 lb of shrimp (450 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the sauteed cabbage -

  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), to cook the cabbage with
  • 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), thinly sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the shrimp scampi, mince or finely dice the garlic and peel and devein the shrimp (defrosted if frozen). For the sauteed cabbage, thinly slice the cabbage.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the cabbage to the skillet and saute until soft, about 8 to 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Meanwhile, in a separate skillet, melt the ghee over medium heat. Add the garlic to the skillet and saute until fragrant, about 30 seconds.
  4. Add the shrimp to the skillet and saute until cooked through and opaque, about 2 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the sauteed cabbage between 2 plates. Top each plate with the shrimp and garlic ghee sauce.

name: Keto Bacon and Tomato Stuffed Avocados
ingredients:
• 2 slices of bacon (56 g), diced
  • 2 large avocados (400 g)
  • 8 cherry tomatoes (136 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 1 green onion (5 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon. Chop the cherry tomatoes and green onion.
  2. In a nonstick skillet over medium heat, add the bacon and saute until crispy, about 2 to 3 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. Meanwhile, cut each avocado in half lengthwise and remove the pits. With a spoon, carefully scoop out the flesh of the avocado and set aside the avocado skins.
  4. In a medium bowl, combine the diced bacon, avocados, tomatoes, mayo, and green onion. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Fill the avocado skins with equal amounts of the avocado mixture and serve.

name: Keto Bread Rolls
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), melted
  • 6 Tablespoons of coconut flour (42 g)
  • 0.25 teaspoon baking soda (1 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of gelatin (12 g)
  • 6 Tablespoons of hot water (90 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of Italian seasoning (1 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of salt (2 g)
directions:
1. Melt the coconut oil.
  2. Preheat the oven to 300°F (150°C).
  3. In a medium bowl, combine the coconut oil, coconut flour, and baking soda.
  4. In a separate bowl, whisk together the gelatin and hot water to create your gelatin egg.
  5. Pour the gelatin egg mixture into the coconut flour mixture and combine well.
  6. Add in the Italian seasoning and salt, to taste, and mix well into a dough. (You can taste the mixture and add more seasonings, if desired.)
  7. Use your hands to form 2 small rolls. Place each roll on a baking tray lined with parchment paper.
  8. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 40 to 50 minutes until the outside of each roll is slightly browned and crispy (like a typical bread roll).
  9. Let the rolls cool completely before serving in order for the gelatin to set and hold the roll together. Enjoy at room temperature with ghee, coconut oil, or dipped in olive oil.

Note: This recipe can be doubled, tripled, etc. if you want to make more Keto bread rolls at the same time.

name: Keto Chicken Caesar Salad
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the Caesar dressing -

  • 4 Tablespoons of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of Dijon mustard (5 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of garlic powder (3 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. In a small bowl, combine the dressing ingredients and set aside.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and saute until cooked through, about 5 to 7 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Set aside to cool slightly.
  3. In a large bowl, toss the romaine lettuce leaves with the Caesar dressing. Add the cooked chicken, cucumber, and onion to the bowl.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Slow Cooker Pork Carnitas
ingredients:
• 2 lbs of pork shoulder (900 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of chili powder (6 g) (or to taste)
  • 1 Tablespoon of cumin powder (6 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of paprika (6 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of dried oregano (3 g)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. If needed, cut the pork shoulder into several large pieces to fit in the slow cooker.
  3. Make a paste by combining the olive oil, lime juice, chili powder, cumin powder, paprika, and dried oregano. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Rub the paste all over the pork shoulder.
  4. Place the onion and garlic in the bottom of the slow cooker. Place the pork shoulder on top of the onion and garlic.
  5. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 4 to 5 hours until the pork shreds easily.
  6. Let the pork rest for 30 minutes before removing it from the slow cooker. Place the pork on a carving board and use 2 forks to shred it into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Beef and Asparagus Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 8 spears of asparagus (128 g), trimmed and cut into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Trim and cut the asparagus into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces. Mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium heat. Add the asparagus to the skillet and saute for 5 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef and garlic to the skillet and saute until the ground beef is cooked through and the asparagus is soft, about 6 to 8 minutes.
  4. Add the spinach and lime juice to the skillet and saute until the spinach is wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the stir-fry between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Shrimp Fried Rice
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 lb of shrimp (450 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of sesame oil (5 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Process the cauliflower into rice-like pieces. Thinly slice the onion. Peel and devein the shrimp (defrosted if frozen). Mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the cauliflower and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Meanwhile, in a separate large skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium heat. Add the shrimp to the skillet and saute until cooked through and opaque, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the cooked shrimp, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, sesame oil, garlic, and fresh ginger to the cauliflower “rice” and saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the fried “rice” between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Garlic Chicken and Peppers
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 teaspoon of cumin powder (1 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of paprika (1 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell pepper, thinly slice the onion, dice the chicken breasts and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until slightly soft, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken breasts to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 7 to 10 minutes.
  4. Add the garlic, cumin powder and paprika to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the saute between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Oven-Baked Salmon and Vegetable Medley
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml)
  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen, cut into large pieces
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 4 spears of asparagus (64 g), trimmed and cut into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), sliced
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Cut the salmon filets into large pieces, defrosted if frozen. Break the cauliflower into small florets. Trim and cut the asparagus into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces and slice the onion.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. In a large bowl, combine the avocado oil, salmon, cauliflower, asparagus, and onion. Pour the mixture evenly onto a rimmed baking tray.
  4. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 25 minutes until the vegetables are soft and the salmon is cooked through and flakes easily. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and top with the salmon and vegetables.

name: Keto Warm Bacon Slaw
ingredients:
• 6 slices of bacon (168 g), diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 1 head of cabbage (700 g), shredded or thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 5 Tablespoons of mayo (75 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of mustard (10 ml)
  • 3 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (3 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, shred or thinly slice the cabbage, thinly slice the onion and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. In a nonstick skillet over medium heat, add the bacon and cook until crispy, about 8 to 10 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. Meanwhile, in a separate skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the cabbage and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 7 to 10 minutes.
  4. In a large bowl, combine the mayo, olive oil, mustard, and fresh parsley. Add the cabbage mixture and bacon to the bowl and combine completely.

name: Keto Chicken Adobo with Broccoli Mash
ingredients:
For the chicken adobo -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml)
  • 4 chicken breasts (800 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 8 cloves of garlic (24 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 cup of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (120 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons + 2 teaspoons of vinegar (40 ml) (of choice)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the broccoli mash -

  • 1 head of broccoli (450 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 cup of coconut milk (120 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the chicken adobo, chop the chicken breasts, thinly slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic. For the mash, break the broccoli into small florets.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the chicken breasts, onion, and garlic to the saucepan and saute until the chicken is browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Reduce the heat to medium-low and add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos and vinegar to the saucepan. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 20 to 25 minutes until the chicken is cooked through. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Meanwhile, add the broccoli to a steamer and steam for about 5 minutes or until soft to your liking. (Alternatively, bring to a boil about a 1/2-inch (1.25 cm) of water in a saucepan. Add the broccoli to the saucepan, cover, and steam for about 5 minutes or until soft to your liking.)
  5. Add the steamed broccoli and coconut milk to a high-speed blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
  6. Serve the chicken adobo with the broccoli mash.

name: Keto Chopped Salad with Mustard Vinaigrette
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 4 medium eggs
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), chopped
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced

For the mustard vinaigrette -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of vinegar (15 ml) (of choice)
  • 3 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (3 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the salad, chop the romaine lettuce, avocado and tomato and thinly slice the onion. For the mustard vinaigrette, chop the fresh parsley.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove the pot from heat. Place a lid on the pot and let sit for 12 minutes. Drain the eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and chop the eggs.
  3. In a bowl, whisk to combine the olive oil, mustard, vinegar, and fresh parsley. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves. Add the chopped eggs, avocado, tomato, and onion to the bowl.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Eggs Florentine with Sauteed Asparagus
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 8 spears of asparagus (128 g), trimmed and cut in half lengthwise
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), finely diced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • 0.25 cup of coconut milk (60 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook eggs with
  • 4 medium eggs
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Trim and cut the asparagus in half lengthwise. Finely dice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of ghee over high heat. Add the asparagus and saute until slightly brown and tender, about 3 to 4 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove the asparagus from the skillet and set aside.
  3. In the same skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of ghee. Add the onion and garlic and saute until translucent, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  5. Add the coconut milk and fresh parsley to the skillet. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Remove the skillet from the heat and set aside.
  6. In a medium skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the eggs to the skillet and fry until cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Divide the eggs and asparagus between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the spinach cream sauce.

name: Keto Coconut Pancakes
ingredients:
• 4 medium eggs, whisked
  • 0.5 cup of coconut flour (56 g)
  • 1 cup of coconut milk (240 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of vanilla extract (10 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of baking soda (4 g)
  • Erythritol, to taste (optional)
  • 4 Tablespoons of coconut oil (60 ml), to cook with
  • Ghee or coconut butter, for serving
directions:
1. Whisk the eggs.
  2. In a medium bowl, combine the whisked eggs, coconut flour, coconut milk, vanilla extract, baking soda, and optional erythritol.
  3. In a large nonstick skillet, melt the coconut oil over low heat. In batches, ladle the batter into the skillet to form pancakes that are 3 inches (7.5 cm) in diameter. (The batter is thick and does not spread.)
  4. Cook each pancake for 2 minutes. Carefully turn over each pancake and continue to cook for an additional 2 minutes. If needed, continue to cook each pancake, flipping occasionally, until each side is golden brown and the pancake is cooked through.
  5. To serve, top the pancakes with ghee or coconut butter, if desired.

name: Keto Stuffed Chicken Breast
ingredients:
For the pesto -

  • 1/3 cup of olive oil (80 ml) (plus additional, if needed)
  • 1.5 cups of fresh basil leaves (50 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of pine nuts (16 g) (or walnuts)
  • 2 cloves garlic (6 g), roughly chopped
  • 0.5 lemon, juice and zest
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the stuffed chicken breast -

  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (approx. 300 g), broken into florets
  • 2 Tablespoons of Keto Pesto (30 ml) (see recipe above)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • Pinch of cayenne pepper (optional)
  • 2 chicken breasts (approx. 200 g each)
  • 3 Tablespoons of coconut oil (45 ml), to cook with (plus additional to grease the baking tray)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the pesto, roughly chop the garlic and juice and zest the lemon. For the stuffed chicken breast, break the cauliflower into florets.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (180 C). Grease a rimmed baking tray with coconut oil and set aside.
  3. Place the pesto ingredients in a food processor or blender and blend until fully combined. (Refrigerate any unused pesto in an airtight container for up to 3 days.)
  4. Place the cauliflower in a steamer and steam until fork-tender, about 5 to 8 minutes. (If you do not have a steamer, bring to a boil about 1/4-inch [6.35 mm] of water in a large skillet. Place the cauliflower in the skillet and cook, covered, until fork-tender, about 5 to 8 minutes.) Remove the cauliflower from the steamer and drain.
  5. Place the cauliflower and 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of pesto in a food processor or blender and blend until fully combined. Set aside.
  6. In a small bowl, combine the garlic powder and cayenne pepper, if using. Add salt and pepper, to taste. Rub the garlic mixture onto each chicken breast, covering completely.
  7. Using a sharp knife, carefully cut an opening into one side of each chicken breast to create a pocket for the stuffing.
  8. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Place each chicken breast in the skillet and sear on both sides, about 2 to 3 minutes per side. Remove the chicken from the skillet and let cool slightly.
  9. Once the chicken is cool enough to handle, spoon an equal amount of the cauliflower pesto mixture into the pocket of each chicken breast. Place each chicken breast on the prepared baking tray.
  10. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 20 minutes until the chicken has an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C). (Be sure to measure the temperature of the chicken breast and not the stuffing.) Remove the chicken from the oven and let cool for 2 to 3 minutes.
  11. Serve the stuffed chicken breasts with the remaining pesto, if desired.

name: Keto Mustard Fish Salad
ingredients:
• 2 cans of sardines (or canned tuna) (200 g), drained and flaked
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), diced
  • 3 Tablespoons of mayo (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of lemon juice (10 ml) (or to taste)
  • 2 oz of kale (56 g), stems removed
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the sardines, dice the cucumber and remove the kale’s stems.
  2. In a medium bowl, combine the sardines and cucumber with the mayo, mustard, and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the kale between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of fish salad.

name: Keto Pressure Cooker Beef Curry
ingredients:
• 2 lbs of beef stew chunks (900 g)
  • 0.5 cup of beef broth (120 ml) (or water)
  • 2 Tablespoons of curry powder (14 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 head of broccoli (450 g), broken into small florets
  • 3 zucchinis (360 g), chopped
  • 1.75 cups of coconut milk (420 ml)
  • Salt to taste
directions:
1. Break the broccoli into small florets. Chop the zucchinis.
  2. Add the beef chunks, beef broth, curry powder, and garlic powder to the pressure cooker. Secure the lid and cook for 25 minutes on high pressure.
  3. Carefully release the pressure and add the broccoli and zucchinis to the pressure cooker. Secure the lid and cook for an additional 10 minutes on high pressure.
  4. Carefully release the pressure and stir in the coconut milk. Season with salt, to taste.

name: Keto Chicken Couscous Salad
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), diced
  • 4 green onions (20 g), chopped
  • 0.25 cup of fresh parsley (4 g), chopped
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 teaspoons of cumin powder (4 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast and cucumber. Process the cauliflower into rice-like pieces. Chop the green onions and fresh parsley and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until fully cooked, about 6 to 8 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.
  3. In the same skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil. Add the cauliflower to the skillet and saute until just soft, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  4. In a large bowl, combine the cooked chicken and sauteed cauliflower with the olive oil, lemon juice, cucumber, green onions, fresh parsley, garlic, and cumin powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the “couscous” between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Pork and Ginger Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 2 medium eggs (98 g), whisked
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g), sliced
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Whisk the eggs, slice the bell pepper and pork tenderloin, thinly slice the onion, chop the zucchini and mince or finely dice the fresh ginger and garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the whisked eggs and cook until scrambled, about 2 to 3 minutes. Remove the scrambled eggs from the skillet and set aside.
  3. In the same skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables start to soften, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the pork to the skillet and saute until browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  5. Return the egg to the skillet and add the zucchini, fresh ginger, and garlic. Continue to saute until the zucchini is soft and the pork is cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the stir-fry between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Coconut Seafood Soup
ingredients:
• 3 cups of chicken broth (720 ml) (plus additional, if needed)
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), chopped
  • 2 oz of kale (56 g), stems removed and chopped
  • 5 white button mushrooms (50 g), sliced
  • 2 filets of white fish, fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen, cut into large pieces
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the zucchini and kale (stems are removed). Slice the mushrooms and cut the fish filets into large pieces (defrosted if frozen).
  2. Add the chicken broth to a saucepan over high heat and bring to a boil.
  3. Reduce the temperature to medium-high and add the zucchini, kale, and mushrooms to the saucepan and continue to boil until the vegetables are slightly soft, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the fish to the saucepan and continue to boil until the fish is cooked through, about 4 minutes. (Add additional chicken broth to cover the fish, if needed.)
  5. Remove the saucepan from the heat and gently stir in the coconut cream careful to not break the fish into small pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and serve.

name: Keto Quick Beef Tacos
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), diced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of garlic powder (7 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of cumin powder (2 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of paprika (2 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of dried oregano (1 g)
  • 0.25 teaspoon of chili powder (1 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of water (30 ml)
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), separated into individual leaves
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bell pepper, thinly slice the onion and separate the romaine lettuce into individual leaves.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are slightly soft, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef to the skillet and saute until browned, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the garlic powder, cumin powder, paprika, dried oregano, chili powder, and water to the skillet and continue to cook until the sauce is slightly thickened, about 3 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Place the desired amount of taco meat in the lettuce leaves and serve.

name: Keto Chicken Mushroom and Kale Casserole
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with (plus additional to grease the baking dish)
  • 8 chicken thighs (with skin on) (1200 g)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh rosemary (6 g), chopped
  • 30 white button mushrooms (300 g), sliced
  • 2 oz of kale (56 g), stems removed and chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic, chop the fresh rosemary and kale (stems are removed) and slice the mushrooms.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C). Grease a large baking dish with avocado oil and set aside.
  3. With a clean paper towel, pat dry the chicken thighs. Season each side of the chicken with salt and pepper.
  4. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet, skin side down, and cook until the skin is golden brown and crispy, about 5 to 8 minutes.
  5. Carefully turn over the chicken and cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Remove the chicken from the skillet and place in the prepared baking dish.
  6. Reduce the heat to medium-low and add the onion, garlic, and fresh rosemary to the same skillet with cooking fat from the chicken. Cook until the onion is soft, about 10 to 15 minutes.
  7. Increase the heat to medium-high and continue to cook the onion until caramelized with a jam-like consistency. (Add additional avocado oil to the skillet to prevent burning, if needed.)
  8. Add the mushrooms to the skillet and cook until softened, about 2 to 4 minutes. Place the onion mixture around the chicken thighs in the baking dish.
  9. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake at 350°F (180°C) for 20 minutes.
  10. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, toss the kale with the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil.
  11. Remove the baking dish from the oven and increase the heat to 400 F (200 C).
  12. Scatter the kale around the chicken in the baking dish and return the baking dish to the oven.
  13. Continue to bake for an additional 5 minutes until the chicken is cooked through and an instant-read thermometer reaches 165 F (75 C).
  14. Remove the baking dish from the oven and season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Salmon and Broccoli Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), chopped small
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen, diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 1 oz of kale (28 g), stems removed
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger. Chop the broccoli into small pieces. Thinly slice the onion. Dice the salmon filets, defrosted if frozen. Remove the stems of the kale.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the garlic and fresh ginger to the skillet and saute until fragrant, about 30 seconds.
  3. Add the broccoli and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are slightly softened, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the salmon and gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos to the skillet and saute until the salmon is cooked through, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  5. Add the kale to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the saute between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Pan-Seared Pork Tenderloin with Buttery Mash
ingredients:
For the pork tenderloin -

  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the mash -

  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), melted
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the mash, break the cauliflower into small florets and melt the ghee.
  2. Sprinkle the pork with salt and pepper. Set aside.
  3. In a nonstick skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the pork to the skillet and sear on all sides, about 1 to 2 minutes per side.
  4. Reduce heat to medium and continue to cook until done to your liking, about 6 to 8 minutes with an internal temperature of 145 F (63 C) for medium-rare. (Cook the pork for about 10 minutes for medium.) Remove the pork from the skillet and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing.
  5. Meanwhile, boil or steam the cauliflower until soft, about 5 to 7 minutes. Drain well. 
  6. Using a food processor or blender, combine the cauliflower with the ghee until smooth. Season with salt, to taste.
  7. Serve the sliced pork with the mash.

name: Keto Poached Egg and Avocado Toast
ingredients:
• 2.5 Tablespoons of ghee (38 ml), melted (plus additional for the mug)
  • 3 medium eggs (147 g)
  • 1/3 cup of almond flour (40 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of baking powder (1 g)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Melt the ghee and slice the avocado.
  2. Grease a microwave-safe mug with ghee and set aside.
  3. In a small bowl, whisk 1 egg. With a small whisk or fork, combine the whisked egg with the almond flour, baking powder, and a dash of salt. Pour the mixture into the greased mug.
  4. Place the mug in a microwave and cook for 90 seconds on high. Remove from the microwave and let cool slightly.
  5. Once the mug is cool enough to handle, gently remove the bread and slice into 4 pieces.
  6. Toast the bread using a toaster, toaster oven, or under a broiler until toasted to your liking.
  7. Meanwhile, crack the remaining 2 eggs into individual cups or ramekins.
  8. Bring a pot of water to a boil and then reduce the heat to a simmer.
  9. Gently add each egg to the water and poach to your liking, gently spooning the simmering water over the eggs. Cook for 3 minutes for runny poached eggs and up to 5 minutes for soft but not runny poached eggs. Carefully remove the poached eggs from the water with a slotted spoon and place on a clean paper towel to drain.
  10. To serve, place 2 slices of “toast” on each plate and top with the sliced avocado and a poached egg. Season with salt and pepper, if desired.

name: Keto Asian-Inspired Beef and Noodle Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), shredded or very thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 beef steaks (400 g), sliced
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands
  • 1 Tablespoon of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (15 ml)
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Shred or very thinly slice the broccoli, thinly slice the onion, slice the beef steaks and spiralize the zucchini or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands. Mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the broccoli and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are slightly soft, about 6 to 8 minutes.
  3. Add the steaks to the skillet and saute until just browned, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  4. Add the zucchini, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, garlic, and fresh ginger to the skillet and continue to saute until the steaks are cooked to your liking, about an additional 1 to 2 minutes for medium-rare. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the stir-fry between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Veggie and Kale Scramble
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g), whisked
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), chopped
  • 2 oz of kale (56 g), stems removed and chopped
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Whisk the eggs, slice the mushrooms and avocado, chop the zucchini and kale (stems are removed) and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium heat. Add the whisked eggs and scramble until completely cooked, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove the eggs from the skillet and set aside.
  3. In the same skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms to the skillet and saute until soft, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the zucchini to the skillet and saute until softened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  5. Add the kale to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  6. Return the scrambled eggs to the skillet and add the garlic. Continue to saute until the eggs are heated through, about 1 minute. Season with additional salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Divide the scramble between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of sliced avocado.

name: Keto Ham and Bell Pepper Wraps
ingredients:
• 6 slices of ham (168 g)
  • 3 Tablespoons of mayo (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
directions:
1. Thinly slice the bell pepper and cucumber and chop the romaine lettuce.
  2. Spread each slice of ham with 0.5 Tablespoon (7.5 ml) of mayo and 0.5 teaspoon (2.5 ml) of mustard. Place an equal amount of sliced bell pepper and cucumber on the ham slices and roll each slice to create a wrap.
  3. In a large bowl, toss the romaine lettuce leaves with the olive oil and lemon juice.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates. Top each salad with 3 ham wraps and serve.

name: Keto Quick Bolognese Sauce
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 lbs of ground beef (900 g)
  • 6 small tomatoes (540 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of Italian seasoning (3 g)
  • 8 cloves of garlic (24 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 cup of fresh basil leaves (16 g), finely chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, dice the tomatoes, mince or finely dice the garlic and finely chop the fresh basil leaves.
  2. In a large pan, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the pan and saute until soft, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef to the pan and saute until browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  4. Reduce the heat to a simmer and add the tomatoes and Italian seasoning to the pan. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. (If time allows, simmer for 60 minutes.)
  5. Add the garlic and fresh basil to the pan and continue to simmer, uncovered, for an additional 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Spinach and Bacon Salad
ingredients:
• 6 slices of bacon (168 g), diced
  • 6 cups of spinach (180 g)
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml) (or to taste)
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, chop the tomatoes and thinly slice the cucumber.
  2. Add the bacon to a nonstick skillet over medium heat and saute until crispy, about 5 minutes.
  3. In a large bowl, toss the spinach, tomatoes, and cucumber with the olive oil and lemon juice.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with the diced bacon.

name: Keto Fish and Leek Saute with Cauli-Rice
ingredients:
For the saute -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 leek (90 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 filets of cod (680 g), defrosted if frozen, chopped small
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the cauli-“rice” -

  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook cauliflower with
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
