1. For the saute, thinly slice the leek, chop the cod filets into small pieces (defrosted if frozen) and mince or finely dice the fresh ginger. For the cauli-“rice”, process the cauliflower into rice-like pieces.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium heat. Add the leek to the skillet and saute until soft, about 5 minutes.
  3. Add the cod, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, and fresh ginger to the skillet and saute until the cod is opaque and cooked through, about 2 to 4 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Meanwhile, in a separate large skillet, melt the ghee over high heat. Add the cauliflower to the skillet and saute until soft, about 5 minutes. Season with salt, to taste.
  5. Divide the cauli-“rice” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the saute.

name: Keto Ham and Spinach Mini Breakfast Quiches
ingredients:
• 6 medium eggs (294 g), whisked
  • 8 slices of ham (224 g), diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.5 cup of coconut milk (120 ml)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of baking powder (1 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Whisk the eggs, dice the ham, chop the spinach and thinly slice the onion.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease a muffin pan and set aside. (Alternately, use paper liner inserts or a silicone muffin pan and do not grease.)
  3. In a large bowl, combine the whisked eggs, ham, spinach, onion, coconut milk, and baking powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the mixture into 8 cups of the muffin pan to make 8 mini quiches.
  4. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 15 minutes until the eggs are firm and cooked through. Remove the muffin pan from the oven and let cool slightly.
  5. Divide the mini quiches between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Lemon Chicken and Asparagus Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 20 spears of asparagus (320 g), chopped
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the asparagus and dice the chicken breasts.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the asparagus to the skillet and stir-fry until slightly tender, about 4 to 6 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken to the skillet and stir-fry until cooked through, about 6 to 8 minutes.
  4. Add the lemon juice to the skillet and stir-fry for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the stir-fry between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Pork Chops with Sauteed Spinach
ingredients:
For the pork chops -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook the pork chops with
  • 2 pork chops (320 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the sauteed spinach -

  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 6 cups of spinach (180 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the sauteed spinach, thinly slice the onion.
  2. Generously season the pork chops with salt and pepper.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over high heat. Using tongs, place the pork chops on their sides with the fat in direct contact with the skillet. Render until the fat is brown and crispy.
  4. Reduce the heat to medium-high and place the pork chops flat in the skillet. Cook the pork chops for 3 minutes. Turn over and cook for an additional 3 to 5 minutes with an internal temperature of 145 F (63 C) for medium-rare. Remove the pork chops from the skillet and let rest for 5 minutes.
  5. Meanwhile, add the olive oil to a medium-sized skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until soft and slightly browned, about 4 to 6 minutes.
  6. Add the spinach and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Serve the pork chops with the sauteed spinach.

name: Keto Ham and Fried Egg Salad
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 4 slices of ham (112 g), diced
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the romaine lettuce, dice the ham and thinly slice the cucumber.
  2. In a medium skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium heat. Add each egg to the skillet and fry to your liking. Cook for about 4 minutes for a runny yolk, 5 minutes for a medium yolk, and 6 minutes for a hard yolk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. In a large bowl, toss the romaine lettuce leaves, ham, and cucumber with the olive oil and lemon juice.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top each salad with 2 fried eggs.

name: Keto Hamburger Steak and Onions
ingredients:
• 1.5 lbs of ground beef (675 g)
  • 1 medium egg (49 g), whisked
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of onion powder (7 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Whisk the egg and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a bowl, combine the ground beef, whisked egg, garlic powder, and onion powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Form the mixture into 12 thin patties.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. In batches, add the patties to the skillet and cook until desired doneness, about 2 to 3 minutes per side for medium.
  4. In the same skillet, add the onion and saute until golden brown, about 4 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Serve the hamburger steaks with the sauteed onion.

name: Keto Creamy Cauliflower Leek Soup with Bacon and Avocado
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 slices of bacon (56 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 leek (45 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.5 cup of chicken broth (120 ml)
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, break the cauliflower into small florets, thinly slice the leek and slice the avocado.
  2. In a large pan, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the bacon to the pan and cook until crispy, about 4 to 6 minutes. Remove the bacon from the pan with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. Add the cauliflower and leek to the same pan over medium-high heat. Cover and cook until the vegetables are soft, about 7 to 8 minutes.
  4. If using an immersion blender, add the chicken broth and coconut cream to the pan and blend until smooth. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. If using a food processor or blender, combine the vegetables, chicken broth, and coconut cream until smooth. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and top with equal amounts of sliced avocado and diced bacon.

name: Keto Tuscan Chicken Spaghetti
ingredients:
• 1 medium egg (49 g), whisked
  • 2 teaspoons of garlic powder (7 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of Italian seasoning (2 g)
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cup of fresh basil leaves (16 g), chopped
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of lemon juice (5 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Whisk the egg, dice the chicken breasts, chop the tomatoes and fresh basil leaves and spiralize the zucchini or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands.
  2. In a medium bowl, combine the whisked egg, garlic powder, and Italian seasoning. Add the chicken to the bowl and combine until the chicken is completely covered with the egg mixture.
  3. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 6 to 8 minutes.
  4. Add the tomatoes and fresh basil to the skillet and saute until the tomatoes are soft, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Meanwhile, in a separate bowl, toss the zucchini “spaghetti” with the olive oil and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
  6. Divide the “spaghetti” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the

name: Keto Egg Salad Stuffed Avocados
ingredients:
• 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of mustard (5 ml)
  • 2 large avocados (400 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the cucumber and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove from heat and put the lid on the pot. Let sit for 12 minutes and then drain the eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and chop the eggs.
  3. In a medium bowl, combine the chopped eggs, cucumber, and fresh parsley with the mayo and mustard. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Cut the avocados in half and remove the pits. Divide the egg salad into 4 portions and load each portion onto the avocado halves.

name: Keto Blueberry Muffins
ingredients:
• 0.25 cup of ghee (60 ml), melted (plus additional to grease the muffin pan)
  • 1.5 cups of almond flour (180 g)
  • 2 eggs (98 g), whisked
  • 1 Tablespoon of vanilla extract (15 ml)
  • Stevia, to taste
  • 0.5 teaspoon baking soda (2 g)
  • Dash of salt
  • 24 blueberries (12 g or 0.5 cup)
directions:
1. Melt the ghee and whisk the eggs.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Line a 6-cup muffin pan with muffin liners or grease the muffin pan with ghee and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, completely combine the ghee, almond flour, whisked eggs, vanilla extract, stevia, baking soda, and salt.
  4. Poke a sharp knife or toothpick into the blueberries and burst the skin. Stir in 12 of the blueberries into the batter. Set aside the remaining 12 blueberries.
  5. Spoon the batter into the prepared muffin pan, filling each cup about 3/4 full. Place 2 blueberries at the top of each muffin and push halfway into the batter.
  6. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 18 to 20 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean when you insert it into a muffin.
  7. Let the muffins cool slightly before removing them from the muffin pan.

name: Keto Bacon and Spinach Egg Muffins
ingredients:
• 8 slices of bacon (224 g), diced
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g), whisked
  • 1 cup of spinach (30 g), chopped small
  • 2 green onions (10 g), chopped small
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, whisk the eggs and chop the spinach and green onions into small pieces.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease an 8-cup muffin pan and set aside.
  3. In a nonstick skillet, cook the bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside to cool slightly.
  4. In a medium bowl, combine the cooked bacon, whisked eggs, spinach, green onions, and coconut cream. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the mixture into the prepared muffin pan until each cup is 2/3 full.
  5. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until cooked through and the eggs are set.

name: Keto Hard Boiled Egg and Bacon Salad
ingredients:
• 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of vinegar (15 ml) (of choice)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon. Chop the romaine lettuce and tomatoes.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove the pot from heat. Place a lid on the pot and let sit for 12 minutes. Drain the eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and chop the eggs.
  3. Meanwhile, in a nonstick skillet, cook the bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside to cool slightly.
  4. In a large bowl, toss the romaine lettuce leaves, tomatoes, chopped eggs, and bacon with the olive oil and vinegar. Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Mu Shu-Style Pork
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g), sliced into 1-inch (2.5 cm) strips
  • 0.5 head of napa/Chinese cabbage (400 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 white button mushrooms (40 g), sliced
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of vinegar (5 ml) (of choice)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the pork tenderloin into 1-inch (2.5 cm) strips. Thinly slice the cabbage, slice the mushrooms and mince or finely dice the fresh ginger.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the pork to the skillet and saute until slightly browned, about 1 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the cabbage, mushrooms, fresh ginger, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, and vinegar to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 7 to 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Basil Chicken and Bell Pepper Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 1 chili pepper (14 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 1 lb of ground chicken (450 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 cup of fresh basil leaves (16 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell pepper. Finely dice the optional chili pepper (seeds are removed). Mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger and chop the fresh basil leaves.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and optional chili pepper to the skillet and saute until soft, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the ground chicken, garlic, and fresh ginger to the skillet and saute until the chicken is cooked through and no longer pink, about 6 to 8 minutes.
  4. Add the fresh basil and tamari sauce or coconut aminos to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the saute between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Salmon with Sauteed Ginger Cabbage
ingredients:
For the salmon -

  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook the salmon with
  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the sauteed cabbage -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook the cabbage with
  • 0.5 head of napa/Chinese cabbage (400 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 carrot (50 g), grated or thinly sliced
  • 4 green onions (20 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the salmon, defrost the filets if frozen. For the sauteed cabbage, thinly slice the cabbage, grate or thinly slice the carrot, chop the green onions and mince or finely dice the fresh ginger.
  2. Lightly season the salmon with salt and pepper.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over high heat. Place the salmon, skin side down, in the hot ghee and cook for 5 minutes. Carefully turn over the salmon and continue to cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Set aside to rest for 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Meanwhile, in a separate large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the cabbage, carrot, green onions, and fresh ginger to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 7 to 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Serve the salmon with the sauteed cabbage.

name: Keto Caesar Salad with Bacon
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 6 slices of bacon (168 g), diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 carrot (50 g), grated

For the Caesar dressing -

  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of mustard (5 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of garlic powder (3 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, chop the romaine lettuce, thinly slice the onion and grate the carrot.
  2. In a small bowl, whisk to combine the mayo, lemon juice, mustard, and garlic powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Refrigerate until ready to use.
  3. In a medium skillet, cook the bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 5 to 6 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside to cool slightly.
  4. In a large bowl, toss the salad dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves. Add the onion and carrot to the bowl.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the diced bacon.

name: Keto Chicken Cottage Pie
ingredients:
• 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), melted
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 1.5 lbs of ground chicken (675 g)
  • 2 carrots (100 g), grated
  • 2 Tablespoons of Italian seasoning (6 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the cauliflower into small florets, melt the ghee, thinly slice the onion, grate the carrots and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease a 9-inch (23 cm) square baking dish and set aside.
  3. Boil or steam the cauliflower until fork-tender, about 5 to 10 minutes (depending on the size of the florets). Drain well.
  4. Using a food processor or blender, combine the cauliflower with the ghee until smooth. Season with salt, to taste. Set aside.
  5. Meanwhile, add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until translucent, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  6. Add the ground chicken and carrots to the skillet and saute until the ground chicken is browned, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  7. Add the Italian seasoning and fresh parsley to the skillet and continue to saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  8. Place the chicken mixture in the bottom of the prepared baking dish. Place the reserved cauliflower mash on top of the chicken mixture.
  9. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until cooked through.

name: Keto Ground Beef and Bell Pepper Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.5 lb of ground beef (225 g)
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell pepper, thinly slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef and garlic to the skillet and saute until the ground beef is cooked to your liking, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the saute.

name: Keto Curried Chicken Salad Wraps
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), diced
  • 2 stalks of celery (40 g), diced
  • 4 green onions (20 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of curry powder (7 g) (optional)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), separated into individual leaves
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breasts, bell pepper and celery stalks. Chop the green onions and fresh cilantro. Separate the romaine lettuce into individual leaves.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 7 to 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. In a large bowl, combine the cooked chicken with the mayo, bell pepper, celery, green onions, garlic powder, optional curry powder, and fresh cilantro. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Place the desired amount of chicken salad in the lettuce leaves and serve.

name: Keto Asian Miso Soup Topped with Shrimp
ingredients:
• 2 (3 oz or 85 g) packs of shirataki noodles, drained
  • 2.5 cups of chicken broth or bone broth (600 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of tahini sauce (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (15 ml)
  • 0.5 lb of shrimp (225 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • 2 Tablespoons of lemon juice (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of sesame oil (5 ml)
  • 1 cup of spinach (30 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 green onions (10 g), sliced at an angle
  • Dash of hot sauce (optional)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain the shirataki noodles. Peel and devein the shrimp, defrosted if frozen. Thinly slice the spinach and slice the green onions at an angle.
  2. Rinse or boil the shirataki noodles according to the packet instructions to eliminate the smell. Drain well and set aside.
  3. Add the broth, tahini sauce, and tamari sauce or coconut aminos to a saucepan over medium-high heat.
  4. Once the broth is steaming hot, add the shrimp, lemon juice, and sesame oil to the saucepan and heat until the shrimp are cooked through and opaque, about 2 to 5 minutes.
  5. Add the drained noodles, spinach, and green onions to the saucepan and continue to cook until the noodles are heated through and the spinach is wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and serve immediately with a dash of the optional hot sauce.

name: Keto Easy Chicken Meatball Soup
ingredients:
• 8 cups of chicken broth (1920 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of fresh cilantro (4 g), chopped
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1.5 lbs of ground chicken (675 g)
  • 4 medium eggs, whisked
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 cup of fresh parsley (16 g), chopped
  • 4 teaspoons of salt (20 g) (or to taste)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of pepper (1 g) (or to taste)
directions:
1. Chop the fresh cilantro, mince or finely dice the fresh ginger and garlic and whisk the eggs.
  2. Add the chicken broth, fresh cilantro, and fresh ginger to a large pot and simmer over low heat.
  3. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the ground chicken, whisked eggs, garlic, fresh parsley, salt, and pepper. Form the chicken mixture into about 40 to 50 small meatballs.
  4. Place the meatballs in the pot and increase the temperature to medium-high. Bring the broth to a boil and continue to boil until the meatballs are cooked through with an internal temperature of 165°F (74°C), about 10 to 15 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, if desired.

name: Keto Cod with Garlic Butter Sauce and Bacon Spinach Saute
ingredients:
For the cod with garlic “butter” sauce -

  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml)
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 filets of cod, fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • Salt, to taste

For the bacon spinach saute -

  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 8 cups of spinach (240 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the cod with garlic “butter” sauce, mince or finely dice the garlic and defrost the cod filets, if frozen. For the bacon spinach saute, dice the bacon.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the garlic to the skillet and saute until fragrant, about 30 seconds.
  3. Add the cod filets to the skillet and saute for 5 minutes. Carefully turn over each filet and cook for about 4 to 5 minutes until cooked through and the cod flakes easily. Season with salt, to taste. Set aside to rest for 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Meanwhile, in a separate large skillet, saute the bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  5. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Place each cod filet on a plate and drizzle with equal amounts of the garlic “butter” sauce. Serve the cod with the spinach saute.

name: Keto Simple Salad with Cucumber and Avocado
ingredients:
• 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), sliced
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of vinegar (15 ml) (of choice)
  • 2 large avocados (400 g), sliced
directions:
1. Chop the romaine lettuce. Slice the cucumber and avocados.
  2. In a large bowl, toss the romaine lettuce leaves and cucumber with the olive oil and vinegar.
  3. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of sliced avocado.

name: Keto Beef and Eggplant Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium eggplant (500 g), cubed
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 teaspoons of fresh ginger (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the eggplant into cubes. Mince and finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the eggplant to the skillet and stir-fry until soft and slightly browned, about 10 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef to the skillet and stir-fry until browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos, garlic, and fresh ginger to the skillet and stir-fry for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the stir-fry between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Chicken Shawarma with Rice
ingredients:
For the chicken shawarma -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 chicken breasts (800 g), diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of garlic powder (20 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of onion powder (14 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of cumin powder (4 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of paprika (4 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of Italian seasoning (2 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the “rice” -

  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), to cook with
  • 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the chicken shawarma, dice the chicken breasts. For the “rice”, process the cauliflower into rice-like pieces.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  3. Add the garlic powder, onion powder, cumin powder, paprika, and Italian seasoning to the skillet and saute until the chicken is completely coated with the spices, about 1 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Meanwhile, melt the ghee in a separate large skillet over high heat. Add the cauliflower to the skillet and saute until soft, about 8 to 10 minutes. Season with salt, to taste.
  5. Serve the chicken shawarma with the “rice.”

name: Keto Easy Bacon Deviled Eggs
ingredients:
• 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of paprika (1 g) (optional)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove the pot from heat. Place a lid on the pot and let sit for 12 minutes. Drain eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and chop the eggs.
  3. Meanwhile, in a nonstick skillet, cook the bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside to cool slightly.
  4. In a large bowl, toss the spinach with the olive oil. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and set aside.
  5. In the same bowl, combine the chopped eggs and bacon with the mayo, mustard, and optional paprika. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Place equal amounts of the deviled egg mixture on the spinach and serve.

name: Keto Pressure Cooker Garlic Pork Shoulder with Broccoli Mash
ingredients:
For the garlic pork shoulder -

  • 2 lbs of pork shoulder (900 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced
  • 0.5 cup of chicken broth (120 ml)
  • 3 Tablespoons of apple cider vinegar (45 ml)
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of salt (15 g) (plus additional, to taste)
  • 1 teaspoon of pepper (1 g) (plus additional, to taste)
  • 0.5 cup of water (120 ml) (optional)

For the broccoli mash -

  • 1 head of broccoli (450 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 cup of coconut milk (120 ml)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the garlic pork shoulder, slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic. For the mash, break the broccoli into small florets.
  2. Generously season the pork shoulder with salt and pepper. If needed, cut the pork shoulder into several large pieces and place them in the pressure cooker.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until soft and slightly golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes. Place the onion in the pressure cooker.
  4. Add the chicken broth, apple cider vinegar, garlic, salt, and pepper to the pressure cooker. Add the optional water to the bottom of the cooker. (Not all pressure cookers require additional liquid in order to come to pressure. Please consult your owner’s manual to find out if additional liquid is needed.)
  5. Secure the lid and cook on high pressure for 40 minutes. Quick-release the pressure and carefully remove the lid. If the pork is not fork-tender, replace the lid and cook on high pressure for an additional 5 minutes or until the pork shreds easily.
  6. Meanwhile, add the broccoli to a steamer and steam for about 5 minutes or until soft to your liking. (Alternatively, bring to a boil about a 1/2-inch (1.25 cm) of water in a saucepan. Add the broccoli to the saucepan, cover, and steam for about 5 minutes or until soft to your liking.)
  7. Add the steamed broccoli and coconut milk to a high-speed blender or food processor and blend until smooth. Season with salt, to taste.
  8. Serve the garlic pork with the broccoli mash.

name: Keto Oniony Chicken Burgers with Baked Zucchini Fries
ingredients:
For the burgers -

  • 0.75 lb of ground chicken (338 g)
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), grated or thinly sliced
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of garlic powder (5 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • Mustard, for serving (optional)

For the baked zucchini fries -

  • 0.25 cup of almond flour (30 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of Italian seasoning (3 g)
  • 1 medium egg (49 g)
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), seeds removed and cut into fry-size wedges
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the burgers, grate or thinly slice the onion. For the fries, cut the zucchini into fry-size wedges (seeds are removed).
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.
  3. In a small bowl, combine the almond flour and Italian seasoning. In a separate small bowl, whisk the egg.
  4. Dip each zucchini “fry” into the whisked egg and then into the almond flour mixture. Place zucchini fries in a single layer on a parchment paper-lined rimmed baking sheet.
  5. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 30 minutes, turning once during the cooking time, until crispy and golden on the outside. Season with salt, to taste.
  6. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the ground chicken, onion, and garlic powder. Form the chicken mixture into 4 burger patties.
  7. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. In batches, add the burgers to the skillet. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes per side for medium or 4 to 5 minutes per side for well done. Let the burgers rest for 2 to 3 minutes before serving.
  8. Divide the spinach between 2 plates. Place 2 burgers on each plate and top with the optional mustard, if desired. Serve the burgers with the “fries.”

name: Keto Lemony Tuna Salad
ingredients:
• 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), diced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 3 Tablespoons of mayo (45 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of lemon juice (10 ml) (or to taste)
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna, dice the cucumber and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a medium bowl, combine the tuna, cucumber, and onion with the mayo and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of tuna salad.

name: Keto Steak and Eggs
ingredients:
• 2 beef steaks (400 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml)
  • 2 medium eggs (98 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Generously season the steaks with salt.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over high heat. Add the steaks to the skillet and sear for 3 minutes. Using tongs, turn over the steaks and sear for an additional 3 to 4 minutes for medium-rare with an internal temperature of 140 F (60 C). Set aside the steaks to rest for 5 minutes.
  3. In the same skillet over medium heat, add the eggs and fry to your liking, about 3 minutes for a runny yolk or 5 to 6 minutes for a hard cooked yolk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Place a steak on each plate and top with a fried egg.

name: Keto Scrambled Egg and Avocado Toast
ingredients:
• 2.5 Tablespoons of ghee (38 ml), melted (plus additional for the mug)
  • 3 medium eggs (147 g)
  • 1/3 cup of almond flour (40 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of baking powder (1 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Melt the ghee and slice the avocado.
  2. Grease a microwave-safe mug with ghee and set aside.
  3. In a small bowl, whisk 1 egg. With a small whisk or fork, combine the whisked egg with the almond flour, baking powder, and a dash of salt. Pour the mixture into the greased mug.
  4. Place the mug in a microwave and cook for 90 seconds on high. Remove from the microwave and let cool slightly.
  5. Once the mug is cool enough to handle, gently remove the bread and slice into 4 pieces.
  6. Toast the bread using a toaster, toaster oven, or under a broiler until toasted to your liking.
  7. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, whisk the remaining 2 eggs.
  8. In a small skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium heat. Add the whisked eggs to the skillet and scramble until cooked to your liking, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  9. To serve, place 2 slices of “toast” on each plate and top with the sliced avocado and scrambled eggs. Season with additional salt and pepper, if desired.

name: Keto Sausage Egg Bake
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.75 lb of sausages of your choice (338 g), sliced
  • 8 cups of spinach (240 g), chopped
  • 0.25 cup of fresh basil leaves (8 g), chopped
  • 8 medium eggs (392 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the bell pepper and onion. Slice the sausages of your choice. Chop the spinach and fresh basil leaves.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Lightly grease a 9-inch (23 cm) square baking dish and set aside.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft and slightly golden brown, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  4. Add the sausage to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  5. Add the spinach and fresh basil to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Pour the sausage mixture into the prepared baking dish. Make 8 indentions in the mixture and crack an egg into each indention.
  7. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 15 minutes until the egg whites are solid and the yolks are slightly runny.
  8. Remove the baking dish from the oven and let cool slightly before serving.

name: Keto Creamy Shrimp and Bacon with Cauliflower Mash
ingredients:
For the creamy shrimp and bacon -

  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 1 lb of shrimp (450 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.25 cup of coconut cream (60 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the cauliflower mash -

  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.25 cup of coconut milk (60 ml)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the creamy shrimp and bacon, dice the bacon, peel and devein the shrimp (defrosted if frozen) and mince or finely dice the garlic. For the mash, break the cauliflower into small florets.
  2. Boil or steam the cauliflower until soft, about 5 to 7 minutes. Drain well.
  3. Using a food processor or blender, combine the cauliflower with the coconut milk. Season with salt, to taste.
  4. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, saute the bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  5. Add the shrimp and garlic to the skillet and saute until the shrimp is cooked through and opaque, about 2 to 5 minutes.
  6. Add the coconut cream to the skillet and continue to cook until warmed, about 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Divide the cauliflower mash between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the creamy shrimp.

name: Keto Kale Salad with Fried Eggs
ingredients:
• 8 oz of kale (224 g), stems removed and roughly chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 cherry tomatoes (68 g), halved
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 medium eggs (196 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Roughly chop the kale, stems are removed. Thinly slice the cucumber and onion. Cut the cherry tomatoes in half.
  2. In a large bowl, combine the kale, cucumber, cherry tomatoes, and onion with the olive oil and lemon juice. Divide the salad between 2 plates and set aside.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium heat. Add the eggs to the skillet and fry to your liking, about 3 minutes for a runny yolk and 5 to 6 minutes for a hard-cooked yolk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Place 2 fried eggs on top of each salad and serve.

name: Keto Chicken Fajita Wraps
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), sliced into 1-inch (2.5 cm) strips
  • 2 teaspoons of cumin powder (4 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of paprika (2 g)
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), separated into individual leaves
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell pepper and avocado. Thinly slice the onion. Slice the chicken breasts into 1-inch (2.5 cm) strips and separate the romaine lettuce into individual leaves.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft and slightly golden brown, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 6 to 8 minutes.
  4. Add the cumin powder and paprika to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Wrap the desired amount of fajita and sliced avocado in the lettuce leaves and serve.

name: Keto Chicken and Avocado Salad with Creamy Lemon Dressing
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 cherry tomatoes (68 g), halved
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the dressing -

  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml) (or to taste)
directions:
1. For the salad, dice the chicken breast, chop the romaine lettuce, thinly slice the cucumber, cut the cherry tomatoes in half and slice the avocado.
  2. In a medium skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and saute until cooked through, about 5 to 7 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves, cooked chicken, cucumber and tomatoes.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 bowls and top with equal amounts of sliced avocado.

name: Keto Bacon-Wrapped Pork Tenderloin
ingredients:
• 0.5 Tablespoon of garlic powder (5 g)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of onion powder (4 g)
  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g)
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil and set aside.
  2. In a small bowl, combine the garlic powder and onion powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Cover the tenderloin with the garlic mixture.
  3. Wrap the bacon slices around the tenderloin, covering it completely, and secure with toothpicks, if desired.
  4. Place the tenderloin in a skillet over high heat and sear until the bacon is slightly browned, about 1 to 2 minutes per side. Remove the tenderloin from the skillet and place on the prepared baking sheet.
  5. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes with an internal temperature of 145 F (63 C) for medium rare or 160 F (71 C) for medium. Remove the tenderloin from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing.

name: Keto Skillet Chicken with Tomatoes and Peppers
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml)
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 0.5 cup of chicken broth (120 ml)
  • 8 cherry tomatoes (136 g), quartered
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of Italian seasoning (3 g)
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell pepper, thinly slice the onion, dice the chicken breasts, cut the cherry tomatoes into quarters and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until slightly soft, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken breasts to the skillet and saute until browned, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the chicken broth, tomatoes, garlic, and Italian seasoning to the skillet and reduce the heat to a simmer. Cover and continue to simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
  5. Remove the lid and increase the heat to high. Continue to cook, stirring frequently, until the liquid has evaporated, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  6. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Divide the saute between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Creamy Chicken Pasta
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast. Spiralize the zucchinis or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands. Mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 5 to 8 minutes.
  3. Add the zucchini and garlic to the skillet and saute until the zucchini is soft, about 1 to 2 minutes.
  4. Remove the skillet from the heat and add the mayo, stirring well to combine. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the creamy “pasta” between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Ground Beef and Zucchini Stew
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1.5 lbs of ground beef (675 g)
  • 3 cups of beef broth (720 ml)
  • 20 cherry tomatoes (340 g), halved
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), chopped
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g), chopped
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of Italian seasoning (6 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, cut the cherry tomatoes in half, chop the zucchinis and spinach and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large pot, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the pot and saute until translucent, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef to the pot and saute until browned, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the beef broth, tomatoes, zucchinis, spinach, garlic, and Italian seasoning to the pot and reduce the heat to a simmer. Cover and continue to simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Asian Chicken Slaw
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of sesame oil (5 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast and thinly slice the cabbage.
  2. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 5 to 8 minutes. Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.
  3. Add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to the same skillet over medium-high heat. Add the cabbage to the skillet and saute until soft, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  4. Add the cooked chicken, tamari sauce or coconut aminos and sesame oil to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the slaw between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Tuna and Kale Casserole
ingredients:
• 4 cans of tuna (680 g), drained and flaked
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 4 oz of kale (112 g), stems removed and chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 cup of coconut cream (240 ml) (from the tops of 2 refrigerated cans of coconut milk)
  • 3 Tablespoons of lemon juice (45 ml) (or to taste)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna, slice the bell pepper, thinly slice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the fresh parsley and kale (stems are removed).
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Grease an 8-inch (20 cm) square baking dish and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, combine the tuna, bell pepper, kale, and onion with the coconut cream, lemon juice, garlic, and fresh parsley. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the tuna mixture into the prepared baking dish.
  4. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 35 minutes. Remove the baking dish from the oven and let cool for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

name: Keto Fried Cabbage and Sausage
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 0.5 lb of sausages of your choice (225 g), sliced
  • 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of vinegar (15 ml) (of choice)
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.25 cup of fresh parsley (4 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the sausages of your choice. Thinly slice the cabbage and onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of ghee over medium-high heat. Add the sausage to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 4 to 5 minutes. Remove the sausage from the skillet and set aside.
  3. Add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of ghee to the same skillet over medium-high heat. Add the cabbage and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  4. Add the cooked sausage, vinegar, garlic and fresh parsley to the skillet and continue to saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the saute between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Apple Cinnamon Muffins
ingredients:
• 3 cups of almond flour (180 g)
  • 0.5 cup of ghee (120 ml), melted
  • 0.25 cup of applesauce (60 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of lemon juice (5 ml)
  • 3 medium eggs (147 g), whisked
  • 3 Tablespoons of cinnamon powder (18 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of nutmeg (2 g)
  • 0.25 teaspoon of ground cloves (1 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of baking soda (4 g)
  • Stevia, to taste
directions:
1. Melt the ghee and whisk the eggs.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Line or grease a 12-cup muffin pan and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients until smooth. Pour the mixture into the prepared muffin pan.
  4. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 18 to 20 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean when you insert it into a muffin.
  5. Remove the muffins from the oven and let cool slightly. Refrigerate the leftovers in an airtight container.

name: Keto Blueberry Almond and Kale Salad
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 8 oz of kale (224 g), stems removed and chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 5 whole almonds (20 g), chopped
  • 10 blueberries (5 g)

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the salad, chop the almonds and kale (stems removed) and thinly slice the cucumber and onion. For the dressing, chop the fresh parsley.
  2. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the kale, cucumber, onion, almonds and blueberries.
  3. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Loco Moco Burgers with Fried Eggs
ingredients:
• 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of garlic powder (7 g)
  • 2 teaspoons of onion powder (5 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 5 white button mushrooms (50 g), sliced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 cup of beef broth (120 ml)
  • 2 medium eggs (98 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, slice the mushrooms and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a medium bowl, combine the ground beef, garlic powder, and onion powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Form the beef mixture into 4 burger patties.
  3. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. In batches, add the burgers to the skillet. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes per side for medium and 4 to 5 minutes per side for well done. Remove the burgers from the skillet and set aside.
  4. In the same skillet, add the onion and saute until translucent, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  5. Add the mushrooms and minced garlic to the skillet and saute until the onion and mushrooms are golden brown, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  6. Add the broth to the skillet and reduce the heat to a simmer. Continue to simmer, stirring occasionally, until the broth is reduced to make a gravy. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. (If desired, place the burgers in the gravy over low heat and warm the burgers for 1 to 2 minutes.)
  7. Meanwhile, in a separate skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) coconut oil over medium heat. Add the eggs to the skillet and fry to your liking, about 3 minutes for a runny yolk and 5 to 6 minutes for a hard cooked yolk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove from the skillet and set aside.
  8. Serve the burgers with the gravy and top each with the fried eggs.

name: Keto Bacon and Veggie Frittata
ingredients:
• 6 slices of bacon (168 g), diced
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), diced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 10 medium eggs (490), whisked
  • 0.25 cup of coconut cream (60 ml) (from the top of a can of refrigerated coconut milk)
  • 1 cup of spinach (30 g), chopped
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon and bell pepper. Thinly slice the onion and whisk the eggs. Chop the spinach and fresh parsley and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Grease an 8-inch (20 cm) square baking dish and set aside.
  3. Add the bacon to a large nonstick skillet and saute over medium heat until slightly crispy and the fat is rendered, about 4 to 5 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  4. Add the bell pepper and onion to the same skillet over medium-high heat and saute until the vegetables are slightly soft, about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Set aside to cool slightly.
  5. In a large bowl, combine the cooked bacon and cooled vegetables with the eggs, coconut cream, spinach, garlic, and fresh parsley. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the egg mixture into the prepared baking dish.
  6. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the eggs are cooked through and firm.

name: Keto Sheet Pan Chicken and Veg
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided
  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), broken into small florets
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), cut into 1-inch (2.5 cm) cubes
  • 2 teaspoons of garlic powder (7 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the broccoli into small florets. Slice the bell pepper, thinly slice the onion and cut the chicken breasts into 1-inch (2.5 cm) cubes.
  2. Preheat the oven to 425 F (220 C).
  3. In a large bowl, toss 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil with the broccoli, bell pepper, and onion. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the vegetables in a single layer onto a rimmed baking tray.
  4. In the same bowl, toss the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil with the chicken and garlic powder. Pour the chicken in a single layer onto the same baking tray.
  5. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 16 to 18 minutes, stirring once during the cooking time, until the chicken is cooked through and the vegetables are tender.

name: Keto Italian Tuna Salad
ingredients:
• 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), diced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 cup of olive oil (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml) (or to taste)
  • 2 teaspoons of Italian seasoning (2 g)
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna, dice the cucumber and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a medium bowl, combine the tuna, cucumber, and onion with the olive oil, lemon juice, and Italian seasoning. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of tuna salad.

name: Keto Slow Cooker Brisket Chili
ingredients:
• 2 lbs of beef brisket (900 g), deboned
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 1 chili pepper (14 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of cumin powder (12 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of chili powder (6 g) (or to taste)
  • 3 cups of beef broth (720 ml)
  • 1 can of diced tomatoes (400 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Debone the beef brisket. Slice the bell pepper and mushrooms. Thinly slice the onion. Finely dice the optional chili pepper (seeds removed) and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Cut the brisket into 1-inch (2.5 cm) cubes.
  3. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the brisket to the skillet and brown on all sides, about 2 to 3 minutes per side. Remove the brisket from the skillet and place it in the slow cooker.
  4. Add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to the same skillet over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper, onion, mushrooms, optional chili pepper, and garlic to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are slightly soft, about 5 minutes.
  5. Add the cumin and chili powder to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Place the vegetable mixture in the slow cooker.
  6. Add the beef broth and diced tomatoes to the slow cooker, stirring well to combine.
  7. Cover and cook the brisket chili on low for 6 hours. Remove the lid and shred the brisket into bite-size pieces. Cover and continue to cook on low heat for an additional 1 hour or until the brisket is cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Stovetop Brisket Chili
ingredients:
• 2 lbs of beef brisket (900 g), deboned
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 1 chili pepper (14 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of cumin powder (12 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of chili powder (6 g) (or to taste)
  • 3 cups of beef broth (720 ml)
  • 1 can of diced tomatoes (400 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Debone the beef brisket. Slice the bell pepper and mushrooms. Thinly slice the onion. Finely dice the optional chili pepper (seeds removed) and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Cut the brisket into 1-inch (2.5 cm) cubes.
  3. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a heavy-bottomed pot or Dutch oven over medium-high heat. In batches, add the brisket to the pot and brown on all sides, about 5 to 7 minutes per batch. Remove the brisket from the pot and set aside.
  4. Add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to the same pot over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper, onion, mushrooms, optional chili pepper, and garlic to the pot and saute until the vegetables are slightly soft, about 5 minutes.
  5. Add the cumin and chili powder to the pot and saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes.
  6. Reduce the heat to a simmer and add the seared brisket, beef broth, and diced tomatoes to the pot. Cover and continue to simmer, stirring occasionally, for 2.5 to 3.5 hours until the brisket is cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Pressure Cooker Brisket Chili
ingredients:
• 2 lbs of beef brisket (900 g), deboned
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 1 chili pepper (14 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of cumin powder (12 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of chili powder (6 g) (or to taste)
  • 3 cups of beef broth (720 ml)
  • 1 can of diced tomatoes (400 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Debone the beef brisket. Slice the bell pepper and mushrooms. Thinly slice the onion. Finely dice the optional chili pepper (seeds removed) and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Cut the brisket into 1-inch (2.5 cm) cubes.
  3. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the brisket to the skillet and brown on all sides, about 2 to 3 minutes per side. Remove the brisket from the skillet and place in the pressure cooker.
  4. Add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to the same skillet over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper, onion, mushrooms, optional chili pepper, and garlic to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are slightly soft, about 5 minutes.
  5. Add the cumin and chili powder to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Place the vegetable mixture in the pressure cooker.
  6. Add the beef broth and diced tomatoes to the pressure cooker, stirring well to combine.
  7. Secure the lid and cook on high pressure for 35 minutes. Quick release the steam and carefully remove the lid. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Bacon and Egg Spinach Salad
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 4 medium eggs
  • 6 cups of spinach (180 g)
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon and thinly slice the cucumber and onion.
  2. Add the bacon to a large nonstick skillet and saute over medium heat until crispy, about 4 to 5 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. Add the eggs to the same skillet and fry in the bacon fat until cooked to your liking, about 3 minutes for a runny yolk and 5 to 6 minutes for a hard-cooked yolk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the spinach, cooked bacon, cucumber and onion.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top each salad with 2 fried eggs.

name: Keto Spicy Pork and Avocado Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g), sliced into 1-inch (2.5 cm) strips
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of onion powder (4 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of chili powder (2 g) (or to taste)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of mustard (5 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell pepper, pork tenderloin [into 1-inch (2.5 cm) strips] and avocado.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper to the skillet and saute until slightly soft, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  3. Add the pork to the skillet and saute until cooked to your liking, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the garlic powder, onion powder, and chili powder and saute for 1 minute.
  5. Remove the skillet from the heat and toss the saute with the sliced avocado, olive oil, and mustard. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Basil Beef Saute with "Rice"
ingredients:
For the saute -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 cup of fresh basil leaves (16 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the “rice” -

  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook cauliflower with
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the saute, slice the bell pepper, thinly slice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger and chop the fresh basil leaves. For the “rice”, process the cauliflower into rice-like pieces.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft and slightly browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef, garlic, and fresh ginger to the skillet and saute until the ground beef is cooked to your liking, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the fresh basil and tamari sauce or coconut aminos to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Meanwhile, in a separate large skillet, melt the ghee over high heat. Add the cauliflower to the skillet and saute until soft, about 8 to 10 minutes. Season with salt, to taste.
  6. Divide the “rice” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the saute.

name: Keto Creamy Broccoli Soup
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), broken into small florets
  • 1 cup of chicken broth (240 ml)
  • 1 cup of coconut milk (240 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and break the broccoli into small florets.
  2. In a saucepan, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the onion and garlic to the saucepan and saute until the onion is soft and slightly brown, about 5 minutes.
  3. Reduce the heat to a simmer and add the broccoli and chicken broth to the saucepan. Continue to simmer until the broccoli is tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  4. Add the coconut milk to the saucepan and simmer for an additional 1 minute.
  5. Use an immersion blender to puree the soup until smooth. (Alternatively, let the soup cool slightly and puree using a food processor or high-speed blender.) Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Crunchy Chicken and Avocado Salad
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 5 whole almonds (20 g), chopped
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt, to taste

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast, thinly slice the cucumber, chop the almonds and slice the avocado.
  2. In a medium skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and saute until cooked through, about 5 minutes. Season with salt, to taste.
  3. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the spinach, cooked chicken, cucumber and almonds.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of sliced avocado.

name: Keto Easy Coconut Shrimp Curry
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1.5 Tablespoons of curry powder (11 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of garlic powder (3 g)
  • 2 cups of chicken broth (480 ml)
  • 1 lb of shrimp (450 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell pepper, thinly slice the onion, peel and devein the shrimp (defrosted if frozen) and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. In a large pan, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the pan and saute until the vegetables are soft and slightly browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Add the curry powder and garlic powder to the pan and saute until the spices are fragrant, about 1 minute.
  4. Increase the heat to a boil and add the chicken broth and shrimp to the pan. Continue to boil until the shrimp is cooked through and opaque, about 1 to 3 minutes.
  5. Remove the pan from the heat and add the coconut cream and fresh cilantro. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Chopped Salad with Balsamic Vinaigrette
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 2 medium eggs
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), chopped
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of balsamic vinegar (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of mustard (5 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, chop the romaine lettuce, cucumber and tomato and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove the pot from heat. Place a lid on the pot and let sit for 12 minutes. Drain eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and chop the eggs.
  3. Meanwhile, in a medium skillet, cook the bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 5 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  4. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves, chopped eggs, cooked bacon, cucumber, tomato and onion.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Easy Meatloaf with Cauli-Mash
ingredients:
For the meatloaf -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 20 white button mushrooms (200 g), chopped small
  • 1 lb of ground beef (450 g)
  • 2 medium eggs (98 g), whisked
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of onion powder (7 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of Italian seasoning (3 g)
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), cut in half
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the cauli-mash -

  • 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 cup of coconut milk (120 ml)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the meatloaf, chop the mushrooms into small pieces, whisk the eggs, and cut the bacon in half. For the mash, break the cauliflower into small florets.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C).
  3. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium heat. Add the mushrooms to the skillet and saute until caramelized and the liquid has evaporated, about 10 minutes. Remove the mushrooms from the skillet and place them on a paper towel-lined plate to cool.
  4. In a large bowl, combine the ground beef with the cooled mushrooms, whisked eggs, garlic powder, onion powder, and Italian seasoning. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Place the beef mixture in a loaf pan and cover the top of the mixture with the bacon.
  5. Place the pan in the oven and bake for 50 minutes until the meatloaf is cooked through with an internal temperature of 160°F (70°C). Remove the meatloaf from the oven and let cool for 10 minutes before slicing.
  6. Meanwhile, boil or steam the cauliflower until soft, about 5 to 7 minutes. Drain well.
  7. Using a food processor or blender, combine the cauliflower with the coconut milk. Season with salt, to taste.
  8. Serve the meatloaf with the mash.

name: Keto Beef and Onion Egg Muffins
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml)
  • 0.5 lb of ground beef (225 g)
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g), chopped
  • 8 medium eggs, whisked
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of 1 refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, chop the spinach and whisk the eggs.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease an 8-cup muffin pan and set aside.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef and onion to the skillet and saute until the ground beef is browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove the skillet from the heat and let cool.
  5. In a large bowl, combine the whisked eggs and coconut cream with the cooled beef mixture. Season with additional salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the mixture into the prepared muffin pan, filling each muffin cup about 2/3 full.
  6. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until the eggs are set.

name: Keto "Spaghetti" with Creamy Bacon Mushroom Sauce
ingredients:
• 6 slices of bacon (168 g), diced
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 0.25 cup of chicken broth (60 ml)
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, slice the mushrooms, mince or finely dice the garlic and spiralize the zucchinis or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands.
  2. In a large nonstick skillet, saute the bacon over medium heat until slightly crispy, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the mushrooms and garlic to the skillet and saute until the mushrooms are softened and browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  4. Reduce the heat to a simmer and add the coconut cream and chicken broth to the skillet. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes until the sauce starts to thicken, stirring frequently. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the zucchini “spaghetti” between 2 plates and top with the creamy sauce.

name: Keto Ground Turkey and Bacon Vegetable Skillet
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.75 lb of ground turkey (338 g)
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 6 spears of asparagus (96 g), chopped into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh thyme (3 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon and chop the asparagus into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces. Thinly slice the onion and chop the fresh thyme.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the ground turkey and bacon to the skillet and saute until the ground turkey is browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Add the asparagus and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft and the turkey is cooked through, about 10 minutes.
  4. Add the spinach and fresh thyme to the skillet and saute until the spinach is wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto BLT Salad with Creamy Lemon Dressing
ingredients:
For the salad

  • 6 slices of bacon (168 g), diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), sliced
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced

For the dressing -

  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of mayo (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, chop the romaine lettuce, slice the tomatoes and thinly slice the cucumber and onion.
  2. In a medium skillet, cook the bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the olive oil, mayo, and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves. Add the tomatoes, cucumber, and onion to the bowl.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of cooked bacon.

name: Keto Turkey and Avocado Salad
ingredients:
For the salad

  • 6 cups of spinach (180 g)
  • 0.25 lb of sliced turkey breast (113 g)
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
directions:
1. Thinly slice the cucumber and onion. Slice the tomato and avocado.
  2. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the spinach, sliced turkey, cucumber, tomato and onion.
  3. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of sliced avocado.

name: Keto Garlic "Butter" Salmon with Lemon Asparagus Saute
ingredients:
For the salmon -

  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), divided
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt, to taste

For the asparagus saute -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 20 spears of asparagus (320 g), chopped into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the salmon, defrost the salmon filets if frozen and mince or finely dice the garlic. For the saute, chop the asparagus into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces and thinly slice the onion.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C).
  3. Lightly season each salmon filet with salt. Place each salmon filet on a piece of parchment paper or aluminum foil to create a packet.
  4. Cover each salmon filet with 0.5 Tablespoon (7.5 ml) of ghee and equal amounts of garlic. Fold the sides and top of the parchment paper or aluminum foil to ensure the ghee remains inside each packet. Place the packets on a rimmed baking sheet.
  5. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the salmon flakes easily. Let rest for 2 to 3 minutes before serving.
  6. Meanwhile, add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium heat. Add the asparagus and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  7. Add the lemon juice to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  8. Divide the saute between 2 plates and top each plate with a salmon filet and garlic “butter” sauce.

name: Keto Chicken Kiev with Garlic Spinach Saute
ingredients:
For the chicken kiev -

  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g)
  • 4 Tablespoons of ghee (60 ml), divided (do not melt)
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 medium egg, whisked
  • 0.25 cup of coconut flour (28 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of garlic powder (20 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of salt (5 g)

For the garlic spinach -

  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml), to cook the spinach with
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the chicken kiev, mince or finely dice the garlic and whisk the egg. For the garlic spinach, mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Preheat the oven to 425 F (220 C). Line a rimmed baking tray with parchment paper and set aside.
  3. Using a small knife, cut a slit into 1 side of each chicken breast, but not cutting to the other side, to form a pocket. (Alternatively, pound the chicken breasts into thin layers.)
  4. Place equal amounts of ghee and garlic into each chicken breast. (Alternatively, place an equal amount of ghee and garlic on top of each pounded chicken breast and roll.) Secure the chicken breasts with toothpicks.
  5. Add the whisked egg to a small bowl. In a separate bowl, combine the coconut flour, garlic powder, and salt to make the “breading.”
