  6. Place each chicken breast in the whisked egg. Then, place each chicken breast into the “breading” and cover completely. Place each “breaded” chicken breast on the prepared baking tray.
  7. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 35 minutes until the internal temperature of the chicken reaches 165 F (75 C). Remove from the oven and let rest for 2 to 3 minutes before serving. Remove the toothpicks and discard.
  8. Meanwhile, add the olive oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the garlic to the skillet and saute until fragrant, about 30 seconds.
  9. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  10. Place a chicken breast on each plate and serve with equal amounts of sauteed spinach.

name: Keto Chicken and Broccoli Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the broccoli into small florets, thinly slice the onion, dice the chicken breasts and mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the broccoli and onion to the skillet and stir-fry until the vegetables are soft, about 7 to 9 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken to the skillet and stir-fry until cooked through, about 8 to 10 minutes.
  4. Add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos, garlic, and fresh ginger to the skillet and stir-fry for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Avocado and Tomato Salad
ingredients:
• 2 large avocados (400 g), sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (4 g), chopped
  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of balsamic vinegar (5 ml) (or to taste)
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the avocados, chop the tomato and fresh basil leaves and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a medium bowl, combine the avocados, tomato, onion, and fresh basil with the olive oil and balsamic vinegar. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of salad.

name: Keto Garlic Beef and Veg Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 10 spears of asparagus (160 g), chopped into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 5 white button mushrooms (50 g), sliced
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the asparagus into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces. Thinly slice the onion, slice the mushrooms, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the zucchinis.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the asparagus, onion, and mushrooms to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 7 to 10 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef and garlic to the skillet and saute until browned, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the zucchinis to the skillet and saute until soft and the ground beef is cooked to your liking, about 2 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Sauteed Veggie Bowl with Bacon and Fried Eggs
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), broken into small florets
  • 4 spears of asparagus (64 g), chopped into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 medium eggs
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, break the broccoli into small florets, chop the asparagus into 1-inch (2.5 cm) pieces and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bacon to the skillet and saute until crispy, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the broccoli, asparagus, and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 7 to 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Meanwhile, in a separate large skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium heat. Add the eggs to the skillet and fry to your liking, about 3 minutes for a runny yolk and 5 to 6 minutes for a hard-cooked yolk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the vegetables between 2 plates and top each plate with 1 fried egg.

name: Keto Chicken Spinach Salad with Caesar Dressing
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the Caesar dressing -

  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of mustard (5 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of garlic powder (3 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast, thinly slice the cucumber and chop the tomato.
  2. In a medium skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 5 to 7 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Set aside to cool slightly.
  3. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the spinach, cooked chicken, cucumber and tomato.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Creamy Basil Chicken "Pasta"
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 0.25 cup of coconut cream (60 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 4 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (8 g), chopped
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breasts, chop the tomatoes and fresh basil leaves, mince or finely dice the garlic and spiralize the zucchini or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Add the tomatoes to the skillet and saute until soft, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the coconut cream, fresh basil, and garlic to the skillet and cook until the sauce starts to thicken and the chicken is cooked through, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the zucchini “noodles” between 2 plates and top with the creamy basil chicken.

name: Keto Fried Egg and Bacon Salad
ingredients:
For the salad-

  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 2 medium eggs
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, chop the romaine lettuce and tomato and thinly slice the cucumber and onion.
  2. Place the bacon in a medium skillet over medium heat and saute until crispy, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. Add the eggs to the same skillet and fry in the bacon fat until cooked to your liking, about 3 minutes for a runny yolk and 5 to 6 minutes for a hard-cooked yolk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the olive oil and lemon juice. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves, cooked bacon, cucumber, tomato and onion.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top each salad with 1 fried egg.

name: Keto Zucchini "Spaghetti" and Zesty Meatballs
ingredients:
For the meatballs -

  • 1 lb of ground pork (450 g)
  • 1 medium egg, whisked
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of garlic powder (5 g)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of onion powder (4 g)
  • 1.5 teaspoons of Italian seasoning (2 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped

For the sauce -

  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 4 green onions (20 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (4 g), chopped
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the meatballs, whisk the egg and chop the fresh parsley. For the sauce, chop the tomatoes, green onions and fresh basil leaves, mince or finely dice the garlic and spiralize the zucchini or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands. 
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, combine the ground pork, whisked egg, garlic powder, onion powder, fresh parsley, and Italian seasoning. Form the mixture into medium-size meatballs. Place the meatballs on the baking sheet with about 1-inch (2.5 cm) space between the meatballs.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 15 to 18 minutes until the meatballs are cooked through with an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C).
  5. Meanwhile, add the olive oil to a large skillet over medium heat. Add the tomatoes and garlic to the skillet and saute until the tomatoes are soft, about 2 to 5 minutes.
  6. Add the green onions and fresh basil to the skillet and continue to saute for an additional 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Place the meatballs in the skillet and cover with the sauce.
  8. Divide the zucchini “spaghetti” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of meatballs and sauce.

name: Keto Mini Spinach Meatloaves
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml)
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 lb of ground beef (225 g)
  • 0.5 lb of ground pork (225 g)
  • 8 cups of spinach (240 g), chopped
  • 6 medium eggs, whisked
  • 0.5 cup of coconut milk (120 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of Italian seasoning (6 g)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of salt (8 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of pepper (1 g)
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic, chop the spinach and whisk the eggs.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Grease a 12-cup muffin pan or line with paper liners and set aside.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion and garlic to the skillet and saute until the onion is soft, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the ground beef and ground pork to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 6 to 8 minutes.
  5. Add the spinach to the skillet and saute until wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Remove the skillet from the heat and set aside to cool.
  6. In a large bowl, combine the cooked beef mixture with the whisked eggs, coconut milk, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. Pour equal amounts of the mixture into the prepared muffin pan.
  7. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 10 to 12 minutes until the eggs are cooked through.

name: Keto Creamy Coconut Chicken and Vegetables
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 2 oz of green beans (56 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 cup of chicken broth (120 ml)
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 2 Tablespoons of lime juice (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (4 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the bell pepper, chop the green beans and fresh basil leaves, thinly slice the onion, dice the chicken breasts and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large pan, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper, green beans, and onion to the pan and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 6 to 8 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken and garlic to the pan and saute until the chicken is browned, about 5 to 6 minutes.
  4. Add the chicken broth, coconut cream, lime juice, and fresh basil to the pan and reduce the heat to a simmer. Continue to simmer, stirring frequently, for 20 minutes until the sauce is reduced and the chicken is cooked through. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Pork Carnitas
ingredients:
• 2.5 lbs of pork shoulder (1125 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of olive oil (10 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of dried oregano (2 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of cumin powder (2 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of chili powder (2 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of paprika (2 g)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), sliced
  • 2.5 cups of chicken broth (600 ml)
  • 4 Tablespoons of olive oil (60 ml) (optional)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the onion and garlic.
  2. Preheat the oven to 430°F (220°C). If desired, wrap the pork shoulder with butcher’s twine.
  3. Make a paste by combining the lime juice, olive oil, dried oregano, cumin powder, chili powder, and paprika. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Rub the paste all over the pork shoulder.
  4. Place the onion and garlic in the bottom of a large roasting pan. Place the pork shoulder on top of the onions and garlic.
  5. Pour the chicken broth into the bottom of the roasting pan.
  6. Place the roasting pan in the oven for 10 minutes. Reduce the oven temperature to 320°F (160°C).
  7. Cook in the oven at 320°F (160°C) around 5 hours until the internal temperature reaches 180°F (82°C). Every hour, turn the pork over with tongs and baste with the roasting liquid from the bottom of the pan. If the liquid evaporates from the bottom of the pan, cover the pork with aluminum foil for the remainder of the cooking time.
  8. When the pork is done, remove any butcher’s twine and discard. Let rest for around 20 minutes.
  9. Shred the pork into bite-size pieces. Add in the onion, garlic, and the desired amount of remaining cooking liquid. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  10. If desired, to crisp the meat before serving, add the olive oil to a hot skillet. In batches, saute the shredded meat for 3 to 4 minutes until crisp to your liking.

name: Keto Bacon Burger Bowl with Fried Eggs
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 slices of bacon (56 g), diced
  • 0.5 lb of ground beef (225 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of dried oregano (1 g)
  • 2 medium eggs
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of mustard (10 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, dice the bacon and chop the romaine lettuce and tomatoes.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until translucent, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the bacon to the skillet and saute until slightly crispy, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the ground beef and dried oregano to the skillet and saute until the ground beef is cooked to your liking, about 3 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Meanwhile, in a medium skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium heat. Add the eggs to the skillet and fry to your liking, about 3 minutes for a runny yolk and 5 to 6 minutes for a hard cooked yolk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the romaine lettuce leaves between 2 bowls and top each bowl with equal amounts of the ground beef, fried eggs, and tomatoes.
  7. In a small bowl, combine the mayo and mustard. Drizzle equal amounts of the mayo mixture over each bowl and serve.

name: Keto Creamy Salmon Stew
ingredients:
• 3 cups of chicken broth (720 ml)
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), chopped small
  • 4 stalks of celery (80 g), chopped small
  • 6 white button mushrooms (60 g), sliced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 filets of salmon (with skin on), fresh or frozen (340 g), defrosted if frozen, chopped small
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 0.5 cup of fresh cilantro (8 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the zucchinis, celery stalks and salmon filets (defrosted if frozen) into small pieces. Slice the mushrooms, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the fresh cilantro.
  2. Add the chicken broth to a saucepan over high heat and bring to a boil. Add the zucchinis, celery, mushrooms and garlic to the saucepan and continue to boil, covered, until the vegetables are slightly soft, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the salmon to the saucepan and boil until cooked through, about 2 to 5 minutes.
  4. Reduce the heat to a simmer and add the coconut cream and fresh cilantro to the saucepan. Continue to simmer for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Slow Cooker Turmeric Chicken with Cauliflower "Rice"
ingredients:
For the chicken - 

  • 4 chicken breasts (800 g)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 cup of ghee (60 ml)
  • 10 cloves of garlic (30 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 teaspoon of salt (5 g) (plus additional, to taste)
  • 1 teaspoon of turmeric (2 g)
  • Pepper, to taste

For the cauliflower “rice” - 

  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), to cook the cauliflower with
  • 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the chicken, thinly slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic. For the rice, process the cauliflower into rice-like pieces.
  2. Place the chicken, onion, 0.25 cup (60 ml) of ghee, garlic, salt and turmeric in the slow cooker.
  3. Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or on low for 6 to 8 hours until the chicken shreds easily.
  4. Let the chicken rest for 5 minutes before using 2 forks to shred it in the slow cooker. Season with additional salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, melt 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of ghee over high heat. Add the cauliflower to the skillet and saute until soft, about 5 minutes. Season with salt, to taste.
  6. Serve the turmeric chicken with the cauliflower “rice”.

name: Keto Deviled Egg and Avocado Salad
ingredients:
• 4 medium eggs
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • 1 stalk of celery (20 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of mustard (10 ml)
  • 0.25 teaspoon of paprika (1 g) (or to taste)
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the avocado and thinly slice the celery stalks.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove the pot from heat. Place a lid on the pot and let sit for 12 minutes. Drain the eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and chop the eggs.
  3. In a large bowl, combine the chopped eggs, avocado, and celery with the mayo, mustard, and paprika. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of egg salad.

name: Keto Roasted Pork Tenderloin with Chimichurri Sauce
ingredients:
For the pork tenderloin -

  • 1 teaspoon of salt (5 g) (or to taste)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of pepper (1 g) (or to taste)
  • 1 teaspoon of garlic powder (3 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of Italian seasoning (1 g)
  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with

For the chimichurri sauce -

  • 0.5 cup of fresh parsley (8 g), chopped
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 chili pepper (7 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 4 Tablespoons of olive oil (60 ml)
  • 1.5 teaspoons of vinegar (8 ml), apple cider
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of lemon juice (8 ml)
directions:
1. For the chimichurri sauce, chop the fresh parsley, mince or finely dice the garlic and finely dice the optional chili pepper (seeds removed).
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil and set aside.
  3. In a small bowl, combine the salt, pepper, garlic powder, and Italian seasoning. Cover the tenderloin with 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil and then coat with the seasoning mixture.
  4. Add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Place the tenderloin in the hot skillet and sear on all sides, about 2 to 3 minutes per side. Place the seared tenderloin on the prepared baking sheet.
  5. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes with an internal temperature of 145 F (63 C) for medium-rare or 160 F (71 C) for medium. Remove the tenderloin from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing.
  6. Meanwhile, add the fresh parsley, garlic, optional chili pepper, olive oil, apple cider vinegar, and lemon juice in a blender or food processor and combine until smooth.
  7. Serve the sliced tenderloin with the chimichurri sauce.

name: Keto Sesame Ground Beef Teriyaki with Kale
ingredients:
• 0.25 cup of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (60 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of applesauce (30 ml)
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh ginger (10 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1.75 lbs of ground beef (788 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 20 white button mushrooms (200 g), sliced
  • 4 oz of kale (112 g), stems removed and chopped
  • 2 teaspoons of sesame oil (10 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger. Slice the mushrooms and chop the kale (stems removed).
  2. In a bowl, whisk to combine the tamari sauce or coconut aminos, applesauce, garlic, and fresh ginger. Add the ground beef to the marinade and set aside.
  3. In a large skillet, add the avocado oil over high heat. Add the mushrooms to the skillet and stir-fry until golden brown, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the ground beef with the marinade to the skillet and stir-fry until browned, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  5. Add the kale and sesame oil to the skillet and continue to stir-fry until the ground beef is cooked to your liking and the kale is wilted, about an additional 1 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Bacon and Avocado Kale Salad
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 2 slices of bacon (56 g), diced
  • 6 oz of kale (168 g), stems removed and chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of apple cider vinegar (15 ml)
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, chop the kale (stems removed), thinly slice the cucumber and onion and slice the avocado.
  2. In a medium skillet, saute the bacon over medium-high heat until crispy, about 5 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the kale, cooked bacon, cucumber and onion.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of sliced avocado.

name: Keto Curried Tuna Salad
ingredients:
• 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 2 stalks of celery (40 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh cilantro (1 g)
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of curry powder (2 g) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna. Thinly slice the celery stalks and onion.
  2. In a large bowl, toss the spinach with the olive oil. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and set aside.
  3. In the same bowl, combine the tuna with the remaining ingredients.
  4. Place equal amounts of tuna salad on the spinach and serve.

name: Keto Creamy Chicken Avocado Salad
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 cup of coconut cream (60 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast, slice the avocado and thinly slice the cucumber and onion.
  2. In a medium skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Set aside to cool slightly.
  3. In a medium bowl, combine the cooked chicken, avocado, cucumber, and onion with the coconut cream. Season with additional salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of chicken salad.

name: Keto Beef and Green Bean Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 oz of green beans (112 g), chopped
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the green beans and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the green beans to the skillet and saute until soft, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef and garlic to the skillet and saute until cooked to your liking, about 5 to 8 minutes.
  4. Add the spinach and lime juice to the skillet and saute until the spinach is wilted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the saute between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Sesame Chicken Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), sliced
  • 6 green onions (30 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of sesame oil (5 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breasts, thinly slice the cabbage, slice the zucchini, chop the green onions and mince or finely dice the fresh ginger.
  2. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and stir-fry until cooked through, about 8 to 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.
  3. Add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to the same skillet over medium-high heat. Add the cabbage, zucchini, green onions, and fresh ginger to the skillet and stir-fry until the vegetables are soft, about 10 to 12 minutes.
  4. Add the cooked chicken, tamari sauce or coconut aminos, and sesame oil to the skillet and stir-fry for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Easy Beef Taco Meat
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), diced
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 3 cloves of garlic (9 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 2 teaspoons of cumin powder (4 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of fresh ginger (2 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 teaspoon of chili powder (1 g) (or to taste)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bell pepper and onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and fresh ginger and chop the tomato.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft and browned, about 6 to 8 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef and garlic to the skillet and saute until the ground beef is browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  4. Add the tomato, cumin, fresh ginger, and chili powder to the skillet and saute until the tomato is soft, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Veggie Scramble
ingredients:
• 4 Tablespoons of ghee (60 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 4 medium eggs, whisked
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Whisk the eggs, slice the bell pepper and zucchini and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a large skillet, melt 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of ghee over medium heat. Add the whisked eggs to the skillet and scramble until cooked to your liking, about 2 to 4 minutes. Remove the scrambled eggs from the skillet and set aside.
  3. In the same skillet, melt the remaining 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of ghee over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper, zucchini and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  4. Return the eggs to the skillet and saute until the eggs are heated through, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the veggie scramble between 2 plates.

name: Keto Creamy Garlic Shrimp and "Pasta"
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 lb of shrimp, fresh or frozen (450 g), peeled and deveined, defrosted if frozen
  • 2 cucumbers (440 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic, peel and devein the shrimp (defrosted if frozen) and spiralize the cucumbers or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands.
  2. Add the olive oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion and garlic to the skillet and saute until the onion is soft and slightly browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  3. Add the shrimp to the skillet and saute until cooked through and opaque, about 2 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the cucumber “pasta” and coconut cream to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Warm Bacon and Green Bean Salad
ingredients:
• 6 slices of bacon (168 g), diced
  • 4 oz of green beans (112 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of balsamic vinegar (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, chop the green beans and romaine lettuce and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a medium skillet, add the bacon and cook over medium-high heat until slightly crispy, about 4 to 5 minutes.
  3. Add the green beans and onion to the skillet and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 5 to 7 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. In a large bowl, toss the romaine lettuce leaves with the olive oil and balsamic vinegar.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the green bean saute.

name: Keto Crispy Garlic Chicken Wings with Creamy Coleslaw
ingredients:
For the chicken wings -

  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of hot sauce (10 ml) (optional)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 6 chicken wings (with skin on) (540 g)

For the coleslaw -

  • 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 green onions (20 g), sliced
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of vinegar (10 ml) (of choice)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the coleslaw, thinly slice the cabbage and green onions.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  3. In a small bowl, combine the olive oil, lemon juice, optional hot sauce, and garlic powder to make a marinade. Place the chicken wings and marinade in a sealed container or storage bag and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes. (For more flavorful results, marinate in the refrigerator overnight.)
  4. Place a wire rack inside of a rimmed baking sheet. When ready to cook, remove chicken wings from the marinade and place in a single layer on top of the wire rack. Discard the remaining marinade.
  5. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 35 to 40 minutes until the wings are cooked through and crispy with an internal temperature of 165 F (74 C).
  6. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the creamy coleslaw ingredients.
  7. Serve the chicken wings with the coleslaw.

name: Keto Creamy Mustard Chicken Salad
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 0.25 cup of coconut cream (60 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • 2 teaspoons of mustard (10 ml), (or to taste)
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast, chop the romaine lettuce and tomato and thinly slice the cucumber and onion.
  2. In a medium skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 5 to 7 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. In a small bowl, combine the cooked chicken with the coconut cream and mustard.
  4. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves, cucumber, tomato and onion.
  5. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of chicken salad.

name: Keto Steak with Garlic Mushrooms
ingredients:
• 2 beef steaks (400 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), divided
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 4 green onions (20 g), chopped
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 teaspoons of dried thyme (2 g)
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 0.25 cup of chicken broth (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the mushrooms, chop the onions and tomato and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (180 C). Generously season the steaks with salt and set aside.
  3. In a medium skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of ghee over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms and green onions to the skillet and saute until the mushrooms start to soften, about 3 minutes.
  4. Add the garlic and dried thyme to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Place the mushroom mixture, tomato and chicken broth in an 8-inch (20 cm) square baking dish. 
  6. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
  7. Meanwhile, in a large skillet over high heat, add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of ghee. Add the steaks and sear for 3 minutes. Using tongs, turn over the steaks and sear for an additional 3 to 4 minutes (or until done to your liking) with an internal temperature of 140 F (60 C) for medium-rare. Set the steaks aside to rest for at least 5 minutes before serving.
  8. Serve the steaks with the mushrooms.

name: Keto Shrimp and Guacamole Bowls
ingredients:
For the shrimp bowls -

  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of lime juice (30 ml) 
  • 1 teaspoon of lime zest (1 g)
  • 1 lb of shrimp, fresh or frozen (450 g), defrosted if frozen, peeled and deveined
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the guacamole -

  • 1 large avocado (200 g), mashed
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped small
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of lime juice (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the shrimp bowls, peel and devein the shrimp (defrosted if frozen) and chop the romaine lettuce. For the guacamole, mash the avocado, chop the tomato and fresh cilantro into small pieces and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the olive oil, 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of lime juice, and lime zest. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. 
  3. Add the shrimp to the bowl and marinate for 30 minutes. (For more flavorful results, marinate in the refrigerator for up to 2 hours.)
  4. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine the guacamole ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.
  5. When ready to cook, add the shrimp with the marinade to a large skillet over medium heat and saute until cooked through and opaque, about 2 to 5 minutes. Season with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
  6. Divide the chopped romaine lettuce leaves between 2 bowls. Top each bowl with equal amounts of shrimp and guacamole.

name: Keto Easy Pork Pad Thai
ingredients:
For the pad thai -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 green onions (10 g), sliced
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt, to taste

For the satay sauce -

  • 3 Tablespoons of avocado oil (45 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of almond butter (30 ml)
  • 0.5 small orange (50 g), juice and zest
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the pad thai, thinly slice the pork tenderloin and green onions, spiralize the zucchinis or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands and chop the fresh cilantro. For the satay sauce, juice and zest the orange and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. In a small bowl, whisk to combine the satay sauce ingredients. Set aside until ready to use.
  3. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the pork and green onions to the skillet and saute until the pork is browned, about 1 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the zucchini “noodles” to the skillet and saute until the pork is cooked to your liking, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  5. Add the satay sauce to the skillet and saute until warm, about 30 seconds. If desired, season with additional salt, to taste.
  6. Divide the Pad Thai between 2 plates and garnish with the fresh cilantro.

name: Keto Creamy Cauliflower Soup with Bacon
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 slices of bacon (56 g), diced
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.5 cup of chicken broth (120 ml)
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, break the cauliflower into small florets and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a large saucepan, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the bacon to the pan and cook until crispy, about 3 to 5 minutes. Remove the bacon from the saucepan with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. Add the cauliflower and onion to the same saucepan over medium-high heat. Cover and cook until the vegetables are soft, about 7 to 8 minutes.
  4. If using an immersion blender, add the chicken broth and coconut cream to the saucepan and blend until smooth. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. If using a food processor or blender, combine the vegetables, chicken broth, and coconut cream until smooth. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the soup between 2 bowls and top with the cooked bacon.

name: Keto Chicken and Broccoli Bake
ingredients:
• 3 Tablespoons of avocado oil (45 ml), divided
  • 8 chicken thighs (with skin on) (1200 g)
  • 2 heads of broccoli (900 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), chopped 
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 Tablespoon of Italian seasoning (3 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the broccoli into small florets, chop the zucchinis, thinly slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Lightly grease a large baking dish or rimmed baking tray and set aside.
  3. Generously season the chicken thighs with salt and pepper.
  4. Add 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet, skin side down, and cook until the skin is golden and crispy, about 7 to 8 minutes. Using tongs, turn over the chicken and continue to cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes.
  5. In a large bowl, toss the broccoli, zucchinis, onion, garlic and Italian seasoning with the remaining 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of avocado oil. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Place the vegetables in a single layer in the baking dish. Place the chicken thighs, skin side up, on top of the vegetables. 
  7. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 30 minutes until the chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C). (For softer vegetables, remove the chicken from the baking dish and decrease the oven temperature to 350 F [177 C]. Continue to bake the vegetables for an additional 10 to 15 minutes until soft to your liking.) 
  8. Serve the chicken thighs with the vegetables.

name: Keto Simple Salad with Fried Eggs
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 medium eggs 
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of Italian seasoning (1 g)
directions:
1. Chop the romaine lettuce and tomato. Thinly slice the cucumber and onion.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium heat. Add the eggs to the skillet and fry to your liking, about 3 minutes for a runny yolk and 5 to 6 minutes for a hard-cooked yolk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the olive oil, lemon juice and Italian seasoning. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves. Add the cucumber, tomato and onion to the bowl.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates. Top each plate with 2 fried eggs and serve.

name: Keto Easy Chicken Salsa Lettuce Wraps
ingredients:
For the lettuce wraps -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), separated into individual leaves
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the salsa -

  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml) (or to taste)
  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh cilantro (1 g), chopped
directions:
1. For the wraps, dice the chicken breast, separate the romaine lettuce into individual leaves and slice the avocado. For the salsa, chop the tomatoes and fresh cilantro and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a medium skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet and saute until cooked through, about 5 to 7 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. In a medium bowl, combine the tomatoes, onion, olive oil, lemon juice and fresh cilantro.
  4. Place equal amounts of chicken in the lettuce leaves and top with the salsa and sliced avocado. Fold the lettuce leaves around the chicken and salsa to form a wrap and serve.

name: Keto Stovetop Beef and Veggie Curry
ingredients:
• 1.75 lbs of beef stew chunks (788 g)
  • 0.5 cup of beef broth (120 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of curry powder (14 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 3 zucchinis (360 g), chopped
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1.5 cups of coconut milk (360 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the zucchinis and tomatoes, break the cauliflower into small florets and thinly slice the onion.
  2. Place the beef chunks, beef broth, curry powder and garlic powder in a large pot. Cover and simmer for 90 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the beef is fork-tender. 
  3. Add the zucchinis, cauliflower, tomatoes, onion and coconut milk to the pot. Cover and cook for an additional 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are tender. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Pressure Cooker Beef and Veggie Curry
ingredients:
• 1.75 lbs of beef stew chunks (788 g)
  • 0.5 cup of beef broth (120 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of curry powder (14 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 3 zucchinis (360 g), chopped
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1.5 cups of coconut milk (360 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the zucchinis and tomatoes, break the cauliflower into small florets and thinly slice the onion.
  2. Add the beef chunks, beef broth, curry powder and garlic powder to the pressure cooker. Secure the lid and cook for 25 minutes on high pressure. 
  3. Carefully release the pressure and add the zucchinis, cauliflower, tomatoes and onion to the pot. Secure the lid and cook for an additional 10 minutes on high pressure. 
  4. Carefully release the pressure and stir in the coconut milk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Slow Cooker Beef and Veggie Curry
ingredients:
• 1.75 lbs of beef stew chunks (788 g)
  • 0.5 cup of beef broth (120 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of curry powder (14 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 3 zucchinis (360 g), chopped
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1.5 cups of coconut milk (360 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the zucchinis and tomatoes, break the cauliflower into small florets and thinly slice the onion.
  2. Add the beef chunks, beef broth, curry powder and garlic powder to the slow cooker. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours and on high for 4 to 6 hours. 
  3. Remove the lid and add the zucchinis, cauliflower, tomatoes and onion to the slow cooker. Continue to cook on low for 45 to 60 minutes or on high for 30 minutes. 
  4. Remove the lid and stir in the coconut milk. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Lemon Pepper and Avocado Tuna Salad
ingredients:
• 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 Tablespoons of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml) (or to taste)
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna, thinly slice the cucumber and slice the avocado.
  2. In a large bowl, combine the tuna and cucumber with the mayo, mustard and lemon juice. Season with pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of tuna salad and sliced avocado.

name: Keto Cucumber Avocado and Tomato Salad
ingredients:
• 2 large avocados (400 g), sliced
  • 1 cucumber (220 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped small
  • 0.25 cup of fresh basil leaves (8 g), chopped
  • 0.25 cup of olive oil (60 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 4 cups of spinach (120 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Slice the avocados, thinly slice the cucumber and chop the tomatoes and fresh basil leaves into small pieces.
  2. In a medium bowl, combine the avocados, cucumber, tomatoes and fresh basil with the olive oil and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the cucumber salad.

name: Keto Avocado and Bacon Salad with Apple Cider Dressing
ingredients:
For the salad -

  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced

For the dressing -

  • 3 Tablespoons of olive oil (45 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of apple cider vinegar (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, chop the romaine lettuce, thinly slice the cucumber and onion and slice the avocado.
  2. In a nonstick skillet over medium heat, saute the bacon until crispy, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet with a slotted spoon and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the dressing ingredients. Toss the dressing with the romaine lettuce leaves, cooked bacon, cucumber and onion.
  4. Divide the salad between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of sliced avocado.

name: Keto Pork Chops with Creamy Slaw
ingredients:
For the pork chops -

  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 pork chops (320 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the creamy slaw -

  • 1 head of cabbage (700 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 carrot (50 g), grated
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 3 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (6 g), chopped
  • 6 Tablespoons of mayo (90 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of apple cider vinegar (30 ml) (or to taste)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the slaw, thinly slice the cabbage and onion, grate the carrot and chop the fresh parsley.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Season the pork chops with salt and pepper, to taste.
  3. Add the pork chops to the skillet and cook on one side for 2 to 3 minutes. Using tongs, turn over the pork chops and continue to cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes (or more to the desired doneness). Check with a meat thermometer that the internal temperature reaches 145°F (63°C) for medium-rare. Let the pork chops rest for 10 minutes before serving. 
  4. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the creamy slaw ingredients. 
  5. Serve the pork chops with the slaw.

name: Keto Simple Tuna Salad
ingredients:
• 2 medium eggs 
  • 2 cans of tuna (340 g), drained and flaked
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of lemon juice (5 ml) (or to taste)
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Drain and flake the tuna. Thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove the pot from heat. Place a lid on the pot and let sit for 12 minutes. Drain the eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and chop the eggs.
  3. In a medium bowl, combine the chopped eggs, tuna and onion with the mayo and lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the spinach leaves between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of tuna salad.

name: Keto Cumin Beef and Tomato Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of cumin powder (6 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of apple cider vinegar (5 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the tomatoes and zucchini.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until translucent, about 1 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the ground beef and garlic to the skillet and saute until the ground beef is slightly browned, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  4. Add the tomatoes, zucchini, cumin powder and apple cider vinegar to the skillet and continue to saute until the vegetables are soft and the ground beef is cooked to your liking, about 3 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Fish Taco Bowls with Guacamole
ingredients:
For the taco bowls -

  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 filets of cod (340 g), defrosted if frozen, diced
  • 1 teaspoon of paprika (2 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of chili powder (1 g) (or to taste)
  • 1 head of romaine lettuce (200 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the guacamole -

  • 2 large avocados (400 g), mashed
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped small
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of lime juice (15 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), chopped 
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the taco bowls, dice the cod filets (defrosted if frozen) and chop the romaine lettuce. For the guacamole, mash the avocados, chop the tomato and fresh cilantro into small pieces and thinly slice the onion.
  2. In a large nonstick skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the cod and saute until cooked through, about 3 to 5 minutes. 
  3. Add the paprika and chili powder to the skillet and saute for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Set aside.
  4. Meanwhile, combine the guacamole ingredients.
  5. Divide the romaine lettuce between 2 bowls and top with equal amounts of fish and guacamole.

name: Keto Bacon and Spinach Skillet Frittata
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 4 medium eggs, whisked
  • 0.25 cup of coconut milk (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the bacon, thinly slice the onion, chop the tomato and whisk the eggs.
  2. In a large nonstick skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bacon and onion to the skillet and saute until the bacon is crispy, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  3. Add the tomato and spinach to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 2 to 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. In a small bowl, whisk the eggs and coconut milk until fully combined.
  5. Pour the egg mixture in the skillet and completely cover the vegetables. Reduce the heat to medium-low until the eggs are almost set, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  6. Remove the skillet from the heat, cover, and let stand until the eggs are fully set and no liquid remains, about 5 to 10 minutes.
  7. Divide the frittata between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Zucchini Fries with Garlicky Ground Beef
ingredients:
For the zucchini fries - 

  • 2 zucchinis (240 g), seeds removed, halved and cut into fry-size wedges
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 0.5 Tablespoon of onion powder (4 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the garlicky beef -

  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml)
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.5 lb of ground beef (225 g)
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the fries, slice the zucchinis in half and then cut into fry-size wedges (seeds removed). For the garlicky beef, thinly slice the onion and mince or finely dice the garlic.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Lightly grease a rimmed baking sheet and set aside.
  3. In a bowl, toss the zucchinis with the avocado oil, garlic powder and onion powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Place the zucchinis in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 20 minutes until the zucchini “fries” are cooked to your liking. Remove the baking sheet from the oven and let cool slightly.
  5. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium heat. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until translucent, about 1 to 3 minutes. 
  6. Add the ground beef and garlic to the skillet and saute until the ground beef is cooked to your liking, about 3 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. Divide the zucchini “fries” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of garlicky beef.

name: Keto Basil Chicken Saute
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 0.25 cup of fresh basil leaves (8 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breasts, thinly slice the onion and chop the tomatoes and fresh basil leaves.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and onion to the skillet and saute until the chicken is cooked through, about 7 to 10 minutes.
  3. Add the tomatoes and fresh basil to the skillet and saute until the tomatoes are soft, about 2 to 4 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the saute between 2 plates and serve.

name: Keto Slow Cooker Braised Pork Shoulder
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 lbs of pork shoulder (900 g), cut into large pieces
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced
  • 2 cups of beef broth (480 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of apple cider vinegar (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Cut the pork shoulder into large pieces and slice the onion.
  2. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over high heat. In batches, add the pork to the skillet and brown on all sides, about 5 to 10 minutes per batch. Remove the pork from the skillet and place in the slow cooker.
  3. In the same skillet, add the onion and saute until golden brown, about 5 minutes. Remove the onion from the skillet and place in the slow cooker.
  4. Add the beef broth and apple cider vinegar to the slow cooker. Cover and cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or on low for 6 to 8 hours until the pork shreds easily. Let the pork rest for 10 minutes before removing it from the slow cooker.
  5. Remove the pork from the slow cooker and place on a carving board or large platter. Use 2 forks to shred the pork into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Pressure Cooker Braised Pork Shoulder
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 lbs of pork shoulder (900 g), cut into large pieces
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced
  • 2 cups of beef broth (480 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of apple cider vinegar (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over high heat. In batches, add the pork to the skillet and brown on all sides, about 5 to 10 minutes per batch. Remove the pork from the skillet and set aside.
  2. Add the onion to the skillet and saute until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
  3. Add the pork, onion and the remaining ingredients to the pressure cooker. Secure the lid and cook on high pressure for 40 minutes. 
  4. Quick-release the pressure and carefully remove the lid. If the pork is not fork-tender, replace the lid and cook on high pressure for an additional 5 minutes or until the pork shreds easily. Let the pork rest for 10 minutes before removing it from the pressure cooker.
  5. Remove the pork from the pressure cooker and place on a carving board or large platter. Use 2 forks to shred the pork into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Easy Braised Pork Shoulder
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 2 lbs of pork shoulder (900 g), cut into large pieces
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced
  • 2 cups of beef broth (480 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of apple cider vinegar (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. In a large pot, melt the coconut oil over high heat. In batches, add the pork to the pot and brown on all sides, about 5 to 10 minutes per batch. Remove the pork from the pot and set aside.
  2. In the same pot, add the onion and saute until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
  3. Return the pork to the pot and reduce the heat to low. Add the beef broth and apple cider vinegar to the pot. Cover and cook for 60 minutes until the pork is fork-tender and shreds easily. Let the pork rest for 10 minutes before removing it from the pot.
  4. Remove the pork from the pot and place on a carving board or large platter. Use 2 forks to shred the pork into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Cauliflower Mash
ingredients:
• 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 cup of coconut milk (120 ml)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. Break the cauliflower into small florets.
  2. Boil or steam the cauliflower until soft, about 5 to 7 minutes. Drain well. 
  3. Using a food processor or blender, combine the cauliflower with the coconut milk. Season with salt, to taste.

name: Keto Avocado and Cucumber "Toast"
ingredients:
• 2.5 Tablespoons of ghee (38 ml), melted (plus additional for the mug)
  • 1 medium egg, whisked
  • 1/3 cup of almond flour (40 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of baking powder (1 g)
  • Dash of salt 
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
directions:
1. Melt the ghee, whisk the egg, thinly slice the cucumber and slice the avocado.
  2. Grease a microwave-safe mug with ghee and set aside.
  3. In a small bowl, whisk to combine the melted ghee and whisked egg with the almond flour, baking powder and a dash of salt. Pour the mixture into the greased mug.
  4. Place the mug in a microwave and cook for 90 seconds on high. Remove from the microwave and let cool slightly.
  5. Once the mug is cool enough to handle, gently remove the bread and slice into 4 pieces. 
  6. Toast the bread using a toaster, toaster oven or under a broiler until toasted to your liking. 
  7. Place an equal amount of sliced cucumber and avocado on the toast before serving.

name: Keto Spicy Beef and Basil Stir-Fry
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium bell pepper (120 g), sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), chopped
  • 0.25 cup of fresh basil leaves (8 g), chopped
  • 1 teaspoon of hot sauce (5 ml) (or to taste) (optional)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and onion to the skillet and stir-fry until soft and slightly browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  2. Add the ground beef and garlic to the skillet and stir-fry until the ground beef is slightly browned, about 3 to 4 minutes.
  3. Add the tomatoes and zucchini to the skillet and stir-fry until the vegetables are soft and the ground beef is cooked to your liking, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the fresh basil and optional hot sauce to the skillet and stir-fry for an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
total_nutrition_value: Calories:  560	 Fat:  43 g	 Total Carbs:  13 g	 Fiber:  3 g	 Sugar:  6 g	 Net Carbs:  10 g	 Protein:  31 g

name: Keto Creamy Chicken "Noodle" Soup
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 chicken breast (200 g), diced
  • 0.25 medium onion (28 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • 3 cups of chicken broth (720 ml)
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), spiralized or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands
  • 0.5 cup of coconut cream (120 ml) (from the top of a refrigerated can of coconut milk)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Dice the chicken breast, thinly slice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and spiralize the zucchini or use a vegetable peeler to create noodle-like strands.
  2. In a saucepan, melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken, onion and garlic to the saucepan and saute until the chicken is browned, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  3. Add the chicken broth to the saucepan and increase the heat to high to bring the broth to a boil. Continue to boil until the chicken is cooked through, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  4. Add the zucchini “noodles” to the saucepan and boil for an additional 1 minute.
  5. Remove the saucepan from the heat and add the coconut cream. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Blueberry Coconut Yogurt Smoothie
ingredients:
• 1 container of coconut yogurt (120 ml or 4 oz) 
  • 1 cup coconut milk (240 ml)
  • 10 blueberries (5 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon vanilla extract (3 ml)
  • Erythritol, to taste (optional)
directions: 1. Add all of the ingredients into a blender and combine until smooth.

name: Keto Egg-Free Beef Meatloaf
ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of chia seeds (24 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), to cook with (plus additional to grease the loaf pan)
  • 20 white button mushrooms (200 g), finely chopped
  • 1 lb of ground beef (450 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of onion powder (7 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of dried rosemary (3 g) (or 3 Tablespoons of fresh rosemary)
  • 12 slices of bacon (336 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Finely chop the mushrooms.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350 F (180°C). Line a loaf pan with parchment paper and set aside.
  3. In a small bowl or ramekin, combine the chia seeds with 5 Tablespoons (75 ml) water. Set aside until ready to use.
  4. Meanwhile, add the avocado oil to a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms to the skillet and saute for about 4 to 5 minutes. Reduce the heat to medium-low and continue to saute until the mushrooms are dark brown and most of the moisture has evaporated, about an additional 4 to 5 minutes. Remove the mushrooms from the skillet and place on a paper towel-lined plate to cool.
  5. In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, garlic powder, onion powder, dried rosemary and the cooled mushrooms. Add the chia mixture to the ground beef and mix until just combined. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Place the bacon strips in the prepared loaf pan making sure they overlap the sides on the pan in order to cover the top of the meatloaf.
  7. Place the ground beef mixture in the loaf pan. Press down firmly in the meatloaf with a spatula or your hand. Cover the top of the meatloaf with the bacon.
  8. Place the loaf pan in the oven and bake for 50 minutes or until the internal temperature reaches 160 F (71 C).
  9. Remove the meatloaf from the oven and let cool for 10 minutes before slicing. If desired, spoon excess moisture over the meatloaf after it is sliced.

name: Keto Bacon Meatloaf and Creamy Coleslaw
ingredients:
For the meatloaf -

  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 30 white button mushrooms (300 g), finely chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), finely chopped
  • 1 lb of ground beef (450 g)
  • 1 medium egg (49 g), whisked
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of onion powder (7 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of dried rosemary (3 g)
  • 12 slices of bacon (336 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the coleslaw -

  • 1 head of cabbage (700 g), shredded or thinly sliced
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 carrot (50 g), shredded or thinly sliced
  • 0.5 cup of mayo (120 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of apple cider vinegar (30 ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of mustard (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. For the meatloaf, finely chop the mushrooms and onion and whisk the egg. For the coleslaw, shred or thinly slice the cabbage and carrot and thinly slice the onion.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C). Line a loaf pan with parchment paper and set aside.
  3. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms and onion to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are golden brown and the liquid has evaporated, about 6 to 8 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove the mushroom mixture from the skillet with a slotted spoon and place on a paper towel-lined plate to absorb excess moisture.
  4. In a medium bowl, combine the ground beef, whisked egg, garlic powder, onion powder, dried rosemary, and the mushroom mixture.
  5. Place the bacon strips in the prepared loaf pan making sure they overlap the sides on the pan in order to cover the top of the meatloaf.
  6. Place the ground beef mixture in the loaf pan. Press down firmly in the meatloaf with a spatula or your hand. Cover the top of the meatloaf with the bacon.
  7. Place the loaf pan in the oven and bake for 50 minutes or until the internal temperature reaches 160°F (71°C). Remove the meatloaf from the oven and let cool for 10 minutes before slicing.
  8. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, toss to combine the creamy coleslaw ingredients.
  9. Serve the meatloaf with the coleslaw.

name: Keto Simple Egg and Avocado Salad
ingredients:
• 4 medium eggs
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • 1 stalk of celery (20 g), thinly sliced
  • 0.25 cup of mayo (60 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (2 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. In a pot, cover the eggs with water and bring to a boil. Once boiling, remove the pot from heat. Place a lid on the pot and let sit for 12 minutes. Drain the eggs in a colander and rinse with cold water. Peel and chop the eggs.
  2. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, toss the spinach with the olive oil. Divide the spinach between 2 plates and set aside.
  3. In the same bowl, combine the chopped eggs, avocado, and celery with the mayo and fresh parsley. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Top each plate of spinach with equal amounts of egg and avocado salad.
total_nutrition_value: Calories:  555	 Fat:  54 g	 Total Carbs:  10 g	 Fiber:  8 g	 Sugar:  1 g	 Net Carbs:  2 g	 Protein:  15 g

name: Keto Baked Chicken Drumsticks with Roasted Broccoli
ingredients:
For the drumsticks -

  • 4 chicken drumsticks (with skin on) (500 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided
  • 1 small tomato (90 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 4 olives (12 g), chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the roasted broccoli -

  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), broken into small florets
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:

ingredients:
• 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g), diced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 4 oz of green beans (112 g), chopped
  • 2 green onions (10 g), chopped
  • 0.5 medium bell pepper (60 g), chopped
  • 2 stalks of celery (40 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh basil leaves (4 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cup of coconut milk (120 ml)
  • 0.5 cup of chicken broth (120 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of lime juice (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the pan and saute until cooked through, about 6 to 8 minutes. Use a slotted spoon to remove the cooked chicken from the pan and set aside.
  2. In the same pan, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil. Add the garlic, green beans, green onion, bell pepper, celery, and fresh basil to the pan and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 5 minutes.
  3. Add the cooked chicken, coconut milk, chicken broth, and lime juice to the pan. Reduce the heat to medium and cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes or until the sauce has thickened to desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Divide the chicken and vegetables between 2 bowls and serve.

name: Keto Mushroom and Onion Frittata
ingredients:
• 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 15 white button mushrooms (150 g), chopped
  • 3 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (3 g), chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of Italian seasoning (3 g)
  • 6 medium eggs
  • 0.25 cup of coconut milk (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Thinly slice the onion, mince or finely dice the garlic and chop the mushrooms and fresh parsley.
  2. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Grease an 8-inch (20 cm) square baking dish and set aside.
  3. Melt the coconut oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion and garlic to the skillet and saute until the onion is translucent.
  4. Add the mushrooms, fresh parsley, and Italian seasoning to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are soft, about 5 minutes. Set aside and let cool.
  5. In a medium bowl, whisk the eggs and coconut milk. Add the cooled vegetable mixture and stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Pour the egg mixture into the greased baking dish.
  6. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the eggs are cooked through and set. Remove from the oven and let cool for a few minutes before serving.

name: Keto Crispy Chicken Wings with Avocado Slaw
ingredients:
For the chicken wings marinade -

  • 6 chicken wings (with skin on) (540 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of garlic powder (20 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of hot sauce (10 ml) (or to taste) (optional)
  • 2 teaspoons of black pepper (2 g) (or to taste)
  • Salt, to taste

For the avocado slaw -

  • 0.25 head of cabbage (175 g), thinly sliced
  • 3 Tablespoons of fresh parsley (3 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of mayo (30 ml)
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  2. In a small bowl, combine the marinade ingredients. Place the chicken wings and marinade in a sealed container or storage bag and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes. (For more flavorful results, marinate in the refrigerator overnight.)
  3. Place a wire rack inside of a rimmed baking sheet. When ready to cook, remove the chicken wings from the marinade and place the wings in a single layer on top of the wire rack. Discard the excess marinade.
  4. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until the wings are cooked through and crispy with an internal temperature of 165 F (74 C).
  5. Meanwhile, to make the slaw, combine the cabbage, fresh parsley, and mayo in a large bowl. Add the avocado and stir, careful not to break the avocado slices. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Divide the slaw between two plates and serve with the chicken wings.

ingredients:

  • 0.5 lb of pork belly (225 g), scored on skin-side
  • 2 Tablespoons of vinegar (30 ml) (of your choice)

  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of onion powder (7 g)

For the beets and zucchini -

  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml)
  • 1 zucchini (120 g), roughly chopped
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)

directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  2. In a small baking dish, combine the vinegar, nutmeg, garlic powder and onion powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Set aside.

  5. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake for 40 minutes. Remove the foil and continue to bake for an additional 20 minutes until the liquid has reduced.
  6. Meanwhile, place the peeled and chopped beets into a pot with water and boil until tender, about 25 minutes. Drain well.
  7. In a large skillet, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the drained beets, zucchini and lemon juice to the skillet and saute until the vegetables are cooked to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  8. Slice the pork belly and serve with the beets and zucchini. Drizzle desired amount of baking juices (from cooking the pork belly) over the pork belly and vegetables.

  • 1 head of broccoli (450 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), diced
  • 1 small sweet potato (130 g), chopped
  • 2 cups of chicken broth (480 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of coconut milk (60 ml) (from a room temperature can)
  • 1 Tablespoon of curry powder (7 g)
  • 2 slices of bacon (56 g), diced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. In a large pot, melt the coconut oil over medium heat. Add the broccoli, cauliflower, tomatoes, and sweet potato to the pot and saute until the vegetables are slightly brown, about 7 to 8 minutes.
  2. Add the chicken broth to the pot and reduce the heat to a simmer. Cover and cook until the vegetables are soft to your liking, stirring occasionally. 
  3. Add the coconut milk and curry powder to the pot, stirring to combine. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Meanwhile, in a small skillet, cook the bacon until crispy, about 2 to 3 minutes. 
  5. Add the bacon to the pot and simmer for an additional 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
  6. Divide the vegetable curry between 2 bowls and enjoy.

ingredients:

  • 1 medium onion (110 g), finely diced

  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh cilantro (2 g), finely chopped
  • 6 [3-oz] packs of shirataki noodles (510 g), drained (optional)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil (15 ml), to cook with

For the sauce -

  • 1 cup of water (240 ml)
  • 2 Tablespoons of lime juice (30 ml)
  • 1 chili pepper (14 g), seeds removed and finely diced (optional)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 6 teaspoons of fish sauce (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the garnish -

  • 0.25 head of iceberg lettuce (113 g), finely shredded
  • 0.5 cucumber (110 g), seeds removed, sliced into thin strips
  • 0.5 carrot (25 g), cut into thin strips
  • Small handful of cilantro, finely chopped
  • Small handful of mint, finely chopped
  • Small handful of Thai basil, finely chopped
directions:
1. In a medium bowl, combine the ground pork, onion, fish sauce, garlic and fresh cilantro. Form into small meatballs, about the size of ping-pong balls. Set aside.
  2. If using, rinse and drain the shirataki noodles very well, per package directions. If desired, boil the noodles for 2 to 3 minutes to help eliminate the smell. Drain the noodles and set aside to keep warm.
  3. To make the sauce, heat the water in a medium pan over medium-high heat until warm. Add the lime juice, optional chili pepper, and garlic to the pan. Continue to cook until liquid has reduced by half, stirring occasionally. Once reduced, stir in the fish sauce to the sauce. Season with salt and pepper, to taste, and set aside.
  4. Meanwhile, add the olive oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. In batches, cook the meatballs until browned and cooked through, about 2 to 3 minutes per side depending on the size of the meatballs. Check with a meat thermometer that the internal temperature of the meatballs reaches 165 F (75 C).
  5. To serve, if using, divide the shirataki noodles among 4 bowls and add an equal amount of meatballs to each bowl. Cover the meatballs with the sauce and top with lettuce, cucumber, and carrot. Sprinkle each bowl with the desired amount of cilantro, mint, and Thai basil leaves.
