name: Paleo Steamed Egg Custard
ingredients:
• 2 medium eggs 
  • 1 Tablespoon of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (15 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of sesame oil (5 ml)
  • 1 green onion (5 g), chopped
directions:
1. Place the eggs in a small heatproof bowl or ramekin. Add room-temperature water (approx. the same volume as the eggs).
  2. Mix well. With a spoon, remove the foam that forms on top of the egg mixture.
  3. Place the bowl or ramekin into a steamer for 10 to 12 minutes. (The water in the steamer should be boiling before placing the egg custard into it.)
  4. Check the egg custard to ensure the middle is firm to the touch. Continue to steam for several additional minutes, if necessary.
  5. Carefully remove the egg custard from the steamer. Top with tamari sauce or coconut aminos, sesame oil, and green onion, if desired.

 

RECIPE NOTE: If you do not have a steamer, fill a saucepan S full with water. Place a bowl upside down in the water to partially submerge it. Place the egg custard bowl or ramekin on top of the partially-submerged bowl. Securely place the lid on the saucepan and steam as according to the directions.

name: Paleo Mu Shu Pork with Cauliflower Rice
ingredients:
For the mu shu pork -

  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), divided, to cook with
  • 4 medium eggs, whisked
  • 0.5 lb of pork tenderloin (225 g), sliced into 1-inch (2.5 cm) strips
  • 0.5 head of cabbage (350 g), shredded or thinly sliced
  • 4 carrots (200 g), shredded or thinly sliced
  • 10 white button mushrooms (100 g), sliced
  • 2 teaspoons of fresh ginger (3 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of vinegar (10 ml) (of choice)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the cauliflower rice - 

  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), melted
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. In a large nonstick skillet, melt 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium heat. Let the skillet heat for about 1 minute and pour in the eggs, completely covering the bottom of the skillet to create a pancake. Let the eggs cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until almost firm. Carefully turn over the egg pancake and cook for an additional 30 seconds to 1 minute or until completely cooked through. Remove the egg pancake from the skillet and cut into 1-inch (2.5 cm) strips. Set aside.
  2. In the same skillet, melt the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the pork and stir-fry until browned, about 2 to 4 minutes.
  3. Add the cabbage, carrots, mushrooms, ginger, tamari sauce or coconut aminos and vinegar to the skillet. Stir-fry until the vegetables are soft, about 6 to 8 minutes.
  4. Return the egg to the skillet and stir-fry until warmed through, about 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Meanwhile, to make the cauliflower rice, saute the cauliflower pieces in the ghee on high heat for 5 minutes until softened. Season with salt, to taste.
  6. Serve the cauliflower rice with the mu shu pork.

name: Paleo Creamy Chicken and Mushroom Pasta

name: Paleo Pineapple Pork with Sauteed Spinach
ingredients:
For the pineapple pork -

  • 2 lbs of pork shoulder (900 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of salt (15 g) (or to taste)
  • 1 Tablespoon of ginger powder (6 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of coconut oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 6 slices of pineapple (336 g), cut into chunks

  • 0.25 cup of fresh cilantro (4 g), chopped

directions:
1. Evenly cover the pork shoulder with the salt and ginger powder.

  7. Meanwhile, add the olive oil to a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion and saute until translucent, about 1 to 2 minutes.

For the beef goulash -

  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced

  • 1 lb of beef roast (450 g), cut into 1-inch (2.5 cm) cubes (or stew meat)

  • 0.5 cup of tomato sauce (120 g)

  • 1 bay leaf
  • 1 Tablespoon of paprika (6 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of arrowroot flour (8 g), to thicken sauce (optional)
  • 2 Tablespoons of cold water (30 ml) (plus additional, if needed) (optional)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the cauliflower rice -

  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), melted
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. Add the avocado oil to a large pot over high heat. Add the onion and garlic to the pot and saute until the onion is translucent, about 2 to 3 minutes.

  4. Reduce the heat to very low and add the tomato sauce, beef broth, paprika and bay leaf to the pot. 
  5. Cover and simmer for 60 minutes until the beef is fork-tender, stirring occasionally. Add additional water, 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) at a time, to prevent the mixture from sticking to the bottom of the pot, if needed.
  6. If the sauce is too thin, remove the lid and increase the heat slightly. Cook, stirring often, until the sauce is thick to your liking. Remove and discard the bay leaf. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. If desired, whisk to combine the arrowroot flour with 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of cold water to create a slurry. Add the arrowroot slurry to the pot and stir constantly until the sauce is thick to your liking.
  8. Meanwhile, to make the cauliflower rice, saute the cauliflower pieces in the ghee on high heat for 5 minutes until softened. Season with salt, to taste. 
  9. Serve the goulash over the cauliflower rice.

name: Keto Pressure Cooker Pulled Pork with Broccoli Mash
ingredients:
For the pork -

  • 3 lbs of pork shoulder (1350 g)
  • 1 cup of water (240 ml) (optional)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the broccoli mash -

  • 4 Tablespoons of ghee (60 ml), to cook with (plus additional, if needed)
  • 1 head of broccoli (450 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 medium onion (55 g), thinly sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice (15 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Generously season the pork shoulder with salt and pepper. If needed, cut the pork shoulder into several large pieces and place in the pressure cooker.
  2. If needed, add the optional water to the pressure cooker. (Not all pressure cookers require additional liquid in order to come to pressure. Please consult your owners manual to find out if additional liquid is needed.) Secure the lid and cook on high pressure for 40 minutes. Quick-release the pressure and carefully remove the lid. If the pork is not fork-tender, replace the lid and cook on high pressure for an additional 5 minutes or until the pork shreds easily. (See notes for alternate cooking methods.)
  3. Let the pork rest for 30 minutes before removing it from the pressure cooker. Place the pork on a carving board and use 2 forks to shred it into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. While the pork rests, melt the ghee in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the broccoli and onion to the pan, cover, and cook until the vegetables are soft, about 5 to 7 minutes.
  5. Place the broccoli mixture with the pan drippings and lemon juice in a blender or food processor and blend until smooth. If needed, add additional ghee to create a smooth mash. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. Serve the pulled pork with the broccoli mash.
     

NOTES: 

  • If using a slow cooker, cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or on low for 6 to 8 hours until the pork shreds easily.
  • If using an oven, preheat to 325 F (165 C) and cook for 2.5 to 3.5 hours until the pork shreds easily.

ingredients:

  • 1 Tablespoon of paprika (6 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of dried oregano (3 g)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced
  • 6 cloves of garlic (18 g), minced or finely diced
  • 1 cup of beef broth (240 ml)

  • 2 large avocados (400 g), sliced (for serving)

1. If needed, cut the pork shoulder into several large pieces to fit in the Instant Pot.

  4. Secure the lid and cook on high pressure for 40 minutes. Quick-release the pressure and carefully remove the lid. If the pork is not fork-tender, replace the lid and cook on high pressure for 5 minutes or until the pork shreds easily.
  5. Let the pork rest for 30 minutes before removing it from the Instant Pot. Place the pork on a carving board and use 2 forks to shred it into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  6. To serve, place the desired amount of pork carnitas in the lettuce leaves and top with the sliced avocados.

name: Keto Easy Braised Pork Shoulder with Cauli-Mash
ingredients:
For the braised pork -

  • 0.25 cup of coconut oil (60 ml), to cook with
  • 2 lbs of pork shoulder (900 g), cut into large pieces
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), sliced
  • 2 cups of beef broth (480 ml)
  • 0.25 cup of apple cider vinegar (60 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the cauli-mash -

  • 1 head of cauliflower (600 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 cup of coconut milk (120 ml)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
To make the cauli-mash -

  1. Boil or steam the cauliflower until soft, about 5 to 7 minutes. Drain well. 
  2. Using a food processor or blender, combine the cauliflower with the coconut milk. Season with salt, to taste.

 

If using a slow cooker for the braised pork -

  1. In a large skillet, melt the coconut oil over high heat. In batches, add the pork to the skillet and brown on all sides, about 5 to 10 minutes per batch. Remove the pork from the skillet and place in the slow cooker.
  2. In the same skillet, add the onion and saute until golden brown, about 5 minutes. Remove the onion from the skillet and place in the slow cooker.
  3. Add the beef broth and apple cider vinegar to the slow cooker. Cover and cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or on low for 6 to 8 hours until the pork shreds easily. Let the pork rest for 10 minutes before removing it from the slow cooker.
  4. Remove the pork from the slow cooker and place on a carving board or large platter. Use 2 forks to shred the pork into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Serve the pork with the cauli-mash.
     

If using a pressure cooker for the braised pork -

  1. In the pressure cooker, melt the coconut oil over high heat. In batches, add the pork to the pressure cooker and brown on all sides, about 5 to 10 minutes per batch. Remove the pork from the pressure cooker and set aside.
  2. Add the onion to the pressure cooker and saute until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
  3. Return the pork to the pressure cooker and add the beef broth and apple cider vinegar. Secure the lid and cook on high pressure for 40 minutes. Quick-release the pressure and carefully remove the lid. If the pork is not fork-tender, replace the lid and cook on high pressure for an additional 5 minutes or until the pork shreds easily.  Let the pork rest for 10 minutes before removing it from the pressure cooker.
  4. Remove the pork from the pressure cooker and place on a carving board or large platter. Use 2 forks to shred the pork into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Serve the pork with the cauli-mash.
     

If using a stovetop for the braised pork -

  1. In a large pot, melt the coconut oil over high heat. In batches, add the pork to the pot and brown on all sides, about 5 to 10 minutes per batch. Remove the pork from the pot and set aside.
  2. In the same pot, add the onion and saute until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
  3. Return the pork to the pot and reduce the heat to low. Add the beef broth and apple cider vinegar to the pot. Cover and cook for 60 minutes until the pork is fork-tender and shreds easily. Let the pork rest for 10 minutes before removing it from the pot.
  4. Remove the pork from the pot and place on a carving board or large platter. Use 2 forks to shred the pork into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Serve the pork with the cauli-mash.

Remove the mushrooms from the skillet and place on a paper towel-lined plate to cool.

name: Paleo Pesto-Stuffed Chicken Breast
ingredients:
For the pesto -

  • 1/3 cup of olive oil (80 ml) (plus additional, if needed)
  • 1.5 cups of fresh basil leaves (50 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of pine nuts (16 g) (or walnuts)
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), roughly chopped
  • 0.5 lemon, juice and zest
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the stuffed chicken breast -

  • 2 chicken breasts (approx. 200 g each)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • Pinch of cayenne pepper (optional)
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), to cook with (plus additional to grease the baking tray)
  • 2 Tablespoons of pesto (30 ml) (see recipe above)
  • 0.75 cup of sun-dried tomatoes (approx. 40 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 F (180 C). Grease a rimmed baking tray with avocado oil and set aside.
  2. Place the pesto ingredients in a food processor or blender and blend until fully combined. (Refrigerate any unused pesto in an airtight container for up to 3 days.)
  3. In a small bowl, combine the garlic powder and cayenne pepper, if using. Add salt and pepper, to taste. Rub the garlic mixture onto each chicken breast, covering completely.
  4. Using a sharp knife, carefully cut an opening into one side of each chicken breast to create a pocket for the stuffing.
  5. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Place each chicken breast in the skillet and sear on both sides, about 2 to 3 minutes per side. Remove the chicken from the skillet and let cool slightly.
  6. Once the chicken is cool enough to handle, spoon 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of pesto into the pocket of each chicken breast. Add an equal amount of sun-dried tomatoes to each chicken breast pocket. Place each chicken breast on the prepared baking tray.
  7. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 20 minutes until the chicken has an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C). (Be sure to measure the temperature of the chicken breast and not the stuffing.) Remove the chicken from the oven and let cool for 2 to 3 minutes.
  8. Serve the stuffed chicken breasts with a side salad, if desired.

directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 430 F (220 C). If desired, wrap the pork shoulder with butchers twine.
  2. Make a paste by combining the olive oil, lime juice, chili powder, cumin powder, paprika, and dried oregano. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Rub the paste all over the pork shoulder.

Every hour, turn the pork over with tongs and baste with the roasting liquid from the bottom of the pan. If the liquid evaporates from the bottom of the pan, cover the pork with aluminum foil for the remainder of the cooking time.
  6. When the pork is done, remove and discard any butchers twine. Let rest for 30 minutes before removing the pork from the roasting pan. Place the pork on a carving board and use 2 forks to shred it into bite-size pieces. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

ingredients:
• 3 Tablespoons of avocado oil (45 ml), divided, to cook with 
  • 4 chicken thighs (with skin on) (600 g)
  • 1 medium onion (110 g), thinly sliced
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 Tablespoons of fresh rosemary (6 g), chopped
  • 30 white button mushrooms (300 g), sliced
  • 4 carrots (200 g), grated 
  • 6 oz of kale (168 g), stems removed and chopped
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350F (180C). Grease a baking dish with avocado oil and set aside.
  2. With a clean paper towel, pat dry the chicken thighs. Season each side of the chicken with salt and pepper.
  3. Add 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of avocado oil to a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the skillet, skin side down, and cook until the skin is golden brown and crispy, about 5 to 8 minutes.
  4. Carefully turn over the chicken and cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Remove the chicken from the skillet and place in the prepared baking dish.
  5. Reduce the heat to medium-low and add the onion, garlic and fresh rosemary to the same skillet with cooking fat from the chicken. Cook until the onion is soft, about 10 to 15 minutes.
  6. Increase the heat to medium-high and continue to cook the onion until caramelized with a jam-like consistency. (Add additional avocado oil to the skillet to prevent burning, if needed.)
  7. Add the carrots and mushrooms to the skillet and cook until the vegetables are softened, about 2 to 4 minutes. Place the onion mixture around the chicken thighs in the baking dish.
  8. Place the baking dish in the oven and bake at 350F (180C) for 20 minutes. 
  9. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, toss the kale with the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil.
  10. Remove the baking dish from the oven and increase the heat to 400 F (200 C). 
  11. Scatter the kale around the chicken in the baking dish and return the baking dish to the oven.
  12. Continue to bake at 400 F (200 C) for an additional 5 minutes until the chicken is cooked through and an instant-read thermometer reaches 165 F (75 C).

name: Paleo Roasted Pork Tenderloin and Broccoli Mash
ingredients:
For the pork tenderloin -

  • 1 teaspoon of salt (5 g) (or to taste)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of pepper (1 g) (or to taste)
  • 1 teaspoon of garlic powder (3 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of Italian seasoning (1 g)
  • 1 lb of pork tenderloin (450 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), divided to cook with

For the broccoli mash -

  • 0.5 head of broccoli (225 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.25 cup of coconut milk (60 ml)
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil and set aside.
  2. In a small bowl, combine the salt, pepper, garlic powder, and Italian seasoning. Cover the tenderloin with 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil and then coat with the seasoning mixture.
  3. Add the remaining 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Place the tenderloin in the hot skillet and sear on all sides, about 2 to 3 minutes per side. Place the seared tenderloin on the prepared baking sheet.
  4. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes with an internal temperature of 145 F (63 C) for medium-rare or 160 F (71 C) for medium. Remove the tenderloin from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing.
  5. Meanwhile, add the broccoli to a steamer and steam for about 5 to 7 minutes or until soft to your liking. (Alternatively, bring to a boil about a 1/2-inch [1.25 cm] of water in a saucepan. Add the broccoli to the saucepan, cover, and steam for about 5 to 7 minutes or until soft to your liking.) 
  6. Add the steamed broccoli and coconut milk to a high-speed blender or food processor and blend until smooth. Season with salt, to taste.
  7. Serve the tenderloin with the broccoli mash.

  • 1 Tablespoon of fresh ginger (5 g), minced or finely diced
  • 2 beef steaks (400 g), sliced
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • 2 teaspoons of vinegar (10 ml) (of choice)
  • 4 green onions (20 g), chopped (for garnish)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Mince or finely dice the garlic the fresh ginger, slice the beef steaks and chop the green onions.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the garlic and fresh ginger to the skillet and saute until fragrant, about 1 minute.
  3. Add the steaks to the skillet and saute until cooked to your liking, about 3 to 5 minutes for medium-rare.
  4. Add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos and vinegar to the skillet and saute for about an additional 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Divide the beef between 2 plates and garnish with the green onions.

name: Keto Spinach Cheese Stuffed Chicken Breast with Arugula
ingredients:
• 2 oz of cashew (56 g)
  • 0.25 cup of boiling water (60 ml), for soaking cashews
  • 2 cups of spinach (60 g), chopped
  • 2 cloves of garlic (6 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml)
  • 2 slices of bacon (56 g), diced
  • 2 chicken breasts (400 g)
  • 1 large bag of arugula leaves (125 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Chop the spinach and dice the bacon.
  2. Soak the cashews in boiling water for about 30 minutes. Drain well.
  3. Preheat the oven to 400 F (200 C).
  4. In a high-speed blender or food processor, combine the soaked cashews, spinach, garlic and avocado oil to form a paste.
  5. In a small skillet, cook the bacon over medium-high heat until crispy, about 2 to 4 minutes. 
  6. Stir in the bacon to the cashew mixture. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  7. With a sharp knife, cut a deep slit into each chicken breast, careful not to slice through the entire breast. Fill each breast with equal amounts of the cashew mixture.
  8. Place the chicken on a rimmed baking sheet and bake for 30 minutes. Check with a meat thermometer that the internal temperature of the chicken reaches 165 F (75 C).
  9. Divide the arugula leaves between 2 plates and top each with a chicken breast.

name: Keto Garlic Ghee Shrimp Pasta
ingredients:
• 2 zucchinis (240 g), peeled
  • 2 Tablespoons of ghee (30 ml), to cook with
  • 4 cloves of garlic (12 g), minced or finely diced
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 0.5 lb of shrimp (225 g), defrosted if frozen
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Peel the zucchinis, mince or finely dice the garlic, break the cauliflower into small florets and defrost the shrimp if frozen.
  2. Make the zucchini noodles by using the shredding attachment of a food processor or a spiralizer or else, using a potato peeler to create pasta-like strands or shreds. Set aside.
  3. In a large nonstick skillet, melt the ghee over medium-high heat. Add the garlic and saute until fragrant, about 30 seconds.
  4. Add the cauliflower to the skillet and saute until tender to your liking, about 5 to 8 minutes.
  5. Add the shrimp to the skillet. Saute until the shrimp are pink and opaque, about 3 to 5 minutes.
  6. Add the zucchini “noodles” to the skillet. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

name: Keto Tomato Beef Stir-Fry with Cauliflower Rice
ingredients:
• For the stir-fry -
  • 1 Tablespoon of avocado oil (15 ml), to cook with
  • 0.75 lb of ground beef (338 g)
  • 2 small tomatoes (180 g), chopped
  • 0.5 cup of fresh cilantro (8 g), chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons of gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos (30 ml)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
  • For the cauliflower “rice” -
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15 ml), to cook the cauliflower with
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), processed into rice-like pieces
  • Salt, to taste
directions:
1. For the stir-fry, chop the tomatoes and fresh cilantro. For the “rice”, process cauliflower into rice-like pieces.
  2. Add the avocado oil to a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the ground beef to the skillet and stir-fry until browned, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  3. Add the tomatoes and fresh cilantro to the skillet and stir-fry until the tomatoes are soft, about 2 to 3 minutes.
  4. Add the tamari sauce or coconut aminos to the skillet and stir-fry for an additional 1 to 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Meanwhile, melt the ghee in a separate large skillet over high heat. Add the cauliflower to the skillet and saute until soft, about 5 minutes. Season with salt, to taste.
  6. Divide the “rice” between 2 plates and top with equal amounts of the stir-fry.

name: Keto Avocado Bacon and Egg Open-Faced Sandwich
ingredients:
• 4 slices of bacon (112 g)
  • 2 medium eggs
  • 1 large avocado (200 g), sliced
  • Salt and pepper, to taste

For the bread -

  • 1/3 cup of almond flour (40 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of baking powder (1 g)
  • Dash of salt
  • 1 medium egg, whisked
  • 2.5 Tablespoons of ghee (38 ml), melted (plus additional to grease the mug)
directions:
1. Slice the avocado. For the bread, whisk the egg and melt the ghee.
  2. In a nonstick skillet, cook the bacon over medium heat until crispy, about 6 to 8 minutes. Remove the bacon from the skillet and place on a paper towel-lined plate to drain.
  3. In the same skillet, add the eggs to the reserved bacon fat and fry to your liking. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Remove the eggs from the skillet and set aside.
  4. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the bread ingredients with a small whisk or fork. Pour the mixture into a greased mug.
  5. Place the mug in a microwave and cook for 90 seconds on high. Remove from the microwave and let cool slightly. Once the mug is cool enough to handle, gently remove the bread and slice into 4 pieces.
  6. Place 2 pieces of bread on each plate and top with the avocado slices, bacon, and fried eggs. Sprinkle with additional salt and pepper, if desired.

name: Keto Chocolate Hazelnut Muffins
nutrition_benifits:
Hazelnuts have a lot of health benefits. Like most nuts, hazelnuts are a good source of monounsaturated fats, which are good for your heart.

They also pack in a good amount of vitamin E, B vitamins, folate, potassium, calcium and magnesium. These valuable nutrients are tough to find in our modern diet, which has strayed pretty far away from its natural origins.

Hazelnuts also have more proanthocyanidins than other nuts. This compound may reduce your risk of urinary tract infections and blood clotting.

While you may not be familiar with proanthocyanidins, here’s one you probably are familiar with: fiber. Hazelnuts are a good source of fiber, which helps digestion and makes you feel full.

Just watch your portion size when you’re snacking on hazelnuts. They are good for you, but they also contain a lot of calories, so you don’t want to overindulge. You also don’t want to be munching your way through this keto chocolate hazelnut muffins recipe all in one sitting!
ingredients:
• 3 cups of almond flour (360 g)
  • 0.5 cup of coconut oil (120 ml), melted (plus additional to grease a 12-cup muffin pan)
  • 0.5 cup of hazelnuts (100 g), chopped
  • 4 large eggs (224 g), whisked
  • 0.5 teaspoon of ground nutmeg (1 g)
  • 0.25 teaspoon of ground cloves (1 g)
  • Stevia (or other low carb sweetener, of choice), to taste
  • 1 teaspoon of baking soda (8 g)
  • Dash of salt
  • 3 oz of 100% dark chocolate (80 g), broken into small chunks
directions:
1. Melt the coconut oil, chop the hazelnuts, whisk the eggs and break the dark chocolate into small chunks.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C). Line with paper liners or grease a 12-cup muffin pan with coconut oil and set aside.
  3. In a medium bowl, combine the almond flour, coconut oil, chopped hazelnuts, whisked eggs, ground nutmeg, ground cloves, Stevia (or sweetener, of choice), baking soda, and salt.
  4. Pour the batter into the prepared muffin pan. Place chocolate chunks into the top of each muffin, pressing them down into the batter.
  5. Place the muffin pan in the oven and bake for 18 to 20 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean when you insert it into a muffin.
  6. Let the muffins cool before serving.

name: Vegan Banana and Nut Porridge
ingredients:
• 1 cup (180 g) quinoa
  • 2 cups (480 ml) coconut milk (or almond milk)
  • maple syrup, to taste (optional)

Toppings: 

  • 2 bananas, sliced (7 oz or 200 g)
  • 1/2 cup (59 g) walnuts, chopped
  • 2 Tablespoons (24 g) chia seeds
directions:
1. Bring the plant milk to a boil, add the quinoa, and stir. Turn the heat to the lowest setting, cover, and cook for 20 minutes or until the quinoa has absorbed all the liquid and is fluffy.
  2. Stir in the maple syrup, if desired.
  3. Divide the quinoa porridge into 4 bowls and add the toppings.

name: Keto Overnight Pancake Casserole
description:
For the pancakes -

  • 1 cup of almond flour (120 g)
  • 0.25 cup of coconut flour (28 g)
  • 3 Tablespoons of erythritol (36 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of baking powder (2 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of baking soda (2 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of salt (3 g)
  • 3 eggs, lightly whisked
  • 0.5 cup of unsweetened almond milk (120 ml) (plus additional, if needed)
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), melted and cooled
  • Ghee or additional coconut oil, for cooking

For the casserole -

  • 1 cup of unsweetened almond milk (240 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of cinnamon powder (2 g)
  • 2 to 4 Tablespoons of erythritol (24 g to 48 g), to taste
  • 2 eggs, lightly whisked

For serving (optional) -

  • Ghee, fresh berries, or Keto syrup, of choice
ingredients:
For the pancakes -

  • 1 cup of almond flour (120 g)
  • 0.25 cup of coconut flour (28 g)
  • 3 Tablespoons of erythritol (36 g)
  • 1 teaspoon of baking powder (2 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of baking soda (2 g)
  • 0.5 teaspoon of salt (3 g)
  • 3 eggs, lightly whisked
  • 0.5 cup of unsweetened almond milk (120 ml) (plus additional, if needed)
  • 2 Tablespoons of coconut oil (30 ml), melted and cooled
  • Ghee or additional coconut oil, for cooking

For the casserole -

  • 1 cup of unsweetened almond milk (240 ml)
  • 1 teaspoon of cinnamon powder (2 g)
  • 2 to 4 Tablespoons of erythritol (24 g to 48 g), to taste
  • 2 eggs, lightly whisked

For serving (optional) -

  • Ghee, fresh berries, or Keto syrup, of choice
directions:
1. In a large bowl, whisk to combine the pancake ingredients to make a thick but pourable batter. If needed, add additional almond milk, 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) at a time, until the batter is pourable.
  2. Add a small amount of ghee or coconut oil to a nonstick skillet over medium heat. Pour 1/4 cup (60 ml) of the batter into the skillet and cook for about 2 minutes, until bubbles start to form.
  3. Carefully flip the pancake and cook for about 2 additional minutes until cooked through and golden brown. Set aside the pancake and repeat with the remaining batter.
  4. Cut each pancake in half and arrange in a greased casserole dish and set aside.
  5. In a medium bowl, whisk to combine the casserole ingredients until completely incorporated. Pour the casserole mixture evenly over the pancakes.
  6. Cover the casserole dish with plastic wrap or aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.
  7. When ready to cook, preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Remove and discard the plastic wrap or aluminum foil from the casserole dish. Let the casserole dish sit at room temperature as the oven preheats.
  8. Place the casserole dish in the oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the casserole is golden and cooked through.
  9. Remove the casserole from the oven and let sit for about 5 minutes before serving with optional ghee, fresh berries, or Keto syrup, if desired.

name: Keto Crispy Curry Chicken Drumsticks with Roasted Cauliflower
ingredients:
• 8 chicken drumsticks (with skin on) (1000 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of curry powder (14 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of garlic powder (10 g)
  • 0.5 head of cauliflower (300 g), broken into small florets
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30 ml) (plus additional to grease the baking sheet)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Break the cauliflower into small florets.
  2. Preheat the oven to 450 F (230 C). Lightly grease a rimmed baking sheet with olive oil and set aside.
  3. With a clean paper towel, pat dry each drumstick and set aside.
  4. In a large bowl, combine the curry powder and garlic powder. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  5. Add the drumsticks to the bowl and cover completely with the curry mixture. Place the drumsticks on the prepared baking sheet with the drumsticks not touching.
  6. Place the baking sheet in the oven and bake for 25 minutes, turning over each drumstick after 25 minutes.
  7. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, toss to combine the cauliflower with the olive oil. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Place the cauliflower on a separate rimmed baking sheet.
  8. Place the baking sheet in the oven with the drumsticks and continue to bake for 15 minutes until the cauliflower is cooked to your liking and the chicken has an internal temperature of 165 F (75 C) with a meat thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the drumstick without touching the bone. Remove both baking sheets from the oven.
  9. Place 2 drumsticks on each plate and serve with the roasted cauliflower.

name: Vegan Eggplant Bacon
ingredients:
• 1 medium eggplant (1 lb or 500 g)
  • 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) olive oil
  • 3 Tablespoons (45 ml) gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos
  • 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) maple syrup
  • 2 teaspoons (4 g) smoked paprika
  • 1/2 teaspoon (2 g) garlic powder
  • 1/2 teaspoon (1 g) ground cumin
  • 1/2 teaspoon (1 g) pepper
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 250°F (120°C).
  2. Slice the eggplant into very thin strips. This is easiest with a mandoline or a food processor but can be done carefully with a sharp knife.
  3. Mix the olive oil, tamari sauce, maple syrup, paprika, cumin, garlic powder, and pepper in a small bowl.
  4. Line a baking tray with parchment paper or foil. Arrange the eggplant strips on the tray and brush with the tamari mixture using a pastry brush. Flip the strips over and brush the other side.
  5. Bake for 30 minutes on each side. If they still aren’t as crispy as you would like, turn up the heat to 300°F (150°C) and cook for another 5-10 minutes. They will crisp up as they cool.

name: Vegan Crispy Waffles
ingredients:
• 1 1/4 Tablespoons (15 g) chia seeds
  • 6 Tablespoons (90 ml) water
  • 7 Tablespoons (53 g) almond flour
  • 7 Tablespoons (53 g) cassava flour
  • 1 Tablespoon (11 g) coconut sugar (plus additional, if desired)
  • Pinch of salt
  • 1/2 teaspoon (1 g) baking powder
  • 7/8 cup (210 ml) almond milk
  • 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) coconut oil, melted
  • Blueberries (to serve) (optional)
directions:
1. Make the “egg” by combining the chia with the water in a small bowl. Set aside.
  2. Mix the almond flour, cassava flour, coconut sugar, salt, and baking powder in a medium bowl. Add the chia “egg” mixture and almond milk to the bowl and whisk to combine.
  3. Add the melted coconut oil to the batter and whisk until well blended.
  4. Start heating a greased waffle maker. Pour in the batter and cook until crispy and holding its shape. Carefully remove the cooked waffle from the waffle maker.
  5. Sprinkle with additional coconut sugar and blueberries, if desired. Serve warm.

name: Vegan Apple Cinnamon Pancakes
ingredients:
For the Cinnamon Apples:

  • 1 teaspoon (5 ml) coconut oil
  • 1/2 medium apple (75 g), peeled and chopped
  • 1 teaspoon (2 g) cinnamon powder
  • 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) water

For the Pancakes:

  • 1/2 cup (60 g) cassava flour
  • 1/4 cup (30 g) tapioca flour
  • 1 teaspoon (2 g) cinnamon powder
  • 1 teaspoon (2 g) baking powder
  • 1/2 teaspoon (2 g) baking soda
  • 1/4 teaspoon (1 g) salt
  • 1/2 cup (120 ml) unsweetened applesauce
  • 3/4 cup (180 ml) unsweetened coconut milk (from a carton)
  • Coconut oil (for cooking)
  • maple syrup, to serve with (optional)
directions:
1. Melt 1 teaspoon (5 ml) of coconut oil in a small saucepan over low heat. Add the apple, cinnamon, and water to the saucepan and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes until soft, stirring occasionally.
  2. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine the cassava flour, tapioca flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
  3. Add the applesauce and coconut milk to the bowl and whisk until smooth.
  4. Heat a nonstick pan or skillet over medium heat. If using a pan or skillet that isn’t nonstick, add 1 to 2 teaspoons (5 to 10 ml) of coconut oil to keep the pancakes from sticking.
  5. Pour about 1/4 cup (60 ml) of the batter into the pan and gently spread with the back of the scoop.
  6. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes on the first side until bubbles form on the top of the pancake. Carefully flip and continue to cook for an additional 1 to 2 minutes until cooked through. Repeat with the remaining batter, cooking 2 or 3 pancakes each batch.
  7. Serve the pancakes immediately topped with warm cinnamon apples and optional maple syrup, if desired.

name: Vegan Morning Glory Muffins
ingredients:
• 1 1/2 cups (180 g) almond flour
  • 1/2 cup (60 g) tapioca flour
  • 2 flax eggs: 2 Tablespoons (14 g) flax meal + 6 Tablespoons (90 ml) water
  • 1 teaspoon (4 g) baking soda
  • 1/2 cup (120 ml) almond butter
  • 1/2 cup (120 ml) almond or coconut milk
  • 1/2 cup grated carrots (1.9 oz or 55 g)
  • 1/2 cup grated apples (4.2 oz or 120 g)
  • 1/2 cup chopped walnuts (2 oz or 59 g)
  • 1/2 cup raisins (2.8 oz or 80 g) (optional, if you prefer the muffins to be sweeter)
directions:
1. Make the flax egg; in a small bowl, mix together the flax meal and water and let the mixture sit for a few minutes.
  2. Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease the muffin pans and set aside.
  3. Mix all the ingredients together in a large bowl to form a thick batter.
  4. Spoon the batter into the muffin pans and bake for 25 minutes.
  5. Let cool and enjoy.

name: Keto Bacon Radish Hash
ingredients:
• 1 daikon (340 g), peeled and shredded
  • 2 large eggs (112 g), whisked
  • 4 slices of bacon (112 g), diced
  • 1 clove of garlic (3 g), peeled and minced
  • 1 teaspoon of onion powder (2 g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of avocado oil (30 ml), to cook with
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Place the shredded daikon in a towel and squeeze to try to remove as much moisture as possible.
  2. Mix all the ingredients together.
  3. Add the avocado oil to a frying pan or skillet.
  4. Pour the mixture in and cook until browned. Break into large pieces and flip over and brown the other side.

name: Keto Bacon-Wrapped Mushroom Egg Muffins
description: Bacon, eggs, mushrooms and low carb? Not sure there is a better breakfast-on-the-go out there.
ingredients:
• 12 slices of raw bacon (336 g)
  • 1 cup of mushrooms (approx. 100 g), finely chopped
  • 1/2 cup of spinach (15 g), finely chopped
  • 8 medium eggs (392 g), whisked
  • 1/2 medium onion (55 g), finely chopped
  • 1/2 cup of coconut milk (120 ml) (from a can)
  • 1 teaspoon of baking powder (2 g)
  • Salt and pepper, to taste
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).
  2. Wrap a slice of bacon around the inside of each muffin cup.
  3. Combine the remaining ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
  4. Pour the egg mixture into the muffin cups (makes 12 muffins).
  5. Bake for 25-30 minutes until the middle of the muffins isn’t liquidy anymore.

name: Keto Coconut Bacon Egg Muffins
ingredients:
• 6 medium eggs (294 g)
  • 3/4 cups of coconut flour (84 g)
  • 1/4 cup of coconut oil (60 ml)
  • 12 slices of bacon (336 g), cooked and chopped into bits
  • 1/4 cup of chives (12 g), finely chopped
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).
  2. Mix all the ingredients together and pour into the muffin cups.
  3. Bake for 25-30 minutes until the muffins are solid.
  4. Let the muffins cool and enjoy.

name: Vegan Blueberry Lemon Muffins
ingredients:
• 1 ½ cups (240 g) brown rice flour
  • 6 Tablespoons (45 g) almond flour
  • 3 Tablespoons (30 g) potato starch
  • 3/4 teaspoon (3 g) baking soda
  • 1 ½ teaspoon (3 g) baking powder
  • 6 Tablespoons (90 ml) maple syrup
  • 6 Tablespoons (90 ml) almond butter
  • 3/4 cup (180 ml) applesauce
  • 3/4 cup (180 ml) almond milk
  • 3 Tablespoons (45 ml) lemon juice
  • 1 ½ teaspoons (8 ml) vanilla extract
  • Zest (6 g) of 1 lemon
  • 1 ½ cups (225 g) blueberries
directions:
1. Make sure your almond butter is thin and runny, not so thick that it’s difficult to stir. If your almond butter has been in the fridge and is clumped together, briefly heat it in the microwave until it thins out (about 20-30 seconds).
  2. Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C). Line or grease a 12-cup muffin pan and set aside.
  3. In a large bowl, sift the brown rice flour, almond flour, potato starch, baking soda, and baking powder. Mix to combine well.
  4. In a separate bowl, mix together the maple syrup, almond butter, applesauce, almond milk, lemon juice, vanilla extract, and lemon zest.
  5. Combine the dry and wet ingredients and mix until there are no pockets of flour left. Make sure you scrape the bottom of the bowl for flour.
  6. Gently fold in the blueberries, being careful not to crush them.
  7. Divide the batter among your prepared muffin pan, filling each muffin cup almost to the top.
  8. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until cooked through and lightly golden brown on top.
  9. Remove from the oven, rest the muffins in the pan for a couple of minutes, then transfer the muffins to a wire rack to finish cooling.
  10. Store in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 3 days, or freeze for longer storage.

name: Vegan Banana and Almond Butter Sweet Potato Toast
ingredients:
• 1 medium sweet potato (4.6 oz or 130 g), sliced lengthwise into 4 pieces
  • 1/4 cup (60 ml) almond butter (or other nut butter)
  • 2 bananas (7 oz or 200 g), sliced thin
  • Nuts and seeds, chopped (for topping) (optional)
  • Maple syrup (for drizzling) (optional)
directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).
  2. Line a baking tray with parchment paper. Place the sweet potato slices onto it and bake for 30 minutes until tender.
  3. Warm up the almond butter and spread it onto the sweet potato toast, approx. 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) per slice.
  4. To assemble, top with banana slices, sprinkle with nuts and seeds, and drizzle with maple syrup, if desired.

name: Vegan Jackfruit Pulled Pork
ingredients:
• 1 can (20 oz or 565 g) of young jackfruit in water, drained (around 10 oz or 296 g drained)
  • 1 medium onion (4 oz or 110 g), finely sliced
  • 1/2 cup (120 ml) water
  • Olive oil (for cooking)

For the BBQ sauce: 

  • 1 cup (240 ml) tomato sauce 
  • 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) tomato puree 
  • 1/4 cup (60 ml) apple cider vinegar 
  • 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos 
  • 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) maple syrup 
  • 1 teaspoon (2 g) smoked paprika 
  • 1 teaspoon (2 g) chili powder 
  • 1/2 teaspoon (2 g) garlic powder 
  • 1/2 teaspoon (1 g) onion powder 
  • 1/2 teaspoon (3 g) salt 
  • 1/2 teaspoon (1 g) pepper
directions:
1. Add all the sauce ingredients into a saucepan and bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes until thickened slightly. 
  2. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add the onion and cook for 5 minutes until soft. 
  3. Add the drained jackfruit, BBQ sauce, and water to the pan. Bring to a simmer and cook for 20 to 30 minutes until the jackfruit is tender and the sauce has thickened. If needed, add additional water to the pan as the jackfruit cooks. 
  4. Once tender, shred the jackfruit using two forks and mix well. Serve in a lettuce wrap or as a sandwich.

name: Vegan Sweet Potato Sliders
ingredients:
• 1 chia egg; 1 Tablespoon (12 g) chia seeds + 2 ½ Tablespoons (37 ml) water
  • 1 can (14 oz or 400 g) of lentils, drained and rinsed
  • 1/2 medium onion (2 oz or 55 g), chopped
  • 1 large carrot (1.8 oz or 50 g), chopped
  • 1/2 cup (59 g) walnuts (or other nuts, of choice)
  • 1 clove (3 g) of garlic, peeled
  • 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) tomato paste
  • 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) gluten-free tamari sauce or coconut aminos
  • 1/4 cup (28 g) coconut flour (plus additional, if needed)
  • 3 large sweet potatoes (about 10 oz or 285 g each)
  • 2 large tomatoes (about 7 oz or 200 g each), sliced
  • Lettuce leaves (for serving)
  • Olive oil (for cooking)
  • Salt and pepper (to taste)
directions:
1. Make the chia egg; in a small bowl, mix together the chia seeds and water and let the mixture sit for a few minutes.
  2. Add the drained lentils, onion, carrot, walnuts, and garlic to the bowl of a food processor and pulse to create rough crumbs. Transfer the lentil mixture to a large bowl.
  3. Add the chia egg, tomato paste, and tamari sauce or coconut aminos to the bowl, stirring to combine. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  4. Add the coconut flour to the bowl and fold to combine. If the mixture seems too wet, add an additional 1 Tablespoon (7 g) of coconut flour. The coconut flour will soak up moisture as it sits. Therefore, it’s best to wait about 2 to 3 minutes before adding more coconut flour to the mixture.
  5. Shape the mixture into 12 small patties and place the patties on a large plate or cutting board. Cover the patties with foil or plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
  6. When you are ready to cook, preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).
  7. Cut the sweet potatoes into 24 thick slices, about ¾-inch (2 cm) each slice. Arrange the sliced sweet potatoes on a greased baking tray and drizzle with olive oil. Place the baking tray in the oven and roast for 30 minutes until tender and golden but not too soft.
  8. Meanwhile, add a drizzle of olive oil in a large frying pan or griddle over medium heat. In batches, add the burger patties to the pan and cook for 5 minutes on each side. Continue until all of the patties are cooked.
  9. Serve the sliders sandwiched between two slices of sweet potato with lettuce and sliced tomato. Add Vegan Mayonnaise or Vegan BBQ Sauce, if desired.

name: Vegan Indian Butter Chicken
ingredients:
• 3 Tablespoons (45 ml) coconut oil
  • 1 large onion (5.3 oz or 150g), sliced
  • 1 Tablespoon (5 g) fresh ginger, chopped
  • 4 cloves (12 g) of garlic, smashed
  • 2 Tablespoons (18 g) garam masala
  • 2 teaspoons (4 g) turmeric powder
  • 1 teaspoon (2 g) ground cumin
  • dash of cayenne pepper
  • 1/2 teaspoon (1 g) black pepper
  • 1 teaspoon (6 g) salt
  • 1 can (14.5 oz or 410 g) of diced tomatoes
  • 1 can (13.5 oz or 400 ml) of coconut milk
  • 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) lemon juice
  • 2 cups (340 g) chickpeas, cooked, drained and rinsed
  • 2 cups (200 g) cauliflower florets
  • 1/4 cup (4 g) fresh cilantro, chopped (for garnish)
directions:
1. Heat the coconut oil in a large pot on medium-high heat. Add the onion, ginger, garlic, and spices. Cook for 5 minutes or until the onions begin to wilt and the spices are aromatic.
  2. Add the diced tomatoes and cook for 5 more minutes, stirring occasionally.
  3. Next, add the coconut milk and turn off the heat.
  4. Carefully pour the sauce into a heat-safe blender, and blend until smooth.
  5. Return the sauce to your pot, add the lemon juice, and bring to a simmer.
  6. When the sauce begins to simmer, add the chickpeas and cauliflower. Cook for 15 minutes or until the cauliflower is tender.
  7. Stir in the cilantro before serving.

name: Vegan Dairy-Free Cheese Pizza
ingredients:
For the Crust:

  • 1 flax egg; 1 Tablespoon (7 g) flax meal + 3 Tablespoons (45 ml) water
  • 1 cup (120 g) almond flour
  • 1 cup (120 g) tapioca starch
  • 1/2 cup (48 g) chickpea flour (or coconut flour)
  • 1/3 cup (80 ml) olive oil
  • 1/3 cup (80 ml) warm water
  • 1/2 teaspoon (3 g) salt
  • 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) water

For the Vegan Mozzarella:

  • 1/2 cup (120 ml) coconut milk
  • 5 Tablespoons (38 g) tapioca starch
  • 1 Tablespoon (8 g) nutritional yeast
  • 1 teaspoon (5 ml) vinegar
  • 1/4 teaspoon (1 g) salt
  • 2 Tablespoons (30ml) water

For the Toppings:

  • 1 cup (240 ml) vegan mozzarella rounds
  • 1/4 cup (60 ml) tomato sauce (or marinara sauce)
  • 1 teaspoon (1 g) Italian seasoning
  • 1 sprig of fresh basil (3 g), de-stemmed
directions:
1. Add all the cheese ingredients to a saucepan on medium heat, and whisk together to smooth out any lumps. Continue cooking for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring until the mixture forms a stretchy, gooey ball. Refrigerate for 1 hour to allow the cheese to set.
  2. Make the flax egg: in a small bowl, mix together the flax meal and water and let the mixture sit for a few minutes.
  3. Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).
  4. In a mixing bowl, combine all the crust ingredients until a soft dough forms.
  5. On a parchment-lined baking sheet, spread the dough into a circle shape. Pre-bake the crust for 15 minutes. Remove from the oven and set aside.
  6. Remove the cheese from the refrigerator and work it into 2-inch (5 cm) rounds.
  7. Spread a thin layer of tomato sauce onto the pre-baked pizza crust leaving a 1-inch (2.5cm) border.
  8. Next, evenly distribute the vegan mozzarella rounds around the crust.
  9. Sprinkle it with Italian seasoning, and place in the oven for 20 minutes or until the cheese is melty.
  10. Remove from the oven, garnish with fresh basil leaves, and serve.
